<L>Whan &thorn;at &thorn;e knyht laide honde vpon &thorn;e ryne</L>
<L>And seide sir &thorn;er is no mor to seine</L>
<L>Bot whan &thorn;e luste to ride any where</L>
<L N="316">&YOGH;e most trill a pinne &thorn;at stant in his ere</L>
<L>Whiche .I. schal tel &yogh;ow be-twene vs tuo</L>
<L>&YOGH;e mot neuen him to what place also</L>
<L>Or to what cuntre &thorn;at &yogh;oue lust to ride</L>
<L N="320">And whan &yogh;e come &thorn;ere as &yogh;e lust to abide</L>
<L>Bid him descende and tril ano&thorn;ere pinne</L>
<L>For &thorn;ere-in li&thorn;e &thorn;e effect of al &thorn;e ginne</L>
<L>And wil doune descende and done &yogh;owre will</L>
<L N="324">And in &thorn;at place he wil abide still
<PB REF="00000231.tif" N="203"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="488"></L>
<L>If al &thorn;e werld had &thorn;e contrarie swore</L>
<L>He schal not &thorn;ens be &thorn;rowe ne bore</L>
<L>Or if &thorn;u luste bidde him &thorn;ens gone</L>
<L N="328">Tril &thorn;is pinne and he wil vanessche a-none</L>
<L>Owte of &thorn;e siht of euery maner whiht</L>
<L>And come a&yogh;eine be it daie or nyht</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at &yogh;owe lust to klepen him a&yogh;eine</L>
<L N="332">In suche a gise as .I. schal to &yogh;owe seine</L>
<L>Betwexen &yogh;owe and me and &thorn;at ful sone</L>
<L>Ride whan &yogh;ow luste &thorn;er is no more to done</L>
<L>Enformed whan &thorn;e kinge was of &thorn;e knyht</L>
<L N="336">And ha&thorn;e conseyued in his witte a riht</L>
<L>The manere and &thorn;e forme of all &thorn;is &thorn;inge</L>
<L>Ful glad and bli&thorn;e &thorn;e noble douhti kinge</L>
<L>Repeiringe to his reuel as be-forne</L>
<L N="340">The bridel is in to &thorn;e toure y-borne</L>
<L>And kepped amonge his Iewels leue and dere</L>
<L>The hors vanissed .I. not in what manere</L>
<L>Owte of her siht &yogh;e gette no mor of me</L>
<L N="344">Bot &thorn;us .I. lete in lust and Iolite</L>
<L>&thorn;is kambynscan his lordes festinge</L>
<L>Til wele nyhe &thorn;e daie be-gan to springe<NOTE PLACE="end">[One line blank in the MS.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="2" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART II.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>The norice of digestion is slepe</L>
<L N="348">Gan on hem winke and bad hem take kepe</L>
<L>That muche mete and labur wold haue rest</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; a galpinge mou&thorn;e he al hem kest</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;at it was time to lye a-downe</L>
<L N="352">For blode was in his dominacione<MILESTONE N="83b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Chirise&thorn; blode naturs frende quod he</L>
<L>Thei &thorn;onken him galpinge be two be &thorn;re</L>
<L>An euery whiht gan drawene him to his rest</L>
<L N="356">As slepe hem bad &thorn;ei toke it for &thorn;e best
<PB REF="00000232.tif" N="204"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="489"></L>
<L>Hir dremes schal nouht be told for me</L>
<L>Ful was here heuedes of fumosite</L>
<L>That cause&thorn; dreme of wiche &thorn;er is no charge</L>
<L N="360">Thei slepen til it was prime large</L>
<L>The most parte bot it were Canace</L>
<L>Sche was ful mesurable as wemmen be</L>
<L>For of hir fader had sche take hir leue</L>
<L N="364">To go to rest sone after it was eue</L>
<L>Hir lust nou&yogh;t apalled for to bue</L>
<L>For on &thorn;e morwe vnfestlyche for to se</L>
<L>And sleped hir furst slepe and wooke</L>
<L N="368">For suche a ioye sche in hire hert toke</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e of hir wheynte ringe and of hir meroure</L>
<L>&THORN;at twenty times sche chaunged hir coloure</L>
<L>And in hir slepe riht for impressione</L>
<L N="372">Of hir meroure sche hadde a visione</L>
<L>Where for or &thorn;at &thorn;e sonne vp gan glide</L>
<L>Sche cleped vpon hire Maistres hire be-side</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;at hir luste for to rise</L>
<L N="376">Thes olde wemme &thorn;at bene gladly wise</L>
<L>As is her Maistres answard hire anone</L>
<L>And seide Madame wheder wil &yogh;e gone</L>
<L>Thus erely folke been al in rest</L>
<L N="380">.I. wil quod sche arise for me lest</L>
<L>No longer slepe bot to walken aboute</L>
<L>Hire Maistres clepe&thorn;e wimmen a grete route</L>
<L>And vp &thorn;ei resen wele ten or twelue</L>
<L N="384">Vp rise&thorn; ffrische Canacee hire selue</L>
<L>As Rody and briht as &thorn;eyhe &thorn;e &yogh;onge sonne</L>
<L>&thorn;at in &thorn;e ram ten degres is vp ronne</L>
<L>Noon hier was he whan sche redy was</L>
<L N="388">And for&thorn; sche walke&thorn; esili apase</L>
<L>Arraid afte &thorn;e lusti seson suote</L>
<L>Lyhtly for to pleye and walk on fote</L>
<L>Not bot .v. or .vj. of hir Mein&yogh;e</L>
<L N="392">For in a trenche fere in &thorn;e parke go&thorn; sche
<PB REF="00000233.tif" N="205"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="490"></L>
<L>The vapor whiche &thorn;at fro &thorn;e er&thorn;e glode</L>
<L>Make&thorn; &thorn;e sonne to seme rody and brode</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles it was so faire a siht<MILESTONE N="84a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="396">&THORN;at it maad all hir hertes for to liht</L>
<L>What for &thorn;e seson and &thorn;e morneynge</L>
<L>And for &thorn;e foules &thorn;at sche herde singe</L>
<L>For riht anone sche wist what &thorn;ei mente</L>
<L N="400">Riht be hir songe and knowe al her entente</L>
<L>The knotte whi &thorn;at euery tale is tolde</L>
<L>If it be taried til lust be colde</L>
<L>Of hem &thorn;at han it herkened after &yogh;ore</L>
<L N="404">The sauoure passe&thorn;e euer &thorn;e langere more</L>
<L>For fulsomnesse of prolixite</L>
<L>And be &thorn;is same reson &thorn;enke&thorn; me</L>
<L>.I. schol vnto &thorn;e knotte condescende</L>
<L N="408">And make of hire walkinge sone an ende</L>
<L>Amydde a tree for-drie as white as chalke</L>
<L>As Canacee was pleyinge in hir walke</L>
<L>Ther sat a fawcon ouer hir heued ful hihe</L>
<L N="412">That wi&thorn; a pitous voice so gan to crie</L>
<L>That al &thorn;e woode resed of hire Crie</L>
<L>[And beten hadde hire self so pitouslye<MILESTONE UNIT="MS Reg. 18 C ii folio" N="87a">]</L>
<L>wi&thorn; bo&thorn;e hire wenges til &thorn;e rede blode</L>
<L N="416">Ran endlonge &thorn;e tre &thorn;er as sche stode</L>
<L>And euer in one sche cried alweie and schryht</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; hir beke hire seluen so sche piht</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ere ne was tigre ne cruel beste</L>
<L N="420">&thorn;at dwelle&thorn; ey&thorn;er in wode or in foreste</L>
<L>&thorn;at nolde haue wepped If &thorn;at wepe he cou&thorn;e</L>
<L>For sorwe sche shreyht for hir alweie so low&thorn;e</L>
<L>For &thorn;ar nas neuer &yogh;it man on liue</L>
<L N="424">If &thorn;at .I. cou&thorn;e a faukon wele discriue</L>
<L>&thorn;at herd of suche ano&thorn;er of fairnes</L>
<L>As wele of plumage as of gentilnes</L>
<L>Of schap of &thorn;at &thorn;at myht rekened be</L>
<L N="428">A faukon peregryne &thorn;an semed sche
<PB REF="00000234.tif" N="206"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="491"></L>
<L>Of fremed londe and euer-more as sche stode</L>
<L>Sche swowned now and now for lak of blode</L>
<L>Til wel nyhe is sche fallen fro &thorn;e tree</L>
<L N="432">This faire kinges douhter &thorn;is Canace</L>
<L>&thorn;at on her finger bare &thorn;e wheynte ringe</L>
<L>Thorwe whiche sche vnderstod wele euery &thorn;inge</L>
<L>&thorn;at any foule may in his leden seine</L>
<L N="436">And kowde ansewere him in his leden a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>Ha&thorn;e vnderstonde &thorn;at &thorn;is faukon seide</L>
<L>And wel nyhe for reu&thorn;e almoste sche deide</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e tre sche go&thorn;e ful hastely<MILESTONE N="84b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="440">And on &thorn;is faukon loked ful pitously .</L>
<L>And held hir lap abrode for wele sche wist</L>
<L>The fawkon most fal fro &thorn;e twyst</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at it swoned next for lak of blode</L>
<L N="444">A longe while to waite hire sche stode</L>
<L>Til att &thorn;e last sche spak in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;e hauke as &yogh;e schal after here</L>
<L>&para; What it &thorn;e cause if it be to tell</L>
<L N="448">That &yogh;e bue in &thorn;is furial peine of hell</L>
<L>Quod Canacee vnto &thorn;is hauke aboue</L>
<L>Is &thorn;is for sorwe of de&thorn;e or losse of loue</L>
<L>For as [I] trowe &thorn;es bene causes two</L>
<L N="452">&THORN;at Causen moste a gentil hert woo</L>
<L>Of o&thorn;er harme it rede&thorn; not to speke</L>
<L>For &thorn;i &yogh;oureselfe vpon &yogh;oure self &yogh;owe wreke</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at proue&thorn; wele &thorn;at ey&thorn;er ire or drede</L>
<L N="456">Mot bene encheson of &yogh;oure crewel dede</L>
<L>Sen &thorn;at .I. see none o&thorn;er whiht &yogh;oue chace</L>
<L>For loue of god so do &yogh;owre self grace</L>
<L>Or what maye be &yogh;oure helpe for west nor este</L>
<L N="460">Ne sawhe .I. neuere ar nowe no brid no beste</L>
<L>That ferd wi&thorn; him self so pitously</L>
<L>&YOGH;e slee me wi&thorn; &yogh;oure sorwe verrayly</L>
<L>.I. haue of &yogh;owe so grete compassione</L>
<L N="464">For goddes loue com fro &thorn;e tre a-downe
<PB REF="00000235.tif" N="207"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="492"></L>
<L>And as .I. am a kinges douhter trewe</L>
<L>If &thorn;at .I. verrayly &thorn;e cause knewe</L>
<L>Of yowre disease if laie in my myht</L>
<L N="468">.I. wold amend it or &thorn;at it wer nyht</L>
<L>As wissely helpe me grete god of kinde</L>
<L>And herbes schal .I. riht y-nowe finde</L>
<L>To hele wi&thorn;&thorn;e &yogh;owre hurtes hastely</L>
<L N="472">Tho schright &thorn;is faukon more pitously</L>
<L>Than euer sche dede and fel to grounde a-none</L>
<L>And lie&thorn; on swowne dede as any stone</L>
<L>This Canace ha&thorn;e in hir lappe hir take</L>
<L N="476">Vn-to &thorn;at time sche gan of swoune a-wake</L>
<L>And after &thorn;at sche of swowne gan a-braide</L>
<L>Riht in hir haukes loden &thorn;us sche seid</L>
<L>That pite renne&thorn; sone in gentil hert</L>
<L N="480">Feleynge is similitude in peines smert</L>
<L>Is proued al daie as men maie it see<MILESTONE N="85a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As wele be werke as be auctorite</L>
<L>For gentil hert kepe&thorn; gentillesse</L>
<L N="484">I. see wele &thorn;at &yogh;e hane of me destresse</L>
<L>Compassione my faire Canacee</L>
<L>Of verrey wommanly benyngnite</L>
<L>&THORN;at nature in &yogh;oure principles ha&thorn;e sett</L>
<L N="488">Bot for no hope for to fare &thorn;e bett</L>
<L>Bot for to obeie vnto &yogh;oure hert fre</L>
<L>And for to maken o&thorn;ere be war be me</L>
<L>As be &thorn;e whelpe chastized es &thorn;e lyon</L>
<L N="492">Riht for &thorn;at cause and for &thorn;at conclusion</L>
<L>While &thorn;at .I. haue a leiser and a space.</L>
<L>Myne harme .I. wil confessen ar .I. pace</L>
<L>And euer while &thorn;at one hire sorwe tolde</L>
<L N="496">&thorn;e to&thorn;er weped as sche to water wolde</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at &thorn;e faukon bad hir to be still</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; a sike &thorn;us sche seide hir till</L>
<L>There .I. was bred alas &thorn;at ilke daie</L>
<L N="500">And fosterd in a roche of Marble graie
<PB REF="00000236.tif" N="208"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="493"></L>
<L>So tenderly &thorn;at no &thorn;inge eyled me</L>
<L>.I. wist nouht what was aduersite</L>
<L>Til .I. kou&thorn;e flie ful hihe vnder &thorn;e skye</L>
<L N="504">Tho dwelled a tarselet me fast bye</L>
<L>&THORN;at semed wele of al gentillesse</L>
<L>Al were he ful of treson and of falsenesse</L>
<L>It is wrapped vnder humble charite</L>
<L N="508">And vnder hiewe of trow&thorn;e and in suche manere</L>
<L>Vnde[r] plesance and vnder besi peine</L>
<L>&THORN;at no wyht cou&thorn; haue wende he cou&thorn; feyne</L>
<L>So depe in greine he deiede his coloures</L>
<L N="512">Riht as a serpent hide&thorn; him vnder floures</L>
<L>til he may se his time for to bite</L>
<L>Riht so &thorn;is god of loue Ipocrite</L>
<L>Do&thorn;e so his cerimonijs and obeiceances</L>
<L N="516">And keped in semblant al his obseruances</L>
<L>And soune&thorn; in to gentilles of loue</L>
<L>As in to a tombe is al &thorn;e faire a-boue</L>
<L>And vnder is &thorn;e cours suche as .I. wote</L>
<L N="520">Swyche was &thorn;is ypocrit bo&thorn;e colde and hoote</L>
<L>And in &thorn;is wise he serued his entent</L>
<L>&thorn;at saue &thorn;e fende no man wist what he mente</L>
<L>Til he so longe had wepen a[n]d compleyned<MILESTONE N="85b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="524">And mony a &yogh;ere his seruice to me feyned</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at myne herte to pytous and to nyce</L>
<L>Al Innoce of his crowel malice</L>
<L>For-fered of his de&thorn; as &thorn;ouht me</L>
<L N="528">Vpon his o&thorn;es and his surete</L>
<L>Graunted him loue vpon &thorn;is condicione</L>
<L>&thorn;at euer mo myn honoure and renoune</L>
<L>Were saued bo&thorn; priue and aperte</L>
<L N="532">This is to seine &thorn;at after his desert</L>
<L>.I. &yogh;af him al myn herte and al myn &thorn;ouht</L>
<L>God woote and he and o&thorn;er wise nouht</L>
<L>And toke his hert in chaunge of myne for aye</L>
<L N="536">Bot so&thorn;e is seide gon si&thorn;en mony a daye
<PB REF="00000237.tif" N="209"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="494"></L>
<L>A trew wihte and a &thorn;efe &thorn;enke&thorn; nat one</L>
<L>And whan he sawe &thorn;e &thorn;inge so fer y-.gone</L>
<L>That .I. graunted him fully my loue</L>
<L N="540">In suche a gise as .I. haue seide a-boue</L>
<L>And &yogh;euen him my trewe herte as fre</L>
<L>As he swore he &yogh;aue his hert to me</L>
<L>Anone &thorn;is Tigre ful of doublenesse</L>
<L N="544">Fele on his knees wi&thorn; so deuoute humblesse</L>
<L>With hihe reuerence and as be his chier</L>
<L>So like a gentil louere of manere</L>
<L>So rauesshed as it semed for &thorn;e Ioye</L>
<L N="548">&thorn;at neuer Iason ne Paris of troye</L>
<L>Iason certes ne none o&thorn;ere man</L>
<L>Syn lame&thorn; was &thorn;at al&thorn;er first be-gan</L>
<L>To louen two as writen folke by-forne</L>
<L N="552">Ne neuer si&thorn;e &thorn;e first manne was borne</L>
<L>Ne cou&thorn;e man be tuenty &thorn;ousand parte</L>
<L>Counterfete &thorn;e sophimes of his arte</L>
<L>Ne war wor&thorn;i to vnbokle his galoche</L>
<L N="556">Ther dowblenesse or feyneinge schold aproche</L>
<L>Ne so kou&thorn;e &thorn;onke a whight as he did me</L>
<L>His maner was an heuen for to see</L>
<L>Til any womman were sche neuer so wise</L>
<L N="560">So peynted he and kembe&thorn; att pinte deuise</L>
<L>Als wele is worde as his countenance</L>
<L>And .I. so loued him for his Obeissance</L>
<L>And for &thorn;e treu&thorn;e .I. demed in his herte</L>
<L N="564">That if so were &thorn;at any &thorn;inge him smerte</L>
<L>Al ware it neuer so litel and .I. it wiste<MILESTONE N="86a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Me &thorn;ouht .I. felt de&thorn; att myne hert twiste</L>
<L>And schortly so fer for&thorn;e &thorn;is &thorn;inge went</L>
<L N="568">&thorn;at my will ha&thorn; his willes Instrument</L>
<L>This to seine my will obeide his will</L>
<L>In al &thorn;inge as fer as reson fill</L>
<L>Kepeinge &thorn;e boundes of my worschip euere</L>
<L N="572">Ne neuer had .I. &thorn;inge so lefe ne leuere
<PB REF="00000238.tif" N="210"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="495"></L>
<L>As him; god woote ne neuer schal no mo</L>
<L>This last longer &thorn;an a &yogh;ere or two</L>
<L>That .I. supposed of him no &thorn;inge bot goode</L>
<L N="576">Bot finaly &thorn;us att &thorn;e laste it stode</L>
<L>That fortune wolde &thorn;at he most twynne</L>
<L>Owte of &thorn;at place whiche &thorn;at .I. was inne</L>
<L>Where me was woo it is no questione</L>
<L N="580">.I. kan nou&yogh;t make of hit discripcione</L>
<L>For o &thorn;inge dar .I. tell boldely</L>
<L>.I. knowe what is &thorn;e peine of de&thorn;e &thorn;er-by</L>
<L>Suche harme .I. felte for he ne myht be-leue</L>
<L N="584">So on a daye of me he toke is leue</L>
<L>So sorwfully eke &thorn;at .I. wende verrayly</L>
<L>That he had feled as muche harme as .I.</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at .I. herd him speke and sawe his hiewe</L>
<L N="588">Bot na&thorn;eles .I. &thorn;ouht he was so trewe</L>
<L>And eke &thorn;at he repaire scholde agayne</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; inne a lite while so&thorn;e to seine</L>
<L>And reson wolde eke &thorn;at he mot go</L>
<L N="592">For his honour as oft happe&thorn; so</L>
<L>&thorn;at maade vertue of necessite</L>
<L>And toke it wele se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;at it most be</L>
<L>As .I. best myht .I. hidde fro him my sorwe</L>
<L N="596">And toke him by &thorn;e honde seint Iohn to borwe</L>
<L>And seid &thorn;us. lo .I. am &yogh;oures al</L>
<L>Be&thorn;e suche as .I. haue. bue to &yogh;owe and schal</L>
<L>What he answarde it nede&thorn; nouht reherse</L>
<L N="600">Who can sei bet &thorn;an he whou kan do werse</L>
<L>Whan he ha&thorn; al wele seide &thorn;an ha&thorn; he done</L>
<L>Ther-for be-houe&thorn; him a ful longe spone</L>
<L>&thorn;at schal eten wi&thorn; a fende &thorn;us herd .I. seie</L>
<L N="604">So att &thorn;e last he mote for&thorn;e his weye</L>
<L>And for&thorn;e he flye&thorn; til he cam where him liste</L>
<L>Whan it com him to purpos for to riste.</L>
<L>I trowe he hadde &thorn;ilke text in mynde.<MILESTONE N="86b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="608">&THORN;at al &thorn;inge repaireinge to his kinde
<PB REF="00000239.tif" N="211"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="496"></L>
<L>Glade&thorn; him selfe &thorn;us seine men as .I. gesse</L>
<L>Men loue of propre kinde newefangelnesse</L>
<L>As birdes done &thorn;at men in cage fede</L>
<L N="612">For &thorn;ouhe &thorn;e nyht and daie take of hem hede</L>
<L>And strewe hir cage faire and soft as silke</L>
<L>And &yogh;iue hem suger hony brede and melke</L>
<L>&YOGH;it riht anone as &thorn;at his dore is huppe</L>
<L N="616">He wi&thorn;&thorn;e wi&thorn; his fete wi[l] sporne doune his cuppe</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e wode he wil and wermes ete</L>
<L>So new fongel be &thorn;ei of her mete</L>
<L>And louen none leueres of propre kinde</L>
<L N="620">Ne gentilles of maie hem binde</L>
<L>So ferde &thorn;is tarselet alas &thorn;is daie</L>
<L>&thorn;ouhe he ware gentil borne frische and gaie</L>
<L>And goodly for to see and humble and free</L>
<L N="624">He sawe vp-on a time a kite fle</L>
<L>And sodanly he loued &thorn;is kite soo</L>
<L>&thorn;at al his loue is clene fro me goo</L>
<L>And ha&thorn; his trou&thorn;e falsed in &thorn;is wise</L>
<L N="628">&thorn;us ha&thorn;e &thorn;e kite my loue in her seruise</L>
<L>And .I. am lorne wi&thorn;-oute remedie</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde &thorn;is fawkon gan to crie</L>
<L>And swowned eft in Canace barme</L>
<L N="632">Grete was &thorn;e sorwe of &thorn;at haukes harme</L>
<L>That Canacee and al hir wemmen maade</L>
<L>Thei nest howe &thorn;at &thorn;ei myht &thorn;e faukon glade</L>
<L>Bot Canace home bere&thorn; hir in lappe</L>
<L N="636">And softely in plastres gan hir wrappe</L>
<L>&thorn;er as sche wi&thorn;e hire beke hadde hert hir selue</L>
<L>Nowe can nou&yogh;t Canace bot herbes delue</L>
<L>Oute of &thorn;e grounde and maken salues newe</L>
<L N="640">Of herbes precious and fyne of hewe</L>
<L>To helen wi&thorn; &thorn;e hauke fro daie to nyht</L>
<L>Sche do&thorn;e hire besines and al hir myht</L>
<L>And be hir beddes hede sche maade a mewe</L>
<L N="644">And couerd it wi&thorn; veluetes blewe
<PB REF="00000240.tif" N="212"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="497"></L>
<L>In singne of treu&thorn;e &thorn;at is in wemme[n] seene.</L>
<L>And al wi&thorn;e-oute &thorn;e mewe is peynted grene</L>
<L>In whiche war peynted as &thorn;is fals fowles</L>
<L N="648">As bien &thorn;is tideues tarseletz and owles.</L>
<L>Riht for dispite was peinted hem by side<MILESTONE N="87a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Pyes on hem for to crie and Chide</L>
<L>Thus lete .I. Canace hir hauke kepeinge</L>
<L N="652">.I. wil no more nowe speke of hire ringe</L>
<L>Til it come eft to purpos for to seine</L>
<L>Howe &thorn;at &thorn;is fawkon gatt hir loue a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>Repentant as &thorn;e storie telle&thorn; vs</L>
<L N="656">Be Mediacion of Camballus</L>
<L>&thorn;e kinges son of whiche .I. &yogh;owe tolde</L>
<L>Bot hense for&thorn;e .I. wil proces holde</L>
<L>To speken of aventures and of batailes</L>
<L N="660">&thorn;at &yogh;it was neuer herde so grete merveiles</L>
<L>ffirst wil .I. tell &yogh;owe of Cambynskan</L>
<L>That in his time mony a Cite wan</L>
<L>And after wil .I. speke of Algarsif</L>
<L N="664">Howe &thorn;at he wanne Theodora to his wif</L>
<L>For whan ful oft in grete perile he was</L>
<L>Ne had he bue holpen be &thorn;e hors of bras</L>
<L>And after wil .I. speke of Camballo</L>
<L N="668">&THORN;at fauht in listes wi&thorn; &thorn;e bre&thorn;erne tuo</L>
<L>ffor Canace ar &thorn;at he my[ht] hir wynne</L>
<L N="670">And &thorn;ere .I. left .I. &thorn;enke a&yogh;eine be-gynne</L>
<L>Bot .I. wil here nowe maake a knotte<NOTE PLACE="marg">[8 <I>spurious lines</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L>To &thorn;e time it come next to my lotte</L>
<L>For here be felawes behinde an hepe treulye</L>
<L N="4">&thorn;at wolden talke ful besilye</L>
<L>And haue her sporte as wele as .I.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e daie passe&thorn; fast certanly</L>
<L>Therefore oste take&thorn; nowe goode heede</L>
<L N="8">Who schall next tell and late him speede</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit fabula</B> Armigeri.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="D" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000241.tif" N="213">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="334">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>D.</B> FRAGMENT V.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. WIFE OF BATH'S PREAMBLE.</HEAD>
<HEAD>LANSDOWNE MS.</HEAD>
<HEAD>Incipit prologus vxoris/. de Bathe.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 87</NOTE></HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1*">THan schortly ansewarde &thorn;e wife of Bathe<NOTE PLACE="marg">spurious link</NOTE></L>
<L N="2*">And swore a wonder grete ha&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">spurious link</NOTE></L>
<L N="3*">Be goddes bones .I. wil tel next<NOTE PLACE="marg">spurious link</NOTE></L>
<L N="4*">.I. will nouht glose bot saye &thorn;e text<NOTE PLACE="marg">spurious link</NOTE></L>
<L N="1">Experiment &thorn;ouhe none auctorite</L>
<L>Where in &thorn;is werlde is riht y-nouhe for me</L>
<L>To speke of woo &thorn;at is in mariage</L>
<L N="4">For lordeinges sen .I. twelue &yogh;ere was of Age</L>
<L>&THORN;onked be god &thorn;at eterne alyue</L>
<L>Hosbondes att &thorn;e cherche dor .I. haue hadde five</L>
<L>If .I. so oft myht haue wedded be</L>
<L N="8">Bot al were wor&thorn;i men in here degre.</L>
<L>Bot me was tolde certein nou&yogh;t longe a-gon es<MILESTONE N="87b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;at se&thorn;en criste ne went neuer bot ones</L>
<L>To weddeinge in &thorn;e Cane of Galile</L>
<L N="12">That be &thorn;ilke ensample tauht he me</L>
<L>&THORN;at .I. ne scholde wedded bue bot ones</L>
<L>Herke eke loo suche a scharpe worde for &thorn;e nones</L>
<L>Be side a well ihesu god and man</L>
<L N="16">Spak in repreue of &thorn;e Samaritan</L>
<L>&THORN;ou hast hi-hadde fyve husbondes quod he</L>
<L>And &thorn;at ilke man &thorn;at nowe ha&thorn;e &thorn;e</L>
<L>Is nouht &thorn;in husbonde &thorn;us seide he serteine</L>
<L N="20">What he ment &thorn;erby .I. kan nouht seine</L>
<L>Well . Bot &thorn;at .I. ax. whi &thorn;e fift mane</L>
<L>Was none husbonde to &thorn;e Semaritane</L>
<L>How many myht sche haue in mariage</L>
<L N="24">&YOGH;it herd .I. neuer tell in myne age
<PB REF="00000242.tif" N="214"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="335"></L>
<L>vpon &thorn;is nombre diffinicione</L>
<L>Men maie devine and glosene vp and downe</L>
<L>Bot wele .I. wote expresse wi&thorn;-oute lye</L>
<L N="28">God bad vs wax and multiplye</L>
<L>&THORN;at gentil tixt can .I. wele vnder-stonde</L>
<L>Eke wele .I. he seide myn husbonde</L>
<L>Scholde lete fader and moder and tak to me</L>
<L N="32">Bot of no nombre mencione maade he</L>
<L>Of bygamy or of octagamye</L>
<L>Whi scholde y &thorn;an of it haue velanye</L>
<L>Loke here &thorn;e wisman kinge Salomon</L>
<L N="36">.I. trowe he had wyues mo &thorn;an one</L>
<L>Now wolde god it leuefull were to me</L>
<L>To be refresched half so oft as he</L>
<L>Whiche &yogh;ift of god had he for al his wyves</L>
<L N="40">No man ha&thorn;e suche &thorn;at in &thorn;is werld on lyue is</L>
<L>God wote &thorn;is noble kinge as to my witt</L>
<L>&THORN;e first nyht he hadde mony a mery fitt</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; iche of hem so wele was him on live</L>
<L N="44">Blissed be god &thorn;at .I. haue wedded fyue</L>
<L>Welcome be &thorn;e sext whan &thorn;at euer he schall</L>
<L>For so&thorn;e .I. wil nou&yogh;t kepe chaste in all</L>
<L>Whan myn husbonde is from &thorn;e werlde gone</L>
<L N="48">Son cresten man schal wedde me a-none</L>
<L>For &thorn;an &thorn;e Apostle sei&thorn;e &thorn;at .I. am fre</L>
<L>To wedde on goddes halue where it like&thorn; me</L>
<L>He sei&thorn;e to be wedede is no sinne<NOTE PLACE="marg">Melius est nubere quam vri</NOTE></L>
<L>Better is to be wedded &thorn;an to berne<MILESTONE N="88a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="53">What rekke&thorn;e me &thorn;ouhe folke seie velanye</L>
<L>Of schrewed lame&thorn; and his Bigamye</L>
<L>.I. wote wele Abraham was an holy man</L>
<L N="56">And Iacob eke as fer as euere y kan</L>
<L>And eche of hem had wyves mo &thorn;an tuo</L>
<L>And mony ano&thorn;er holy man also</L>
<L>Wher can &yogh;e seye in any maner age</L>
<L N="60">&THORN;at vs god defended Mariage
<PB REF="00000243.tif" N="215"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="336"></L>
<L>Be expresse worde .I. praie &yogh;owe telle&thorn; me</L>
<L>Or where commaunded he virginite</L>
<L>.I. wote as wele as &yogh;e it is no drede</L>
<L N="64">The Apostle whan he speke&thorn;e of Maidenhede</L>
<L>He seide &thorn;ere-of precept had .I. none</L>
<L>Men mai consel a womman to bene one</L>
<L>Bott counseillinge is no comandement</L>
<L N="68">He put it in owre owen Iugement</L>
<L>For had god commanded maidenhede</L>
<L>&thorn;an hadde he dampned wedinge wi&thorn; &thorn;e dede</L>
<L>And certes if &thorn;ere were no sede .I.-sowe</L>
<L N="72">virginite &thorn;an where-of schold it growe</L>
<L>Poule dorst nouht commanden att &thorn;e leste</L>
<L>A &thorn;inge of whiche his maistre &yogh;af him none heste</L>
<L>The darte is sett vp for virginitee</L>
<L N="76">Chase who so maye . who so renne&thorn; best let see</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;is worde is nouht take of euery whiht</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;ere as god wolde gif it of his myht</L>
<L>.I. wote wele &thorn;at &thorn;e Apostle was a maide</L>
<L N="80">Bot Na&thorn;eles &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at he wrote or saide</L>
<L>He wolde &thorn;at euery wight were suche as he</L>
<L>All ne is bot counseill to virginite</L>
<L>And for to be a wif he &yogh;aue me leue</L>
<L N="84">Of Indulgence so is it of no repreue</L>
<L>To wedde me if &thorn;at my . make dye</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-oute excepcione of bigamye</L>
<L>Al were it goode no womman for to touche</L>
<L N="88">He ment as in his body or his couche</L>
<L>For perill is bo&thorn;e to touche and for to assemble</L>
<L>&YOGH;e knowe what &thorn;is ensample maie resemble</L>
<L>&THORN;is all and somme he helde virginite</L>
<L N="92">Mor perfite &thorn;an wedded in frelete.</L>
<L>Freelte clepe .I. nouht bot &thorn;at he and sche<MILESTONE N="88b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Wolde lede here life al in chastite</L>
<L>.I. graunte it wele .I. haue none envye</L>
<L N="96">&thorn;ouhe maidenhed prefer bygamye
<PB REF="00000244.tif" N="216"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="337"></L>
<L>It like&thorn; hem to be clene in body and goste</L>
<L>Of myne astate .I. wil make no boste</L>
<L>For wele &yogh;e knowe a lorde in his housholde</L>
<L N="100">Ha&thorn;e nouht euery vessel of golde</L>
<L>Some biene of tree and done lorde seruise</L>
<L>God clepe&thorn; folke to him in sunder wise</L>
<L>And eueryche ha&thorn; of god a proper &yogh;ift</L>
<L N="104">Som &thorn;is. som &thorn;at. as him like&thorn; to schift</L>
<L>Virginite is grete perfectione</L>
<L>And conscience eke wi&thorn; deuocione</L>
<L>Bot crist &thorn;at of perfection is well</L>
<L N="108">Bad nouht euery whight he schold sell</L>
<L>All &thorn;at he hadde and &yogh;iue it to &thorn;e pore</L>
<L>And in suche wise folowe him and his lore</L>
<L>He spak to hem &thorn;at wolden leue perfitelye</L>
<L N="112">And lordeynges be &yogh;oure leue &thorn;at am nou&yogh;t .I.</L>
<L>.I. wyl be-stowe &thorn;e flowre of al myne age</L>
<L>In charite and fruyte of Mariage</L>
<L>Tel me also to what conclusione</L>
<L N="116">Were membres maade of generacione</L>
<L>And of so perfit wise and why y-wrouht</L>
<L>Treste&thorn; riht wele &thorn;ei were nouht maad for nouht</L>
<L>Glose who so will and sei bo&thorn;e vp and doune</L>
<L N="120">&thorn;at &thorn;ei were maad for purgacione</L>
<L>Of vryne. and owre bo&thorn;e &thorn;inges smale</L>
<L>Were eke to knowe a female frome a male</L>
<L>And for none o&thorn;ere cause what seie &yogh;e noo</L>
<L N="124">&thorn;e experience woote it is nou&yogh;t soo</L>
<L>So &thorn;at &thorn;e clerkes be not wi&thorn; me wro&thorn;e</L>
<L>.I. sei &thorn;is &thorn;et &thorn;ei maked bue for bo&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;is is to seine for Office and for ese</L>
<L N="128">Of engenderinge &thorn;ere we nouht god displese</L>
<L>Whi scholden men elles in hire bokes sette</L>
<L>&thorn;at man schal &yogh;elde to his wife his dette</L>
<L>Nowe where-wi&thorn; scholde he paye his payment</L>
<L N="132">If &thorn;at he ne vsed his sely instrument
<PB REF="00000245.tif" N="217"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="338"></L>
<L>Than were &thorn;ei maade vpon a creature</L>
<L>To purge vryne and eke for engendrure</L>
<L>Bot .I. sei nou&yogh;t &thorn;at euery wyht is holde<MILESTONE N="89a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="136">&thorn;at ha&thorn;e suche hernays as .I. to &yogh;ow of tolde</L>
<L>To gone and vsen hem in engendrure</L>
<L>Than scholde men take of chastite no cure</L>
<L>Criste was a mayden and schapen as a man</L>
<L N="140">And mony a seinte so&thorn;&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is werlde began</L>
<L>&YOGH;it leued &thorn;ei euer in perfite charite</L>
<L>.I. nyl envye wi&thorn; no virginite</L>
<L>Lete hem ete brede of pured whete sed</L>
<L N="144">And late vs wyues ete barly brede</L>
<L>And &yogh;it wi&thorn; barly brede Marke tel can</L>
<L>Owre lorde ihesu refrissched mony a man</L>
<L>In suche astate &thorn;at god ha&thorn; cleped vs</L>
<L N="148">.I. wil perseuere .I. am nouht precious</L>
<L>In whifehode wil .I. vse myne Instrument</L>
<L>As frely as my maker ha&thorn; it sent</L>
<L>If .I. be daungerous god gif me sorwe</L>
<L N="152">Myne husbond schal it haue bo&thorn;e eue and morwe</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at him luste com for&thorn;e and paie his dette</L>
<L>An husbond .I. wil haue .I. wil not lette</L>
<L N="155">Whiche schal be bo&thorn;e my dettour and my &thorn;rall</L>
<L>And haue his tribulacione wi&thorn; all<NOTE PLACE="marg">&para; Ad Corinthios .vijo. vir sui corporis potes|tatem non habet set mulier.</NOTE></L>
<L>Vpon his flesche while &thorn;at .I. am his wif</L>
<L>.I. haue &thorn;e powere dureinge al my lif</L>
<L>Vpon his propre body and not he</L>
<L N="160">Riht &thorn;us &thorn;e Apostle tolde to me</L>
<L>And bad owre husbondes for to loue vs wele</L>
<L>Al &thorn;is sentens me like&thorn; euery dele</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vp stert &thorn;e pardoner and &thorn;at anone</L>
<L N="164">Nowe dame quod he be god and be seinte Iohn</L>
<L>&YOGH;e bue a noble prechoure in &thorn;is cas</L>
<L>.I. was aboute to wed a wif alas</L>
<L>What schold .I. by it on my flesche so dere</L>
<L N="168">&YOGH;it had .I. leuere none wedde to &yogh;ere
<PB REF="00000246.tif" N="218"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="339"></L>
<L>Abide quod sche Mi tale is nou&yogh;t be-gonne</L>
<L>Nay &thorn;ou schalt drinken of a no&thorn;ere tonne</L>
<L>Are &thorn;at .I. go schal sauere wers &thorn;an ale</L>
<L N="172">And whan &thorn;at .I. haue tolde for&thorn;e my tale</L>
<L>Of tribulacione in mariage</L>
<L>Of whiche .I. am experte in myne age</L>
<L>This is to seye Mi-self ha&thorn; be &thorn;e whippe</L>
<L N="176">&thorn;an maist &thorn;ou chese weder &thorn;ou wilt scippe</L>
<L>Thilke tonne &thorn;at .I. schal a-broche<MILESTONE N="89b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Be ware of it er &thorn;ou to nyhe aproche</L>
<L>For [I] schal tell ensamples mo &thorn;an tenne</L>
<L N="180">Wo so &thorn;at wil be war of o&thorn;ere menne</L>
<L>Be him schal o&thorn;er men correct be</L>
<L>&thorn;is same wordes write&thorn;e tholome</L>
<L>Ride in his almagist and take it &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="184">Dame .I. praye &yogh;owe if &yogh;oure wil were</L>
<L>Said &thorn;is pardoner as &yogh;e began</L>
<L>Tel for&thorn; &yogh;owre tale spare for no man</L>
<L>And teche vs &yogh;onge men of &yogh;oure practike</L>
<L N="188">Gladly quod sche if it maie &yogh;owe like</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;at .I. praie to al &thorn;is compaignye</L>
<L>If &thorn;at .I. speke after my fantasie</L>
<L>As take&thorn;e not a greue of &thorn;at .I. saie</L>
<L N="192">For myne entent is nouht bot for to pleie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nowe sires &thorn;an schal .I. tel &yogh;owe my tale</L>
<L>As euere most .I. drink wyne or ale</L>
<L>.I. schal seie so&thorn;e &thorn;e husbondes &thorn;at I. had</L>
<L N="196">As &thorn;re of hem were riht good and tuo were badde</L>
<L>The &thorn;re were godemen and riche and olde</L>
<L>Vnne&thorn; myht &thorn;ei &thorn;e state holde</L>
<L>In whiche &thorn;ei were bounden vnto me</L>
<L N="200">&YOGH;e wote wele what .I. mene of &thorn;is parde</L>
<L>As god me help .I. lauhe whan .I. &thorn;inke</L>
<L>Howe pytously a nyht .I. maade hem swynke</L>
<L>Bot be me feie .I. told of hit no store</L>
<L N="204">&thorn;ei hadde me &yogh;eue hir londe and here tresore
<PB REF="00000247.tif" N="219"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="340"></L>
<L>Me neded nou&yogh;t do longer diligence</L>
<L>To wynne her loue and done hem reuerence</L>
<L>Thei loued me so wele be god aboue</L>
<L N="208">&thorn;at .I. ne tolde no deynte of here loue</L>
<L>A wise womman wil bisie hire euere in one</L>
<L>To gete hire loue &yogh;e &thorn;are as sche ha&thorn;e none</L>
<L>Bot se&thorn;&thorn;e .I. hadde hem holy in myne honde</L>
<L N="212">And si&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;ei hadde &yogh;if me al hir londe</L>
<L>What schold .I. take hem for to plese</L>
<L>Bot if it were my profit and myne ese</L>
<L>Bot .I. set hem so awerke be my faye</L>
<L N="216">&thorn;at mony a nyht &thorn;ei songen walawaye</L>
<L>The bacon was nou&yogh;t fette for hem .I. trowe</L>
<L>That sum men haue in Essexe att Donnemowe</L>
<L>I gouerne hem so wele after my lawe<MILESTONE N="90a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="220">That iche of hem ful blisful was and fawe</L>
<L>To bringe me gay &thorn;inges fro &thorn;e fayre</L>
