<DIV2 TYPE="tale"><PB REF="00000266.tif" N="238"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="359">
<HEAD>Incipit fabula vxoris de Bathonia.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN &thorn;e olde daies of &thorn;e kinge Arthoure</L>
<L>Of whiche &thorn;at bretons speken grete honoure.</L>
<L>All was &thorn;is land fulfilled of faire</L>
<L N="860">The Elphe queene wi&thorn; hir Ioly compaignie</L>
<L>Daunced withe-oute in mony a grene mede</L>
<L>&THORN;is was &thorn;e olde opinion &thorn;at .I. rede</L>
<L>.I. speke of mony a .C. &yogh;ere a-go</L>
<L N="864">Bot now can no man see none elues mo</L>
<L>For &thorn;e grete charite and &thorn;e preiers</L>
<L>Of lymytours and of o&thorn;er pouere frers</L>
<L>&THORN;at serchen euery lande and euery streme</L>
<L N="868">As &thorn;ikke as motes in &thorn;e sonne beme</L>
<L>Blissinge halles chambres bowres</L>
<L>Citees burghes Castels hihe towres</L>
<L>Thorpes bernes schipnes dayeries</L>
<L N="872">&thorn;is make&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;ere be no fairies</L>
<L>For &thorn;ere as was wonte to walke an elfe<MILESTONE N="97b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;er walke&thorn; nowe &thorn;e limitour him selfe</L>
<L>In vndermeles and in morneynges</L>
<L N="876">And sei&thorn;e his Matines and his holy &thorn;inges</L>
<L>As he go&thorn; in his visitacioune</L>
<L>Wemmen maie go nowe sauely vpe and doune</L>
<L>In euery bossche or vnder euere-y tre</L>
<L N="880">There is none o&thorn;er Incubus bot he</L>
<L>And he wil do hem bot disonoure</L>
<L>And so fel it &thorn;at &thorn;is kinge Ar&thorn;oure</L>
<L>Had in his house a lusty bachellier</L>
<L N="884">&THORN;at on a daie cam rideinge fro &thorn;e reuere
<PB REF="00000267.tif" N="239"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="360"></L>
<L>And happed a-lone as sche was borne</L>
<L>He sawhe a maiden walkinge him be-forne</L>
<L>Of whiche maiden maugreue hire hede</L>
<L N="888">be verrei force he raft hir hir maidenhede</L>
<L>For wiche oppression was suche clamoure</L>
<L>And suche pursuyt vnto kinge Arthoure</L>
<L>That dampned was &thorn;is knyht for to be dede</L>
<L N="892">Be cours of lawe and scholde haue lost his hede</L>
<L>Parauenture suche was &thorn;e statute &thorn;o</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;at &thorn;e queene and o&thorn;er ladies mo</L>
<L>So longe preide &thorn;e kinge of grace</L>
<L N="896">Til he his him graunted in &thorn;e place</L>
<L>And &yogh;aue to &thorn;e qwene al att hir will</L>
<L>To chese we&thorn;er sche wolde him saue or spill</L>
<L>The queen &thorn;onked &thorn;e kinge wi&thorn; al here myht</L>
<L N="900">And after &thorn;is &thorn;us spak sche to &thorn;e knyht</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at sche seihe her time vpon a daye</L>
<L>Thou stondest &yogh;it quod sche in suche araye</L>
<L>&thorn;at of &thorn;i lyf &yogh;it hast &thorn;ou no surte</L>
<L N="904">.I. graunte &thorn;e lif; if &thorn;u canst tel me</L>
<L>what &thorn;inge is &thorn;at wemmen moste desiren</L>
<L>Be war and kepe &thorn;i nekke bone from yren</L>
<L>And if &thorn;ou can nou&yogh;t tel it me anone</L>
<L N="908">&YOGH;it wil .I. &yogh;eue &thorn;e leue for to gone</L>
<L>A twelmo&thorn; and a daie to seke and lere</L>
<L>An ansewere sufficiant in &thorn;is matier</L>
<L>And surte wil .I. haue ar &thorn;at &thorn;ou pace</L>
<L N="912">Thi body for to &yogh;elden in &thorn;is place</L>
<L>Woo was &thorn;is knyht and sorwful he sike&thorn;</L>
<L>Bot whate he may nouht do al as him like&thorn;</L>
<L>And att &thorn;e last he chase him for to wende<MILESTONE N="98a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="916">An com a&yogh;eine riht att &thorn;e &yogh;eres ende</L>
<L>With suche answere as god wold him purueye</L>
<L>And take&thorn; his leue and wende&thorn; for&thorn; his weye</L>
<L>He seke&thorn;e euery house and euery place</L>
<L N="920">Where as hope&thorn; for to finde grace
<PB REF="00000268.tif" N="240"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="361"></L>
<L>To leren whatt &thorn;inge wemmen louen most</L>
<L>Bot he nowe cou&thorn;e riden in no cost</L>
<L>Where as he myht finde in &thorn;is matier</L>
<L N="924">Two creatures accordinge in fere</L>
<L>Some seide wemmen louen best riches</L>
<L>Some seide honour some seid Iolynes</L>
<L>Some seide Riche araye and lust abedde</L>
<L N="928">And oft tim to be wedowe and wedde</L>
<L>Some seide &thorn;at we be most esede</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at we bene flaterde and yplesede</L>
<L>He go&thorn; ful nyhe &thorn;e so&thorn;e .I. wil nouht lye</L>
<L N="932">A man schal wynne vs best wi&thorn; flaterye</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; attendance and wi&thorn; besines</L>
<L>Bene we y-lymede bo&thorn; more and les</L>
<L>And som men sein howe &thorn;at we louen best</L>
<L N="936">For to bue fre and do riht as vs lest</L>
<L>And &thorn;at no man repreue vs of oure vice</L>
<L>Bot sei &thorn;at we bue wise and no&thorn;inge nice</L>
<L>For trewly &thorn;are is none of vs al</L>
<L N="940">If any wight wil clowe vs on &thorn;e gal</L>
<L>&THORN;at we nyl loke or he seie &thorn;e so&thorn;e</L>
<L>Assaie and he schal finde it &thorn;at he do&thorn;e</L>
<L>For be we neuere so vicious with-inne</L>
<L N="944">we wil be holden wise and clene of sinne</L>
<L>And summen seine &thorn;at grete delite haue we</L>
<L>For to be holden stable and eke secre</L>
<L>And in o purpos stedfastly to dwell</L>
<L N="948">And nouht be-wrye &thorn;inge &thorn;at men vs tell</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;at tale is nou&yogh;t wor&thorn; a rake stele</L>
<L>Parde we wemmen kan no &thorn;inge hele</L>
<L>Wittenesse of myda wil &yogh;e here &thorn;e tale</L>
<L N="952">Ouide a-monges o&thorn;er &thorn;inges smale</L>
<L>Sei&thorn; Mida ha vndre his longe heres</L>
<L>Growinge vpon his tuo asse eres</L>
<L>The whiche vice he hidde as he best myht</L>
<L N="956">Ful subtily from eueryche mannes siht
<PB REF="00000269.tif" N="241"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="362"></L>
<L>That saue his wif &thorn;er wist &thorn;ere-of no mo<MILESTONE N="98b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>He loued hir most and trist to hir also</L>
<L>He praide hir most &thorn;at vnto no creature</L>
<L N="960">sche schold nou&yogh;t tel of his disfigure</L>
<L>Sche swore him naye for al &thorn;is werld to wynne</L>
<L>Sche nold do; &thorn;at velany or &thorn;at synne</L>
<L>To make hir husbonde haue so foule a name</L>
<L N="964">For reproueinge of him and fowle schame</L>
<L>Bot Na&thorn;eles hir &thorn;ouht &thorn;at sche deide</L>
<L>&thorn;at sche so longe scholde a counsel hide</L>
<L>Hir &thorn;ouht it satt so sore aboute hir hert</L>
<L N="968">&THORN;at nedely sum worde hir mot a-stert</L>
<L>And se&thorn; sche dorste tel it to no man</L>
<L>Doune to a marese fast sche ranne</L>
<L>Til sche came &thorn;er hire hert was a fire</L>
<L N="972">And as betoure beble&thorn; in &thorn;e myre</L>
<L>Sche laide hir mou&thorn;e in-to &thorn;e water downe</L>
<L>Be-wrye me nouht &thorn;ou water wi&thorn; &thorn;i soune</L>
<L>Quod sche . to &thorn;e .I. tel it and no mo</L>
<L N="976">Myne husbonde ha&thorn;e longe asses eres tuo</L>
<L>Nowe is myne hert al hole now it is owte</L>
<L>.I. myht no longer kep it oute of doute</L>
<L>Here mai &yogh;e see &thorn;ouhe we a time abide</L>
<L N="980">&YOGH;it oute it mot we mowe no counsel hide</L>
<L>&THORN;e remenant of &thorn;e tale if &yogh;e wil here</L>
<L>Rede&thorn; ovide and &yogh;e maie it lere</L>
<L>This knyht of wiche mi tale is speciali</L>
<L N="984">Whan &thorn;at he sauh he miht nouht com &thorn;ere bye</L>
<L>This to seie what wemmen louen most</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-inne his hert sorweful was &thorn;e goste</L>
<L>Bot home he go&thorn;e he miht nouht soiorne</L>
<L N="988">The daie was come &thorn;at homward most he torne</L>
<L>And in his wei it happed him to ride</L>
<L>In all his care vnder a forest side</L>
<L>Where he sawhe on o daunce go</L>
<L N="992">Of ladys foure and twenty and &yogh;it moo
<PB REF="00000270.tif" N="242"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="363"></L>
<L>Towarde &thorn;e dawnce he drowhe him &yogh;erne</L>
<L>In hope &thorn;at som wisdome scholde he lerene</L>
<L>Bot certeinly ar he came fully &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="996">Vanyssched was &thorn;e daunce he wist nouht where.</L>
<L>No creature sawe he &thorn;at bare lif</L>
<L>Saue in &thorn;e grene he sawhe sittinge a wif</L>
<L>A fowler wight &thorn;ei may no man devise<MILESTONE N="99a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1000">A-&yogh;ein &thorn;e knyht &thorn;e olde wif gan arise</L>
<L>And seid sir knyht here for&thorn;e li&thorn;e no weye</L>
<L>Tel me what &thorn;at &yogh;e seken be &yogh;oure feye</L>
<L>Parauentur it maie &thorn;e better be<NOTE PLACE="marg">[bue, <I>with</I> u <I>scratcht out</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L N="1004">This olde folke can muche &thorn;inge quod sche</L>
<L>My leue quod &thorn;is knyht serteine</L>
<L>.I. am bot dede bot if &thorn;at .I. can seine</L>
<L>Whatt &thorn;inge it is &thorn;at wemmen most desire</L>
<L N="1008">Cou&thorn;e &yogh;e me wise .I. wold wele white &yogh;owre hire</L>
<L>Plyht me &thorn;i trou&thorn;e here in my honde quod sche</L>
<L>The next &thorn;inge &thorn;at .I. require &thorn;e</L>
<L>Thowe schalt it do if it ly in &thorn;i myht</L>
<L N="1012">And .I. wil tel it &yogh;owe ar it he nyht</L>
<L>Haue here my trou&thorn;e quod knyht .I. graunt</L>
<L>&THORN;at quod sche .I. maye me wele auant</L>
<L>Thi lif is saue for .I. wil stonde &thorn;er bye</L>
<L N="1016">Vpon my lif &thorn;e qweene wil saie as .I.</L>
<L>Latt see whiche is &thorn;e proddest of hem al</L>
<L>That were&thorn; on a kercheue or a cal</L>
<L>&thorn;at dar sey nay of &thorn;at .I. schal &yogh;ow teche</L>
<L N="1020">Lat vs go for&thorn;e wi&thorn;-oute longer speche</L>
<L>Tho rouned sche a pistel in his ere</L>
<L>And bad him to be gladde and haue no fere</L>
<L>Whann &thorn;ei be commen to &thorn;e courte &thorn;is knyht</L>
<L N="1024">Seid he had holde his daie as he had hiht</L>
<L>And redy was his ansewere as he seide</L>
<L>Foll<NOTE PLACE="marg">[? MS Fo <I>or</I> Fv]</NOTE> mony a noble wif and mony a maide</L>
<L>And mony a wedew for &thorn;at &thorn;ei bu wise</L>
<L N="1028">The queene hire seluen sitt Iuge as Iustise
<PB REF="00000271.tif" N="243"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="364"></L>
<L>Assemblede ben his answere for to here</L>
<L>And afterwarde &thorn;is knyht was bode a-piere</L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;e knyht schold tel in audience</L>
<L N="1032">To euery. wight commanded was silence</L>
<L>What &thorn;inge &thorn;at werldly wemmen louen mest</L>
<L>&thorn;is knyht ne stode nou&yogh;t stil as do&thorn;e a beste</L>
<L>Bo to &thorn;is questione a-none he ansewerde</L>
<L N="1036">Wi&thorn; manly voyce &thorn;at al &thorn;e court it herde</L>
<L>My liege lady lady general quod he.</L>
<L>Womman desiret to haue souereynte</L>
<L>As wele ouer hir husbonde as hir loue</L>
<L N="1040">And for to be in maistre him a-boue</L>
<L>This &yogh;owre most desire &thorn;ouhe &yogh;e me kill<MILESTONE N="99b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Do&thorn;e as &yogh;owe list .I. am here att &yogh;oure will</L>
<L>In al &thorn;e courte ne was &thorn;er wif ne maide</L>
<L N="1044">Ne wedowe &thorn;at contraried &thorn;at he seide</L>
<L>Bot seyden he was wor&thorn;i to haue his lyf</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde vpstert &thorn;is olde wif</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at &thorn;e knyht sawe sittinge on &thorn;e grene</L>
<L N="1048">Mercie quod sche Mi souereine ladi qweene</L>
<L>Ar &thorn;at &yogh;oure Court depart do me riht</L>
<L>.I. tauht &thorn;is ansewer vn-to &thorn;is knyht</L>
<L>For whiche he pliht me his trou&thorn;e &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="1052">The first &thorn;inge .I. wolde of him require</L>
<L>He wolde it do if it lei in his myhte</L>
<L>Be-for &thorn;e Court &thorn;an praie .I. &thorn;e sir knyht</L>
<L>Quod sche &thorn;at &thorn;u me tak vnto &thorn;i wif</L>
<L N="1056">For wele &thorn;u woste &thorn;at .I. haue kepped &thorn;i lif</L>
<L>If .I. saye fals seye so&thorn;e vpon &thorn;i fey</L>
<L>This knyht ansewerd alas and walawaie</L>
<L>.I. wote riht wele &thorn;at suche was my beheste</L>
<L N="1060">For goddes loue chese a newe requeste</L>
<L>Tak al my goode and lat my body go</L>
<L>Nay &thorn;an quod sche .I. schrewe vs bo&thorn;e tuo</L>
<L>For &thorn;at .I. be foule olde and pouer</L>
<L N="1064">.I. nolde for al &thorn;e metal ne for Oer
<PB REF="00000272.tif" N="244"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="365"></L>
<L>&thorn;at vnder er&thorn;e is graue or li&thorn;e aboue</L>
<L>Bot if &thorn;at .I. &thorn;i wif were and &thorn;i loue</L>
<L>Mi loue quod he nay my . dampnacione</L>
<L N="1068">Alas &thorn;at any of my nacione</L>
<L>Schold euere so foule disparaged bue</L>
<L>Bot al for nouht &thorn;e ende is &thorn;is &thorn;at he</L>
<L>Constreigned was he nedes most he hir wedde</L>
<L N="1072">And take&thorn; &thorn;is olde wif and go&thorn; to bedde</L>
<L>Now wold sum men seine parauenture</L>
<L>&THORN;at for my necligence .I. do no cure</L>
<L>To tel &yogh;owe &thorn;e Ioye and &thorn;e arraye</L>
<L N="1076">&THORN;at att &thorn;e feste was &thorn;ilke daye</L>
<L>To whiche &thorn;inge schortely ansewere .I. schal.</L>
<L>.I. seie &thorn;er was no ioye ne fest att al</L>
<L>&THORN;er nas bot heuynes and muche sorwe</L>
<L N="1080">For priuely he wede hire on morwe</L>
<L>And al daie after hidde him as an owle</L>
<L>So woo was him his wif loked so foule.</L>
<L>Grete was &thorn;e sorwe &thorn;e knyht had in his &thorn;ouht<MILESTONE N="100a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1084">Whan he was wi&thorn; his wyf ybedde brouht</L>
<L>He walowe&thorn; and torne&thorn; to and fro</L>
<L>His olde [wyf] laye smyleinge euermo</L>
<L>And seide Dere husbonde o benedicite</L>
<L N="1088">Fare&thorn; euery knyht &thorn;us wi&thorn; his wif as &yogh;e</L>
<L>Is &thorn;is &thorn;e lawe of kinge Ar&thorn;ors house</L>
<L>Is euery knyht of his &thorn;us daungerous</L>
<L>.I. am &yogh;oure loue and eke &yogh;oure wif</L>
<L N="1092">.I. am sche whiche saued ha&thorn; &yogh;oure lif</L>
<L>And sertes &yogh;it dide .I. &yogh;owe neuer vnriht</L>
<L>Whi fare &yogh;e &thorn;us wi&thorn; me &thorn;e first niht</L>
<L>&YOGH;e faren like a man &thorn;at had lost his witte</L>
<L N="1096">Fy what is my gilte for goddes loue tell itte</L>
<L>And it schal bue amended if .I. maie</L>
<L>Amend quod &thorn;is knyht nay naye</L>
<L>That wil nouht bue amendede neuere mo</L>
<L N="1100">&THORN;ou ert so lo&thorn;ely and so olde also
<PB REF="00000273.tif" N="245"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="366"></L>
<L>And &thorn;er-to comen of so lowe a kinde</L>
<L>&thorn;at litel wonder is &thorn;ouhe .I. walow and winde</L>
<L>So wolde god myne herte wolde to-breste</L>
<L N="1104">Is &thorn;is quod sche &thorn;e cause of &yogh;oure vnreste</L>
<L>&YOGH;e certeinly quod he no wonder is</L>
<L>Nowe sir quod sche .I. cou&thorn;e amende al &thorn;is</L>
<L>If &thorn;at me list ar it were daies &thorn;re</L>
<L N="1108">So well &yogh;e myhtte bere &yogh;owe vn-to me</L>
<L>Bot for &yogh;e speken of suche gentillese</L>
<L>As is descended oute of al richesse</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ere-for scholden &yogh;e be gentil men</L>
<L N="1112">Suche errogance is nouht wor&thorn;e an hen</L>
<L>Lo who &thorn;at most is vertuous alweie</L>
<L>Preue and a-pert and most ende&thorn; aie</L>
<L>To do gentil dedes &thorn;at he can</L>
<L N="1116">And take him for &thorn;e grettest gentil man</L>
<L>Crist will we cleime of him oure gentilnes</L>
<L>Not of oure eldres for here olde reches</L>
<L>For &thorn;ouhe &thorn;ei &yogh;eue vs al her Heritage</L>
<L N="1120">For whiche we cleime to be of hihe parage</L>
<L>&YOGH;it may &thorn;ei nouht be-que&thorn;e for no &thorn;inge</L>
<L>To none of vs her vertuous leueinge</L>
<L>That maad hem gentil men y-called be</L>
<L N="1124">And bad vs folowen hem in suche degre.</L>
<L>Wele can &thorn;e wise Poet of fflorens<MILESTONE N="100b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;at hiht Dante speke&thorn; in &thorn;is sentens</L>
<L>Lo in Suche maner rim is dantes tale</L>
<L N="1128">Ful selde vp rise&thorn; be his braunches smale</L>
<L>Prowes of man for god of his prouesse</L>
<L>Wil &thorn;at we of cleime oure gentillesse</L>
<L>For of oure helders maie we no &thorn;inge cleime</L>
<L N="1132">Bot temperal &thorn;inge &thorn;at man maie hirte and maheime</L>
<L>Eke euery white wote &thorn;is as wele as .I.</L>
<L>If gentillesse were planted naturalye</L>
<L>Into a certeine lignage doune &thorn;e line</L>
<L N="1136">Preue and aperte &thorn;an wold hey neuer fyne
<PB REF="00000274.tif" N="246"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="367"></L>
<L>To done of gentillesse &thorn;e faire ofice</L>
<L>Thei myhten do no velany nor vice</L>
<L>Tak fire and bere it in &thorn;e derkest house</L>
<L N="1140">Be-twex &thorn;is and &thorn;e mount of Caucasouse</L>
<L>And let men schette &thorn;e dore and go &thorn;en&dotb;ne</L>
<L>&YOGH;it wil &thorn;e fire ly as fair and brenne</L>
<L>As &thorn;ouh a .M. men myht it be-holde</L>
<L N="1144">His office naturele ay wil it holde</L>
<L>Vp peril of lif til &thorn;at it deie</L>
<L>Here maie &yogh;e se wele howe &thorn;at genterye</L>
<L>Is nouht anexed to possession</L>
<L N="1148">Se&thorn; folke do&thorn; nouht her operacion</L>
<L>Alweie as do&thorn;e &thorn;e fire lo in his kinde</L>
<L>For god it wote men maie ful often finde</L>
<L>A lorde sone do schame and velanye</L>
<L N="1152">And he &thorn;at wil haue prise of his gentirye</L>
<L>For he was borne of a gentil hous</L>
<L>And hadde his heldres noble and vertuous</L>
<L>And nyl him-seluen do no gentil dedes</L>
<L N="1156">Ne folowe his gentill ancestre &thorn;at dedes</L>
<L>He is nouht gentil be he duc or Erle</L>
<L>For veleyns sinful dede mak a cherle</L>
<L>For gentillesse ne is bot reuente</L>
<L N="1160">Of &thorn;ine Auncestres for hire bente</L>
<L>Whiche is a stronge &thorn;inge for &thorn;i persone</L>
<L>The gentilles come&thorn; fro god alone</L>
<L>Than come&thorn; oure verraie gentilles of grace</L>
<L N="1164">He was no&thorn;inge be-que&thorn;e vs wi&thorn; oure place</L>
<L>Thinke&thorn; howe noble as sei&thorn; valerius</L>
<L>Was &thorn;ilke tullius hostilius.</L>
<L>That oute of pouert ros to hihe noblesse<MILESTONE N="101a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1168">Rede&thorn; Senec and rede eke Boesse</L>
<L>There schold &yogh;e seen expresse &thorn;at it no drede is</L>
<L>That is gentil &thorn;at do&thorn;e gentil dedes</L>
<L>And &thorn;er-fore dere husbonde .I. &thorn;us conclude</L>
<L N="1172">Al were &thorn;at myne Ancestres were so rude
<PB REF="00000275.tif" N="247"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="368"></L>
<L>&YOGH;it maie &thorn;at hihe god and so hope .I.</L>
<L>Graunt me grace to leue vertuously</L>
<L>Than am .I. gentil whan &thorn;at .I. be-ginne</L>
<L N="1176">To leuen vertuously and weuen sinne</L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;are as &yogh;e of pouert me repreue</L>
<L>The hihe god on whom &thorn;at we beleue</L>
<L>In wilful pouert ches to leue his lif</L>
<L N="1180">And certes euery man and maide and wif</L>
<L>Maie vnder-stonde ihesu heuen kinge</L>
<L>Ne wold nou&yogh;t chese a vicious leueinge</L>
<L>Glad pouert is an honest &thorn;inge certeigne</L>
<L N="1184">This wil senec an[d] o&thorn;ere clerkes seine</L>
<L>Who so &thorn;at holde him paide of his pouert</L>
<L>.I. holde him riche al had he nouht sert</L>
<L>He &thorn;at couete&thorn; is a pouer wight</L>
<L N="1188">For he wold haue &thorn;at is nouht in his myht</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;at nouht ha&thorn;e ne couete&thorn; to haue</L>
<L>Is riche al-&thorn;ouhe men holde him bot a knaue</L>
<L>Verray pouert is sinne propurly</L>
<L N="1192">Iuuenal sei&thorn;e of pouert merely</L>
<L>The pore man whan he go&thorn; be &thorn;e waye</L>
<L>Be-for &thorn;e &thorn;eues he maie singe and pleye</L>
<L>Pouert is hatel good and as .I. gesse</L>
<L N="1196">A ful grete bringer oute of besinesse</L>
<L>A gre amender eke of Sapience</L>
<L>To him &thorn;at lakke&thorn; it in pacience</L>
<L>Pouer is &thorn;is al &thorn;ouhe it seme Alinge</L>
<L N="1200">Possessione &thorn;at no wyht wil chalinge.</L>
<L>Pouert ful oft whan a ma[n] is lowe</L>
<L>Make&thorn; his and eke him self to knowe</L>
<L>Pouert in spektacle is as &thorn;enke&thorn; me</L>
<L N="1204">&THORN;ourhe whiche he maie his verray frende se</L>
<L>And &thorn;ere sen &thorn;at .I. &yogh;owe nou&yogh;t greue</L>
<L>Of my pouert no more me repreue<NOTE PLACE="marg">&para; Nota de Senectute</NOTE></L>
<L>Nowe sire of elde &yogh;e preue me</L>
<L N="1208">And certes sir &thorn;oruhe none auctorite
<PB REF="00000276.tif" N="248"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="369"></L>
<L>Wher in no boke &yogh;e gentil of honoure<MILESTONE N="101b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Seine &thorn;at men scholde an olde wife do fauoure</L>
<L>And clepe her moder for her gentillesse</L>
<L N="1212">An Auctours schal .I. finde as .I. gesse</L>
<L>Nowe &thorn;ere &yogh;e seine &thorn;at .I. am foule and olde</L>
<L>&THORN;an drede &yogh;owe nouht to be no cokewolde</L>
<L>For fil&thorn;e and hel&thorn;e as mot .I. &thorn;e</L>
<L N="1216">Bene grete werdeins vpon chastite</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles sen .I. knowe &yogh;oure delite</L>
<L>.I. scha[l] ful-fill &yogh;oure werly appetite</L>
<L>Chese nowe quod sche one of &thorn;is &thorn;inges tweye</L>
<L N="1220">To haue me foule and olde til &thorn;at .I. deie</L>
<L>And be to &yogh;owe a trewe humble wif</L>
<L>And neuer &yogh;oue displese in al my lif</L>
<L>Or elles &yogh;e wil haue me &yogh;onge and faire</L>
<L N="1224">And take &yogh;oure auenture of &thorn;e repaire</L>
<L>That schal com to &yogh;oure house be cause of me</L>
<L>Or in sume o&thorn;ere place wel maie be</L>
<L>Nowe chese &yogh;oure seluen whe&thorn;er &thorn;at &yogh;ou like&thorn;</L>
<L N="1228">This knyht a-vised him and sore he sike&thorn;</L>
<L>Bot att &thorn;e last he seide in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>My lady and my loue and wife so dere</L>
<L>.I. putte me in &yogh;oure wise gouernaunce</L>
<L N="1232">Gesse&thorn; &yogh;oure self whiche maie be most plesaunce</L>
<L>And most honour to &yogh;owe and me also</L>
<L>.I. do no force whe&thorn;er of &thorn;e tue</L>
<L>For as &yogh;owe like&thorn; it sufficet me</L>
<L N="1236">Than haue .I. gete of &yogh;owe &thorn;e maistre quod sche</L>
<L>Sen .I. may chese and gouerne as me lest</L>
<L>&YOGH;e sertes wif quod he .I. holde it for &thorn;e best</L>
<L>Kisse me quod sche we be no longer wro&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1240">For be my trow&thorn;e .I. will be to &yogh;owe bo&thorn;e</L>
<L>&THORN;is is seine to be to &yogh;owe bo&thorn;e feire and goode</L>
<L>.I. praie to god &thorn;at .I. mot steruen woode</L>
<L>Bot .I. to &yogh;owe be also sadde and trewe</L>
<L N="1244">As euer was wif sen &thorn;at &thorn;e werlde was newe
<PB REF="00000277.tif" N="249"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="370"></L>
<L>And bot .I. be to morwe also faire to seen</L>
<L>As any lady Emperes or qween</L>
<L>&THORN;at is be-twene &thorn;e est and eke &thorn;e west</L>
<L N="1248">Do wi&thorn; my lif and de&thorn;e riht as &yogh;ow lest</L>
<L>Kast vp &thorn;e kurteyne and loke how it is</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;e knyht sauhe al &thorn;is</L>
<L>&THORN;at sche so faire was and so &yogh;onge &thorn;er-to<MILESTONE N="102a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1252">For ioy he hent hir in his armes tuo</L>
<L>His hert ba&thorn;ed in a ba&thorn;&thorn;e of blisse</L>
<L>A. M. time a rewe he gan hir kisse</L>
<L>And sche obeide him in euery &thorn;inge</L>
<L N="1256">&THORN;at myht done him plesans or likeinge</L>
<L>And &thorn;us &thorn;ei leued vnto her lyues hende</L>
<L>In parfite Ioye and ihesu criste vs sende</L>
<L>Hosbonde meke &yogh;onge and fresshe y bedde</L>
<L N="1260">And grace to ouer-lede hame &thorn;at we wedde</L>
<L>And eke .I. praie to ihesu schort her lyues</L>
<L>&THORN;at wil nouht be gouernd be hir wyues</L>
<L>And olde and Angrye Nigard in dispence</L>
<L N="1264">God send hem sone a verrei Pestelence</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit</B> fabula <B>Matrone</B> vxoris <B>de</B> Bathonia.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000278.tif" N="250">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="371">
<HEAD>Incipit prologus fratris<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 102</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>This wor&thorn;i lymitour &thorn;is noble frere</L>
<L>He maad alweie lowreynge chere</L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;e Sompnour bot for honeste</L>
<L N="1268">No veleyns worde as &yogh;ite spake he</L>
<L>Bot att &thorn;e last he saide vnto &thorn;e wife</L>
<L>Dame good god &yogh;yue &yogh;owe riht good life</L>
<L>&YOGH;e haue touchede here as mot .I. &thorn;e</L>
<L N="1272">In scole Matier gret difficulte</L>
<L>&YOGH;e haue seide muchel &thorn;inge riht wele .I. seie</L>
<L>Bot dame here as we riden be &thorn;e weie</L>
<L>Vs nede&thorn; nouht to speken bot of game</L>
<L N="1276">And lete Auctorites in goddes name</L>
<L>To precheinge and to schole eke of clergie</L>
<L>Bot if it like vnto &thorn;is compaignie</L>
<L>.I. wil &yogh;owe of a Somnour tel a game</L>
<L N="1280">Parde .I. maie wele knowe be &thorn;i name</L>
<L>&thorn;at of no somnour mai no good be seide</L>
<L>.I. praie &thorn;at none of &yogh;owe be yuel apaide</L>
<L>A Somnour is a romer vp and doune</L>
<L N="1284">Wi&thorn; a mendement of fornicacioune</L>
<L>And is .I.-bette att euery tounes ende</L>
<L>Owre &thorn;an spake a sir &yogh;e scholde be hende</L>
<L>And curteis as man of &yogh;oure astate</L>
<L N="1288">In compaignie we wil no debate</L>
<L>Telle&thorn; &yogh;oure tale and late&thorn; &thorn;e somenour be</L>
<L>Naie quod Somnour late him sei to me</L>
<L>What so him liste whan it come&thorn; to my lote</L>
<L N="1292">Be god .I. schal him qwite euery grote.</L>
<L>I schall him tell whiche a grete honour<MILESTONE N="102b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>It is to be [a] flateringe limitour</L>
<L>And of ful mony ano&thorn;er crime</L>
<L N="1296">Whiche nede&thorn;e nouht rehersen att &thorn;is time</L>
<L>And his office .I. schal him tell .I.-wis</L>
<L>Owre oste answard pees no more of &thorn;is</L>
<L>And afterwarde he seide vn-to &thorn;e frere</L>
<L N="1300">Tel for&thorn;e &yogh;owre tale my leue mayster dere.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit prologus.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000279.tif" N="251">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="372">
<HEAD>Incipit fabula.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 102, <I>back</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Whilom &thorn;ere was dwelinge in myne contre</L>
<L>An Arche-deken a man of hihe degre</L>
<L>That boldely dide execucion</L>
<L N="1304">In poneschinge of fornicacione</L>
<L>Of whiche craft and eke of baudrye</L>
<L>Of diffamacion and avowtrie</L>
<L>Of cherche reues and of testamentes</L>
<L N="1308">Of contractes and of lac of sacramentes</L>
<L>Of vsury and of Simony also</L>
<L>Bot certes Lychoures dede he grettest woo</L>
<L>Thei scholden singe if &thorn;ei wer hente</L>
<L N="1312">And smale ti&thorn;ers weren fowle schente</L>
<L>If any person wolde vpon hem pleine</L>
<L>There myht a-stert him no pecuniale peyne</L>
<L>For smale ti&thorn;es and eke smale offringe</L>
<L N="1316">He maade &thorn;e peple spitusly to singe</L>
<L>For or &thorn;e bischop cauht hem wi&thorn; his hoke</L>
<L>Thei were in &thorn;e Arche-decanes boke</L>
<L>And &thorn;an hadde he &thorn;oruhe his Iurdictione</L>
<L N="1320">Power to done on hem Correctione</L>
<L>He had a somnoure redy to his hand</L>
<L>A slyhere boye was none in yngelande</L>
<L>For Sotely he had his especiaile</L>
<L N="1324">That tauht him where he myht availe</L>
<L>He cou&thorn;e spare of lychours one or tuo</L>
<L>To techen him to foure &middot; and twenty mo</L>
<L>ffor &thorn;ouhe &thorn;is somnour woode were as an hare</L>
<L N="1328">To tel his harlotry .I. wil nou&yogh;t spare
<PB REF="00000280.tif" N="252"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="373"></L>
<L>For we bue oute of her correctione</L>
<L>Thei haue of vs no Iurdictione</L>
<L>Ne neuer scholle terme of al her lyues</L>
<L N="1332">Peter so bue &thorn;e wymmen of &thorn;e styues</L>
<L>Quod &thorn;is Somnour yput houte of al oure cure</L>
<L>Pes wi&thorn; meschaunce and wi&thorn; misauenture<MILESTONE N="103a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Thus seid owre oste and late him tel his tale</L>
<L N="1336">Now telle&thorn; for&thorn;e and lete &thorn;e Somnour gale</L>
<L>Ne spare&thorn; nouht myne owen meister dere</L>
<L>This false &thorn;ef &thorn;is somenour quod &thorn;e frere</L>
<L>Hadde alweie baudes redye to his honde</L>
<L N="1340">As any hauke to lure in Ingelonde</L>
<L>&thorn;at tellen him al &thorn;e secree &thorn;at &thorn;ei knewe</L>
<L>Of hire acqueyntance was nat come of newe</L>
<L>&thorn;ei weren his approwers priuely</L>
<L N="1344">He toke him self a grete profit &thorn;er by</L>
<L>His maister knewe nat alweie what he wan</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-outen maundement of a lewed man</L>
<L>He cou&thorn;e Somne of pein cristes curs</L>
<L N="1348">And &thorn;ei weere glad to fill his purs</L>
<L>And maade him grete festis att nale</L>
<L>Riht as Iudas had purse smale</L>
<L>And was a &thorn;eef riht suche a &thorn;eef was he</L>
<L N="1352">His maister had bot half his Dewte</L>
<L>He was. if .I. schal &yogh;euen him his laude</L>
<L>An &thorn;eef and eke a somnour and a baude</L>
<L>He had eke wenches of his retenue</L>
<L N="1356">That whe&thorn;er sir Robert or sir hewe</L>
<L>Or Iohn or Raufe or who &thorn;at it wer</L>
<L>&thorn;at lei by hem &thorn;ei tolde it in his ere</L>
<L>&THORN;us was &thorn;e wenche and he of on assent</L>
<L N="1360">Ande he wolde feche a feyned maundement</L>
<L>And somone hem to chapeter bo&thorn; tuo</L>
<L>And pil &thorn;e man and latt &thorn;e wenche go</L>
<L>Than wolde he seie frend .I. sal for &thorn;i sake</L>
<L N="1364">Do strike &thorn;e oute of owre letter blake
<PB REF="00000281.tif" N="253"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="374"></L>
<L>&thorn;e &thorn;ar no more as in &thorn;is caas trauaile</L>
<L>.I. am &thorn;i frende &thorn;ere .I. &thorn;e maie availe</L>
<L>Sertein he knewe of briburs mo</L>
<L N="1368">&thorn;an possible is to tell &yogh;ou to</L>
<L>For in &thorn;is werlde is no doge for &thorn;e bowe</L>
<L>&thorn;at knowe an hurt dere fro an holde bet cowe</L>
<L>&thorn;an &thorn;is Somenour knewe a licour</L>
<L N="1372">Or a vouter or elles a paramour</L>
<L>And for &thorn;at was &thorn;e fruyte of al &thorn;e rente</L>
<L>Ther-for on it he set al his entente</L>
<L>And so be-fel &thorn;at ones on a daie</L>
<L N="1376">&thorn;is Somnour euere wayteinge one his preye</L>
<L>Rode for to somne a holde wif a ribibe<MILESTONE N="103b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Feynein a cause for he wald bribe</L>
<L>And happed &thorn;at he sauhe to-for him ride</L>
<L N="1380">A gaie &yogh;oman vnder a forest side</L>
<L>A bowe he bare and arwes briht and kene</L>
<L>He had vpon a courteby of grene</L>
<L>An hatte vpon his hede wi&thorn; fenges blake</L>
<L N="1384">Sir quod &thorn;is Somnour heile and wele a take</L>
<L>Welkom quod he and euery good felawe</L>
<L>Weder rides &thorn;ou vnder &thorn;is grene wod schawe</L>
<L>Saide &thorn;is &yogh;oman wilt &thorn;ou fer to daie</L>
<L N="1388">&thorn;e Somnour him ansewerd and seide naye</L>
<L>Here fast by quod he is myn entent</L>
<L>To riden for to reisene vp a rent</L>
<L>It longe&thorn; to my lordes dewte</L>
<L N="1392">Ert &thorn;ou &thorn;an a baillif &yogh;e quod he</L>
<L>He dorst nou&yogh;t fo verre fel&thorn;e and schame</L>
<L>Sei &thorn;at he was somnour for &thorn;e name</L>
<L>De par dieux quod &thorn;is &yogh;oman dere bro&thorn;er</L>
<L N="1396">&thorn;ou ert a bailif. and .I. am ano&thorn;er</L>
<L>.I. vnknowen as in &thorn;is contre</L>
<L>Of &thorn;in acqueyntance .I. wil praie &thorn;e</L>
<L>And eke of bre&thorn;erhede if &thorn;at &thorn;ou liste</L>
<L N="1400">.I. haue golde and siluer in my chiste
<PB REF="00000282.tif" N="254"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="375"></L>
<L>If &thorn;at &yogh;e happed to com in to owre schire</L>
<L>It schal be &thorn;ine riht as &thorn;ou wilt desire</L>
<L>Gremercie quod &thorn;is Somnour be my fei&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1404">Euer-iche in o&thorn;ers honde her trou&thorn; ley&thorn;e</L>
<L>For to be swore bre&thorn;er to &thorn;ei deye</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde &thorn;ei ride for&thorn;e &thorn;er weie</L>
<L>&thorn;is somnour wi&thorn; &thorn;at was as ful of Iangles</L>
<L N="1408">As foll of venym be &thorn;is wereangles</L>
<L>And euere enquireinge vpon euery &thorn;inge</L>
<L>Bro&thorn;er quod he where is &yogh;oure dwelynge</L>
<L>Ano&thorn;er daie if .I. schal &yogh;ou seche</L>
<L N="1412">&thorn;is &yogh;oman him ansewarde in soft speche</L>
<L>Bro&thorn;e[r] quod he fer in &thorn;e nor&thorn;e cuntre</L>
<L>Where as .I. hope some time .I. schal &thorn;e se</L>
<L>Ar we departe .I. schal &thorn;e so wel wisse</L>
<L N="1416">&thorn;at of myne hous schalt &thorn;ou neuer mysse</L>
<L>Now bro&thorn;er quod &thorn;is Somenour .I. &yogh;ow preie</L>
<L>Teche me while we riden be &thorn;e weie.</L>
<L>Sen &thorn;at &yogh;e be a baillif as am .I.<MILESTONE N="104a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1420">Som subtilite tel me fei&thorn;fully</L>
<L>In myne office how &thorn;at .I. maie most winne</L>
<L>And spare nouht for conscience ne sinne</L>
<L>Bot as my bro&thorn;er tel me howe do &yogh;e</L>
<L N="1424">Nowe be my trew&thorn;e bro&thorn;er dere seide he</L>
<L>As .I. schal tellen &thorn;e a fai&thorn;ful tale</L>
<L>My wage buen ful streite and smale</L>
<L>My lorde is harde to me and dangerous</L>
<L N="1428">And myne Office ful laborous</L>
<L>And &thorn;ere-fore be extorcions .I. leue</L>
<L>For so&thorn;e .I. al &thorn;at men wil me &yogh;eue</L>
<L>Allgate be sleiht or violence</L>
<L N="1432">Frome &yogh;ere to &yogh;ere .I. winne al my dispence</L>
<L>.I. kan no better tellen fai&thorn;fully</L>
<L>Now sertes quod Somnour so fare .I.</L>
<L>.I. spare nouht to taken god it wote</L>
<L N="1436">Bot if it be to heuy or to hote
<PB REF="00000283.tif" N="255"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="376"></L>
<L>What .I. maye gette in Counseill priuely</L>
<L>No manere consciens of &thorn;at haue .I.</L>
<L>Ner mye extorcion .I. myht not leuen</L>
<L N="1440">Of suche Iapes wil .I. nouht bu schreuen</L>
<L>For stomak ne for conscience knowe .I. none</L>
<L>.I. schrewe &thorn;is schrift faders euerychone</L>
<L>Wele be we mette be god and be seint Iame</L>
<L N="1444">Bot leue bro&thorn;er tel me &thorn;an &thorn;i name</L>
<L>Quod &thorn;is Somnour in &thorn;is mene while</L>
<L>This &yogh;oman gan a litel for to smyle</L>
<L>Bro&thorn;er quod he wil towe &thorn;at .I. &thorn;e tell</L>
<L N="1448">.I. am a steue my dwellinge is in hell</L>
<L>And here .I. ride aboute my purchasinge</L>
<L>To witte if men wil &yogh;eue me any &thorn;inge</L>
<L>Mi purchache is to fett al my rent</L>
<L N="1452">Looke howe &thorn;ou ridest for &thorn;e same entent</L>
<L>To winne good &thorn;ou rekkest neuer howe</L>
<L>Riht so fare .I. for ride wolde .I. nowe</L>
<L>In to &thorn;e werldes ende for a preie</L>
<L N="1456">A quod &thorn;is somnour Benedicite what &yogh;e seie</L>
<L>.I. wende &yogh;e were a &yogh;oman trewly</L>
<L>&YOGH;e haue a mannes schappe as wel as .I.</L>
<L>Haue &yogh;e &thorn;an a figure determinate</L>
<L N="1460">In hel &thorn;er &yogh;e bene in &yogh;oure astate.</L>
<L>Nai certainly quod he &thorn;are haue we none<MILESTONE N="104b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Bot whan vs like&thorn;e we can tak vs one</L>
<L>Or elles make &yogh;ou seme we bene schape</L>
<L N="1464">Som tim a man or lyke an hape</L>
<L>Or lyke an angel can .I. ride or goo</L>
<L>It is no wonder &thorn;inge &thorn;ouhe it be soo</L>
<L>A lousy Iogelour can disceyue &thorn;e</L>
<L N="1468">And perde &yogh;it can .I. mor craft &thorn;an he</L>
<L>Whi quod &thorn;is Somnour Ride &yogh;e &thorn;an or gone</L>
<L>In Sondre schappe and nouht alweie one</L>
<L>For we quod he wil vs suche forme make</L>
<L N="1472">As most able is oure preis to take
<PB REF="00000284.tif" N="256"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="377"></L>
<L>What make&thorn; &yogh;owe to haue al &thorn;is laboure</L>
<L>Ful mony a cause leue sir Somnour</L>
<L>Seid &thorn;is fende bot al &thorn;inge ha&thorn;e time</L>
<L N="1476">&thorn;e daie is schort and it is passed prime</L>
<L>And &yogh;it ne wann .I. no &thorn;inge in &thorn;is daie</L>
<L>.I. wil entend to wynynge if .I. maie</L>
<L>And nouht entende oure wittes to declare</L>
<L N="1480">For bro&thorn;er myne &thorn;i witte is al to bare</L>
<L>To vnderstonde &thorn;ouhe .I. tolde hem &thorn;e</L>
<L>Bot for &thorn;ou axest whi labour we</L>
<L>For sum time we bue goddes instrumentz</L>
<L N="1484">And mennes to done his commandementz</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at him vpon his creatures</L>
<L>In diuerse attes and in diuers figures</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-outen him we haue no myht certaine</L>
<L N="1488">If &thorn;at him lust stande &thorn;er a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>And sum tym att oure preie haue we leue</L>
<L>Onely &thorn;e body and nouht &thorn;e soule greue</L>
<L>Wittenes on Iob whom &thorn;at we deden woo</L>
<L N="1492">And sumtyme haue we myht of bo&thorn;e tuo</L>
<L>This to seine of soule and body eke</L>
<L>And som time we buen suffered for to done seke</L>
<L>Vpon a man and do his soule vnrest</L>
<L N="1496">Nouht his body and al is for &thorn;e best</L>
<L>Whan he wi&thorn;-stonde&thorn; oure temptacione</L>
<L>It is a cause of saluacione</L>
<L>Al be it &thorn;at it was nou&yogh;t owre entent</L>
<L N="1500">He scholde be saue bot &thorn;at we wold him hent</L>
<L>And some tim be we seruant vn-to a man</L>
<L>As &thorn;e Erchebysschope sei&thorn;e Dunstan</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e Aposteles seruant was .I.<MILESTONE N="105a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1504">&yogh;it tell me quod Somnour fei&thorn;fully</L>
<L>Maake &yogh;e &yogh;owe bodys &thorn;us al wey</L>
<L>Of Elementes &thorn;e fende seid naye</L>
<L>Som time we feine and sum time we rise</L>
<L N="1508">Wi&thorn; dede bodies in ful sundre wyse
<PB REF="00000285.tif" N="257"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="378"></L>
<L>And speke as renably faire and wele</L>
<L>As to &thorn;e phitonessa did Samuele</L>
<L>And &yogh;it wil sum men saie it was nouht he</L>
<L N="1512">.I. do no fors of &yogh;oure diuinite</L>
<L>Bot o &thorn;inge warne .I. &thorn;e .I. wil nouht Iape</L>
<L>Thou wilt algates wite howe we be schape</L>
<L>Thou schalt her-after-ward my bro&thorn;er dere</L>
<L N="1516">Come where &thorn;e nede&thorn; not of me to lore</L>
<L>For &thorn;ou schalt be &thorn;in owen experience</L>
<L>Com in to &thorn;e chaier to rede &thorn;is sentence</L>
<L>Better &thorn;an virgile while he was on lyue</L>
<L N="1520">Or dante also nowe lat vs ride belyue</L>
<L>For .I. wil holde company wi&thorn; &thorn;e</L>
<L>Til it be so &thorn;at &thorn;ou for-sake me</L>
<L>Naie quod Somnour &thorn;at schal not be-tide</L>
<L N="1524">.I. am a &yogh;oman knowe is ful wide</L>
<L>Mi trou&thorn;e wil .I. holde to &thorn;e as in &thorn;is caas</L>
<L>For &thorn;eih &thorn;ou were &thorn;e deuel Sathanas</L>
<L>My trou&thorn;e will .I. holde to my bro&thorn;er</L>
<L N="1528">As .I. am sworne and iche of vs to o&thorn;ere</L>
<L>For to be trewe bro&thorn;er in &thorn;is caas</L>
<L>And bro&thorn;er wee goon to owre purchas</L>
<L>Take &thorn;u &thorn;i part what men wil &thorn;e &yogh;eue</L>
<L N="1532">And .I. schal myne &thorn;us maye we bo&thorn;e leuen</L>
<L>And if &thorn;at any of vs haue more &thorn;an o&thorn;er</L>
<L>lat him be trewe and part it wi&thorn; his bro&thorn;er</L>
<L>.I. graunt quod &thorn;e deuel be my feye</L>
<L N="1536">And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde &thorn;ei reden for&thorn;e &thorn;eire weie</L>
<L>And riht att &thorn;e entringe of &thorn;e tounes ende</L>
<L>To whiche &thorn;e somnour schope him for to wende</L>
<L>He sawhe a cart &thorn;at charged was wi&thorn; haye</L>
<L N="1540">Whiche &thorn;at a carter droue for&thorn; on his waye</L>
<L>Dep was &thorn;e way for whyche &thorn;e cart stode</L>
<L>&thorn;is carter smote and striued as he war woode</L>
<L>Heyt brok heyt scotte what spare we fore &thorn;e stones</L>
<L N="1544">The fende quod he &yogh;owe fette bo&thorn;e bodi and bones
<PB REF="00000286.tif" N="258"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="379"></L>
<L>As ferfor&thorn;ly as euer were &yogh;e folde<MILESTONE N="105b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>So muche woo as .I. haue for &yogh;owe &thorn;oled</L>
<L>The deuel haue al bo&thorn;e hors and carte and haye</L>
<L N="1548">Thouht &thorn;is Somnour here schal we haue a pleie</L>
<L>And nere &thorn;e fende he drouhe as nouhten were</L>
<L>An ful priuely rouned in his ere</L>
<L>Herken my bro&thorn;er herken be &thorn;i fei&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1552">Heres &thorn;ou nouht howe &thorn;e carter sei&thorn;e</L>
<L>Hent it a-none for he ha&thorn; &yogh;euen it &thorn;e</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e heye and carte and eke his caples &thorn;re</L>
<L>Nay quod &thorn;e deuel god wote neuer a dele</L>
<L N="1556">It is nouht his entent trust me wele</L>
<L>Ax him &thorn;i self if &thorn;ou trowest not me</L>
<L>Or elles stinte a while and &thorn;ou schalt see</L>
<L>This Carter &thorn;akkes his hors on &thorn;e croupe</L>
<L N="1560">And &thorn;ei be-gonne to drawe and to stoupe</L>
<L>Heyte nowe quod he &thorn;at ihesu criste &yogh;ow blisse</L>
<L>And al his hondewerke bo&thorn;e more and lisse</L>
<L>&thorn;at was my faire lyarde boye</L>
<L N="1564">And .I. praie god saue &thorn;e and seinte loye</L>
<L>Nowe is my carte oute of &thorn;e slouhe parde</L>
<L>Lo bro&thorn;er quod &thorn;e fende what tolde .I. &thorn;e</L>
<L>He[re] maie &yogh;e se myne owen dere bro&thorn;er</L>
<L N="1568">&THORN;e carle spak o &thorn;inge bot he &thorn;ouht ano&thorn;er</L>
<L>Latt vs go for&thorn;e abouten owre viage.</L>
<L>Here wynne .I. no &thorn;inge vpon cariage</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;ei com somwhat oute of &thorn;e toune</L>
<L N="1572">This Somnour to his bro&thorn;er gan roune</L>
<L>Bro&thorn;er quod he here wonne&thorn; an olde rebek</L>
<L>&thorn;at hadde al-moste as leue to lese here neke</L>
<L>As for to &yogh;eue a peny of hire goode</L>
<L N="1576">.I. wil haue tuelue pens &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at sche be wode</L>
<L>Or .I. wil somone hire to oure Office</L>
<L>And &yogh;it god woote of hire know .I. no vice</L>
<L>Bot for &thorn;ou canst nouht as in &thorn;is countre</L>
<L N="1580">Wynne &thorn;i coste take here ensample of me
<PB REF="00000287.tif" N="259"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="380"></L>
<L>This Somnour clepe&thorn; att &thorn;e wydoues gate</L>
<L>Come owte he seide &thorn;ou olde veritate</L>
<L>.I. troue &thorn;ou hast sum frere or preste wi&thorn; &thorn;e</L>
<L N="1584">Who clepe&thorn; seide &thorn;is wif benedicite</L>
<L>God saue &yogh;owe sire what is &yogh;oure swete wil</L>
<L>.I. haue quod he a somons of &thorn;e here a bil</L>
<L>Vp peine of Curseinge loke &thorn;at &thorn;u be<MILESTONE N="106a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1588">To morwe to-for owre Archidiacane kne</L>
<L>To anseward to &thorn;e Courte of certeine &thorn;inges</L>
<L>Now quod sche lorde ihesu criste kinge of kinges</L>
<L>So wissely helpe me as .I. ne maie</L>
<L N="1592">.I. haue bue seke and &thorn;at ful mony a daie</L>
<L>.I. maye nouht so ferre go quod sche ne ride</L>
<L>Bot .I. be dede so prike&thorn; it in my side</L>
<L>May .I. nou&yogh;t ax a libel sir Somonour</L>
<L N="1596">And anseware &thorn;e by my procatoure</L>
<L>To suche a &thorn;inge as men wolden aposen me</L>
<L>&YOGH;is quod &thorn;is Somonour paie anone latt se</L>
<L>Tuelue pens to me. and .I. wil &thorn;e acquite</L>
<L N="1600">I schal no profett haue &thorn;er-by bot lite</L>
<L>Mi maister ha&thorn;e &thorn;e prophet and not .I.</L>
<L>Com of and late me riden hastili</L>
<L>&YOGH;eue me tuelue pens .I. maie no longer tarie</L>
<L N="1604">Tuelue quod sche ladi seint Marie</L>
<L>So wisely helpe out of care and sinne</L>
<L>&THORN;is wide worlde &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at .I. schold it wynne</L>
<L>Ne haue .I. no&yogh;t tuelue pens wi&thorn;-in myne holde</L>
<L N="1608">&YOGH;e knowen wele &thorn;at .I. am pouer and olde</L>
<L>Ky&thorn;e &yogh;oure Almos on me pouere wrecche</L>
<L>Nay &thorn;an quod he foule fende me fecche</L>
<L>If .I. &thorn;e excuse if &thorn;ou scholdest be spilte</L>
<L N="1612">Alas quod sche god wote .I. haue no gilte</L>
<L>Pay me quod he or be &thorn;e swete Anne</L>
<L>As .I. wil bere awaie &thorn;i newe panne</L>
<L>For dett whiche &thorn;ou owest me of olde</L>
<L N="1616">Whan &thorn;ou madest &thorn;in hosbonde kokewolde
<PB REF="00000288.tif" N="260"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="381"></L>
<L>.I. paied att home for &thorn;i correccioun</L>
<L>Thou lext quod sche be my saluacioun</L>
<L>Ne was .I. neuer or now wedowe ne wif</L>
<L N="1620">Somned in-to &yogh;oure court in al my lif</L>
<L>Ne neuer .I. was bot of my body trewe</L>
<L>To &thorn;e deuel blake and rouhe of hewe</L>
<L>&YOGH;if I. &thorn;i body. and my panne also</L>
<L N="1624">And whan &thorn;e deuel herd hir curs so</L>
<L>Vpon hir knes he seid in &thorn;is maner</L>
<L>Now Mable myne owen moder dere</L>
<L>es &thorn;is &yogh;owre wil in ernest &thorn;at &yogh;e seie</L>
<L N="1628">The deuel quod sche fette him ar he deie.</L>
<L>And panne and al but he will him repent<MILESTONE N="106b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Naie olde stote &thorn;at is nou&yogh;t myne entent</L>
<L>Quod &thorn;is Somnour for to repent me</L>
<L N="1632">For any &thorn;inge &thorn;at .I. haue hadde of &thorn;ee</L>
<L>.I. wolde .I. hadde &thorn;i smokke and euery clo&thorn;e</L>
<L>Nowe bro&thorn;ere quod &thorn;e deuel be nouht wro&thorn;e</L>
<L>This body and &thorn;is panne is my be riht</L>
<L N="1636">Thou schalt wi&thorn; me to hell &yogh;ut to-nyht</L>
<L>Where &thorn;ou schalt know of oure priuete</L>
<L>More &thorn;an a maistre of diuinite.</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde &thorn;is foule fende him hente</L>
<L N="1640">Body and soule he wi&thorn; &thorn;e deuel went</L>
<L>Where &thorn;at Somnours han her heritage</L>
<L>And god &thorn;at maad after his ymage</L>
<L>Mankinde saue and gide vs al and sume</L>
<L N="1644">An leue &thorn;is Somnour good man to be-come</L>
<L>Lordinges .I. cou&thorn;e haue tolde &yogh;oue quod &thorn;is frere</L>
<L>Hadde .I. had leiser for &thorn;is Somnour here</L>
<L>After &thorn;e tixt Crist Poule and Iohn</L>
<L N="1648">And of oure o&thorn;er doctours mony on</L>
<L>Suche peines &thorn;at &yogh;oure hert myht a-grise</L>
<L>Albeit so no tunge maie devise</L>
<L>&thorn;ouht &thorn;at .I. myht a &thorn;ousand wynter tell</L>
<L N="1652">&thorn;e peyne of &thorn;ilke corsid house of hell
<PB REF="00000289.tif" N="261"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="382"></L>
<L>Bot for to kepe us fro &thorn;at cursed place</L>
<L>Wake&thorn; and praye&thorn; ihesu for his grace</L>
<L>. . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE></L>
<L N="1656">Herkene&thorn; &thorn;is word be war as in &thorn;is caas</L>
<L>The lion sitte in his awaite alweie</L>
<L>To sle &thorn;e Innocent if &thorn;at he maie</L>
<L>Dispose&thorn; aye &yogh;oure hertes to wi&thorn;-stonde</L>
<L N="1660">The fende &thorn;at &yogh;owe wold make &thorn;rall and bonde</L>
<L>He maie nouht tempten &yogh;owe over &yogh;owre myht</L>
<L>For criste wil be &yogh;oure champion and knyht</L>
<L>And praie&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is somnour him repent</L>
<L N="1664">Of his mesedede ar &thorn;at &thorn;e fende hem hent</L>
</LG>
