<PB REF="00000290.tif" N="262">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="383">
<HEAD>Incipit prologus aparitoris<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 106, <I>back</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>This Somnour in his stirep hihe stode</L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;is frere his hert was so wode</L>
<L>&thorn;at like an haspen lef he quoke for ire</L>
<L N="1668">Lordeinges quod he bot o &thorn;inge .I. desire</L>
<L>.I. &yogh;owe be-seche &thorn;at of &yogh;oure curtesie</L>
<L>Se&thorn; &yogh;e haue herd &thorn;is fals frere lye</L>
<L>As suffre&thorn; me .I. maie a tale tell<MILESTONE N="107a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1672">This frere boste&thorn; &thorn;at he knowe&thorn; hell</L>
<L>As god wote &thorn;at is litel wonder</L>
<L>Freres and fendes ben bot litel in sunder</L>
<L>For parde &yogh;e haue oft time herd tell</L>
<L N="1676">How &thorn;at a frere rauisshed was in hell</L>
<L>In spiret ones be a visione</L>
<L>And as Angel led him vp and downe</L>
<L>To schewen him &thorn;e peynes &thorn;at &thorn;ere were</L>
<L N="1680">In al &thorn;e place sawe he nou&yogh;t a frere</L>
<L>Of o&thorn;er folke he sawe y-nowe in woo</L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;is Angel spak &thorn;e frere &thorn;oo</L>
<L>Now sir quod he haue freres suche grace</L>
<L N="1684">&thorn;at none of hem schal com in-to &thorn;is place</L>
<L>&yogh;is quod &thorn;is Aungel mony a melione</L>
<L>And vn-to Sathanas he had him adoune</L>
<L>And now ha&thorn; Sathanas sai&thorn; he taile</L>
