<L>And to euery spokes ende in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L N="2264">Ful saddely scholden lay here nose iche a frere</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure noble Confessoure &thorn;ere god him saue</L>
<L>Schal holde his vpriht in-to &thorn;e naue</L>
<L>Than schal &thorn;is cherle wi&thorn; bely styffe and touht</L>
<L N="2268">As any tabur hider buen brouht</L>
<L>And sett him on &thorn;e whele riht on &thorn;is carte</L>
<L>Vpon he naue and late him maake a farte</L>
<L>And &yogh;e schol see vp peril of my lif</L>
<L N="2272">Be preue whiche &thorn;at is demonstratif
<PB REF="00000308.tif" N="280"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="401"></L>
<L>&thorn;at equali &thorn;e soune of it wil wende</L>
<L>And eke &thorn;e stynk to &thorn;e spokes ende</L>
<L>Saue &thorn;at &thorn;is wor&thorn;i man &thorn;is confessoure</L>
<L N="2276">Because he is a man of grete honoure</L>
<L>Schal haue &thorn;e first fruyte as reson is</L>
<L>The noble vsaga of freres &yogh;it is &thorn;is</L>
<L>The wor&thorn;i men of hem scholen first be serued</L>
<L N="2280">And Serteynly he ha&thorn; it wele deserued</L>
<L>He ha&thorn; to-day tauht vs so muche goode</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; precheinge in &thorn;e pilput &thorn;er he stoode</L>
<L>&thorn;at .I. maie vouche saue .I. saie for me</L>
<L N="2284">He hadde &thorn;e first smel of fartes &thorn;re</L>
<L>And so wolde al his couent hardely</L>
<L>He bere&thorn; him so faire and so holyly</L>
<L>The lorde &thorn;e lady and eche mon saue &thorn;e frere</L>
<L N="2288">Saiden &thorn;at Iankyn spak in &thorn;is matiere</L>
<L>As wele as Euclide or ptholome<NOTE PLACE="marg">[t <I>is</I> l <I>crost</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L>Toucheinge &thorn;e cherle subtelite</L>
<L>And by hihe make him speke as he spak</L>
<L N="2292">He is no fule ne none demoniak</L>
<L>And Ianky ha&thorn; wonne a newe gowne</L>
<L>Mi tale is done we buen almost att towne</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit fabula Aparitoris;</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="E" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000309.tif" N="281-2">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="403">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>E.</B> FRAGMENT VI.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; 1. THE CLERK'S HEAD-LINK.</HEAD>
<HEAD>LANSDOWNE MS.</HEAD>
<HEAD>&para; Incipit prologus Clerici;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 114</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Sir Clerc of Oxenforde owre Oste seide</L>
<L>&YOGH;e ride as still and coie as do&thorn; a maide</L>
<L>Weer newe spowsed sittinge att &thorn;e borde</L>
<L N="4">This daie ne herde .I. of &yogh;oure tounge a worde</L>
<L>I trowe &thorn;at &yogh;e stody aboute some sophime</L>
<L>Bot Salomon sei&thorn;e euery &thorn;inge ha&thorn;e time</L>
<L>For godessake be&thorn;e of Better chier</L>
<L N="8">It is no time for to stodie here.</L>
<L>Tel vs sum mery tale be &yogh;oure feie<MILESTONE N="114b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For what man is entrede in-to pleie</L>
<L>He nedes mote vnto &thorn;e plaie assent</L>
<L N="12">Bot preches nouht as freres done in lente</L>
<L>To make vs for oure olde sinnes wepe</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;at &thorn;i tale Make us nouht to sl[e]pe</L>
<L>Tell vs sum Mery &thorn;inge Of Auentures</L>
<L N="16">&YOGH;oure termes &yogh;oure coloures &yogh;oure figures</L>
<L>Kepe hem in store til so be &yogh;e enditen</L>
<L>Hihe stylede as whan &thorn;at men to kinges writen</L>
<L>Speke&thorn; so pleine att &thorn;is time .I. &yogh;ou preie</L>
<L N="20">That we may vnderstonde what &yogh;e seie</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;is wor&thorn;i clerke benyngly ansewerd</L>
<L>Oste quod he .I. am vnder &yogh;oure &yogh;erde</L>
<L>&YOGH;e hane of vs as noue &thorn;e gouernance</L>
<L N="24">And &thorn;erfore wil .I. do &yogh;owe obeissance
<PB REF="00000310.tif" N="283"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="404"></L>
<L>As fer as reson axe&thorn; hardely</L>
<L>.I. will &yogh;owe tel a tale whiche &thorn;at .I.</L>
<L>Lerened att P&amacr;douse of a wor&thorn;i clerke</L>
<L N="28">As preuede be his worde and his werk</L>
<L>He is nowe dede and nailed in his chist</L>
<L>.I. praie to god &yogh;if his soule good ryst</L>
<L>Fraunces Petrak &thorn;e Laureat poet</L>
<L N="32">Hiht &thorn;is clerke whos rethorik swoet</L>
<L>Enlumyned al. ytaile of Potrie</L>
<L>As Linian dide of Philosophie</L>
<L>Or lawe or o&thorn;er arte particulere</L>
<L N="36">Bote &thorn;at wil nouht suffur dwell here</L>
<L>Bot as it were a twynklinge of an eye</L>
<L>Hem bo&thorn;e ha&thorn;e and al schal we dye</L>
<L>Bot for to tell of &thorn;is wor&thorn;i man</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;at tauht me &thorn;is tale as he gan</L>
<L>.I. seie &thorn;at wi&thorn; hyhe stile first endite&thorn;</L>
<L>Or he &thorn;e body of his tale write&thorn;</L>
<L>A prohemye in &thorn;e whiche descriue&thorn; he</L>
<L N="44">Pymonde and of Saluces &thorn;e Contre</L>
<L>And speke&thorn; of Appenyne &thorn;e hulles hihe</L>
<L>&thorn;at buen &thorn;e boundes of lumbardie</L>
<L>And of &thorn;e mounte vesulus in special</L>
<L N="48">Where as &thorn;e poe out of a wel smal</L>
<L>Take&thorn; his first springeinge and his sours</L>
<L>&thorn;at estward ay encrese&thorn; in his cours</L>
<L>To Emel warde &middot; ferrir and venise<MILESTONE N="115a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="52">Whiche of longe &thorn;inge were to deuise</L>
<L>And treuly as to my Iuggement</L>
<L>Me &thorn;enke&thorn; &thorn;at a &thorn;inge impertinent</L>
<L>Saue &thorn;at he wil con[u]eyn his matier</L>
<L N="56">Bot &thorn;is is tale whiche &thorn;at &yogh;e maie hier</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit prologus;</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000311.tif" N="284">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="405">
<HEAD>hic incipit fabula <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="115"> <NOTE PLACE="head">[No breaks are between the stanzas in the MS.]</NOTE></HEAD>
<DIV3 N="1" TYPE="part">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="57">Ther is riht att &thorn;e west side of Itaile</L>
<L>Doune att &thorn;e rote of Vesulus &thorn;e colde</L>
<L>A lusti pleine aboundaunt of vitaile</L>
<L>Where mony a toure and toune &thorn;ou maiste beholde</L>
<L>&THORN;at founden were in time of faders olde</L>
<L>And mony ano&thorn;er delitable siht</L>
<L N="63">And Saluces &thorn;e noble contre hiht</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="64">A markes whilome lorde was of &thorn;at lande</L>
<L>[As were his worthi elderes hym be-fore<MILESTONE UNIT="MS Reg. 18 C 2 folio" N="131b"><NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS Reg. 18 C 2<I>omits l.</I> 66-7.]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>And obeissan aie redy to his hande</L>
<L N="67">Were al his lieges bo&thorn;e lesse and more</L>
<L>&THORN;us in delite he leue&thorn; and ha&thorn; done &yogh;ore</L>
<L>Beloued and drad &thorn;orwhe fauoure of fortune</L>
<L N="70">Bo&thorn;e of his lordes and of his comune</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="71">&THORN;ere-wi&thorn; he was as to speke of Lignage</L>
<L N="73">A faire person and stronge and &yogh;onge of age</L>
<L N="72">The gentillest bore of lombardye</L>
<L>[And ful of honoure and of curtesye<NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS Reg. 18 C 2]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>Discrete ynouhe his Contre for to Gye</L>
<L>Saue in summe &thorn;inges he was to blame</L>
<L N="77">And Waltier was &thorn;is &yogh;onge lordes name.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="78">I. blame him &thorn;us &thorn;at he considerd nouht</L>
<L>In time comynge what myht him be-tide</L>
<L>Botte on his luste present was al his &thorn;ouht</L>
<L>[And for to hauke and hunte on euery syde<MILESTONE UNIT="MS Reg. 18 C 2 folio" N="132a">]</L>
<L>Wel nyhe al o&thorn;ere Cures lete he slide</L>
<L>And eke he nolde &thorn;at was &thorn;e werst of all</L>
<L N="84">Wedde no wife for owhte &thorn;at maie befall
<PB REF="00000312.tif" N="285"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="406"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="85">Onely &thorn;at poynte his peple bare so sore</L>
<L>&THORN;at flokingmele on a day to him &thorn;ei went</L>
<L>And of him &thorn;at wisest was of lore</L>
<L N="88">Or elles &thorn;at &thorn;e lorde beste wolde assent</L>
<L>&THORN;at scholde tellen him what his peple ment</L>
<L>Or elles cou&thorn;e schew wele suche matier</L>
<L N="91">He to &thorn;e Markys seide as &yogh;e schal here</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="92">O noble Markes &yogh;oure humanite</L>
<L>Assuri&thorn;e vs and whisse vs hardines</L>
<L>As oft as time is of necessite</L>
<L>That we to &yogh;owe maie tell oure Heuinesse<MILESTONE N="115b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Accept lorde now of &yogh;oure gentilnesse</L>
<L>&thorn;at we wi&thorn; petous hert to &yogh;owe pleine</L>
<L N="98">And late &yogh;oure eres nouht my voice disdeyne</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="99">&para; Al haue .I. nouht to done in &thorn;is matiere</L>
<L>Mor &thorn;an ano&thorn;ere man ha&thorn;e in &thorn;is place</L>
<L>&YOGH;itte as for as muche as &yogh;e my lorde so dere</L>
<L N="102">Haue alweie schewde me fauore and grace</L>
<L>.I. dare &thorn;e better ax of &yogh;owe a space</L>
<L>Off Audience to schewen oure request</L>
<L N="105">And &yogh;e my lorde to do riht as &yogh;owe liest</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="106">&para; For certes lorde so wele lyke&thorn; vs &yogh;owe</L>
<L>And al &yogh;owre werkes and euer ha&thorn;e &thorn;at we</L>
<L>Ne cou&thorn;e nouht oure seluen deuisen howe</L>
<L N="109">We myht leue in more felice</L>
<L>Saue o &thorn;inge lorde if &yogh;owre wil be</L>
<L>&thorn;at for to be a wedded man &yogh;owe list</L>
<L N="112">&thorn;an were &yogh;oure peple in Souereigne hertes rest</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="113">&para; Bou&thorn;e &yogh;oure nek vnder &thorn;at blisfull &yogh;ok</L>
<L>Off Souereignete nouht of seruise</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at men clepe spowsal or wedlok</L>
<L N="116">And &thorn;inke&thorn; lord amonges &yogh;oure &thorn;ouhtes wise
<PB REF="00000313.tif" N="286"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="407"></L>
<L>[ffor of wedlok/ cometh gret emprise<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Harl. 1758, leaf 115; <I>not in</I> MS Reg. 18 C 2]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>For &thorn;ouhe we slepe or wake or roume or ride</L>
<L N="119">Ay. flie&thorn; &thorn;e time and wil no man abide</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="120">And &thorn;ouh &yogh;oure grene &yogh;ou&thorn;e floure as &yogh;ite</L>
<L>&para; In crepe&thorn; Age al wei as still as stone</L>
<L>And de&thorn;e manasse&thorn; euery age and smyte&thorn;</L>
<L N="123">In eche astate for &thorn;er askape&thorn; none</L>
<L>And also certeigne as we knowe ichone</L>
<L>&thorn;at we schal deie. As vncerteigne we all</L>
<L N="126">Biene of &thorn;at daie &thorn;at de&thorn; schal on vs fall</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="127">&para; Accepte &thorn;an of vs &thorn;e trewe entente</L>
<L>&thorn;at neuer &yogh;it refuysed &yogh;oure hest</L>
<L>And we lorde &yogh;if &thorn;at &yogh;e wil asente</L>
<L N="130">Chese &yogh;owe a wif in schort time att &thorn;e lest</L>
<L>Borne of &thorn;e gentelest and of the mest</L>
<L>Of al &thorn;is londe so &thorn;at it ouht seme</L>
<L N="133">Honour to god and &yogh;owe as we can deme</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="134">&para; Deliuer vs of al &thorn;is besy dede</L>
<L>And take&thorn; a wif for hihe goddes sake</L>
<L>ffor if it so be-fel as god for-bede</L>
<L N="137">&thorn;at &thorn;oure de&thorn;e &yogh;oure lignage scholde slake</L>
<L>And &thorn;at a stronge successoure scholde take<MILESTONE N="116a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&YOGH;oure Heritage woo were vs on lyve</L>
<L N="140">Where-for we praie &yogh;owe hastely to wiue</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="141">&para; Here meke preiere and here pitouse chiere</L>
<L>Maaked &yogh;e Markes hert haue pite</L>
<L>[Wol ye quod he myn oune peple deere<MILESTONE UNIT="MS Reg. 18 C 2 folio" N="132b">]</L>
<L N="144">To &thorn;at .y. nerste euer &thorn;ouht to steyne me</L>
<L>I. me reIoysed of my lybertie</L>
<L>&THORN;at selden time is founden mariage</L>
<L N="147">&THORN;ere .I. was fre .I. most be in seruage
<PB REF="00000314.tif" N="287"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="408"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="148">&para; Bot na&thorn;eles .I. see &yogh;oure trewe entente</L>
<L>And truste vpon &yogh;oure witte and haue done aye</L>
<L>Where-for wi&thorn; all my fre wil .I. wil assente</L>
<L N="151">To wedde me als sone as eu[er]e .I. maie</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;ere as &yogh;e haue proferd me to daie</L>
<L>To chese me a wif .I. &yogh;owe relese</L>
<L N="154">&THORN;at choise and pray &yogh;oue of &yogh;oure profure cese</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="155">&para; For .I. wote &thorn;at childern often bien</L>
<L>Vnlyke here elders hem before</L>
<L>Bounte come&thorn; al of god nouht of &thorn;e strene</L>
<L N="158">Of whiche &thorn;ei bue engenderd and y-bore</L>
<L>.I. truste in godese bounte and &thorn;ere fore</L>
<L>Myn mariage and myne astate and reste</L>
<L N="161">.I. him be-take he maie do as him leste</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="162">&para; Lete me alone in cheseinge of my wif</L>
<L>&THORN;at charge vpon my bak .I. wil endure</L>
<L>Bot .I. &yogh;owe preie and charge vpon &yogh;owre lif</L>
<L N="165">&THORN;at what wife .I. take &yogh;e me assure</L>
<L>To worschip hire while &thorn;at hire life maie endure</L>
<L>In worde and werke bo&thorn;e here and euerywhere</L>
<L N="168">As sche an Emperoure douhter weere</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="169">&para; And fer&thorn;er-more &thorn;is schal &yogh;e swere &thorn;at &yogh;e</L>
<L>A&yogh;eine my choice schal neuer gruche ne strive</L>
<L>ffor se&thorn; .I. schal for-go my liberte</L>
<L N="172">Att &yogh;oure request as euer mot .I. &thorn;ryve</L>
<L>&thorn;er as my hert is set &thorn;er wil .I. wiue<NOTE PLACE="marg">[<I>This line at the side, in a different</I> 15<I>th-cent. hand.</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L>And bot &yogh;e wil assente in suche manere</L>
<L N="175">.I. praie &yogh;owe speke&thorn; no more of &thorn;is matiere</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="176">&para; Wi&thorn; hertly wil &thorn;ei swore and assenten</L>
<L>To al &thorn;is &thorn;inge &thorn;er seide no whiht naye</L>
<L>Besekeinge him of grace or &thorn;at &thorn;ei wenten</L>
<L N="179">&thorn;at he wold graunten hem a cerceigne daie
<PB REF="00000315.tif" N="288"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="409"></L>
<L>Of his spowsel as sone as euere he maie</L>
<L>For &yogh;it alweie &thorn;e peple sum what drede</L>
<L>Lest &thorn;at &thorn;is Markes no wife wold wedde<MILESTONE N="116b" UNIT="folio"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="183">&para; He graunted hem a dai suche as him list</L>
<L>On whiche he wil be wedded sekurly.</L>
<L>And seide He dide al &thorn;is att &thorn;eire request</L>
<L N="186">An &thorn;ei wi&thorn;e humble entent ful buxhumly.</L>
<L>Kneleynge vpon here knese ful reuerently</L>
<L>Him &thorn;onkynge all and &thorn;us &thorn;ei haue an ende</L>
<L N="189">Of here entente and home a&yogh;eine &thorn;ei wende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="190">&para; And here-vpon he to his officiers</L>
<L>Commaunde&thorn; for &thorn;e feste to purveie</L>
<L>And to his priue knyhtes and swyers</L>
<L N="193">Suche charge &yogh;af as him list on hem leye</L>
<L>And &thorn;ei to his commandement obeie</L>
<L>And yche of hem do&thorn; his diligence</L>
<L N="196">To do vn-to &thorn;e fest reuerence.</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="2" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART II.]</HEAD>
<HEAD>Prima pars fabule</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="197">Nowht fer fro &thorn;e paleis honurable</L>
<L>Where as &thorn;e Markes schope his mariage</L>
<L>The[re] stode a &thorn;rope of &thorn;e Cite delitable</L>
<L N="200">In whiche &thorn;at pouer folke of &thorn;at vilage</L>
<L>Hadden her bestes and her herbergage</L>
<L>And of here laboure toke here sustinance</L>
<L N="203">After &thorn;e er&thorn;e &yogh;af hem abundance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="204">&para; Amonge &thorn;ise pouer folke &thorn;er dwelled a man</L>
<L>Whiche was holde pouerest of hem al</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;e hihe god sum time sende can</L>
<L N="207">His grace in-to a lite oxe stal</L>
<L>Ianicula Men of &thorn;at &thorn;orpe him cal</L>
<L>A douhter had he faire ynouhe to siht</L>
<L N="210">An Crisilda &thorn;is &yogh;onge maiden hiht
<PB REF="00000316.tif" N="289"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="410"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="211">&para; Bot for to speke of vertuouse beute</L>
<L>&THORN;an was sche one of &thorn;e fairest vnder sonne</L>
<L>Ful pouerly fosterd was sche</L>
<L N="214">No lycourous luste was in hire hert yronne</L>
<L>Wele ofter of &thorn;e wel &thorn;an of &thorn;e tonne</L>
<L>Sche dranke for sche wolde vertuse plese</L>
<L N="217">Sche knewe wele laboure bot none ydel ese</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="218">&para; Bot &thorn;ouhe &thorn;is maide tender were of age</L>
<L>&YOGH;ite in &thorn;e breste of hire virginite</L>
<L>&thorn;ere was y-closed ripe and scharpe corage</L>
<L N="221">And in a grete reuerence and charite</L>
<L>Hire olde pouer fader fosterd sche</L>
<L>A fewe schepe spynynge on &thorn;e felde sche kepped<MILESTONE N="117a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="224">Sche nolde nou&yogh;t be ydel til &thorn;at sche slepped</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="225">&para; And whan sche cam homwarde sche wald bringe</L>
<L>Wortes or o&thorn;er herbes times oft</L>
<L>The whiche sche schredde and se&thorn;e for here leueinge</L>
<L N="228">And maade hire bedde ful harde and no&thorn;inge soft</L>
<L>And ay sche kepped her faders life on loft</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;e euerye obeissance and dilegence</L>
<L N="231">&THORN;at childe myht do to fadere reuerence</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="232">&para; Vpon Crizilda &thorn;e pouer creature</L>
<L>Ful oft si&thorn;e &thorn;e Markes sett is eye</L>
<L>As he on hunteinge rode perauenture</L>
<L N="235">And whan it fell &thorn;at he myht hire aspye</L>
<L>He nouht wi&thorn; wanton lokeinge of folye</L>
<L>His eyen kast on hire bot in sad wise</L>
<L N="238">Vpon hire chere he wolde him of avise</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="239">&para; Commendinge in his ert here wommanhede</L>
<L>And eke hir vertue passinge any whihte</L>
<L>Of so &yogh;onge age as wele in chere as in dede</L>
<L N="242">For &thorn;ouhe &thorn;e peple haue no grete insiht
<PB REF="00000317.tif" N="290"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="411"></L>
<L>In vertue he considered ful riht</L>
<L>Her bounde and disposed &thorn;at he wolde</L>
<L N="245">Wedde hire onely if euere he wed scholde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="246">&para; &thorn;e daie of weddinge cam bot no whihte can</L>
<L>Tel what womman &thorn;at it scholde be</L>
<L>For whiche merveile wondere&thorn; mony man</L>
<L N="249">And seiden whan &thorn;ei were in priuete</L>
<L>Wil nouht oure lorde leue his vanite</L>
<L>Wil he nouht wedde alas alas &thorn;e while</L>
<L N="252">Whi wil he &thorn;us him self and vs be-gile</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="253">&para; Bot na&thorn;eles &thorn;is Markes ha&thorn;e done make</L>
<L>Of gemmes sette in golde. and in asure</L>
<L>Broches and ringes for crisild sake</L>
<L N="256">And of hir clo&thorn;inge toke he &thorn;e mesure</L>
<L>Of a maiden lyke to hire stature</L>
<L>And eke of o&thorn;er ornamentes al</L>
<L N="259">&thorn;at vnto suche a wedynge scholde fal</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="260">&para; The time of hundren of &thorn;e same daie</L>
<L>Aproche&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;is weddynge schold be</L>
<L>And al &thorn;e paleis putt was in araie</L>
<L N="263">Bo&thorn;e hal and chambre iche in his degre</L>
<L>Houses of officez stoffed wi&thorn; plente</L>
<L>Ther mai &thorn;ou see of daynteuos vitaile<MILESTONE N="117b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="266">That maie be founde as fer as last ytaile</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="267">&para; This Roial Markes richeli araide</L>
<L>Lordes and ladies in his compaigne</L>
<L>The whiche vnto &thorn;e feste were praide</L>
<L N="270">And of his retenu &thorn;e bachellarie</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; mony a soune of sundre Melodie</L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;e vilage of whiche .I. tolde</L>
<L N="273">In &thorn;is arraie &thorn;e riht weie ha&thorn;e holde
<PB REF="00000318.tif" N="291"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="412"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="274">&para; Crisid of &thorn;is god wote ful innocente</L>
<L>That for hir schapen al &thorn;is arraie was</L>
<L>To fecche water atte &thorn;e wel is went</L>
<L N="277">And come&thorn; home as sone as euer sche maie</L>
<L>For wele sche hadde herde saie &thorn;at ilke daie</L>
<L>&THORN;at Markes scholde wedde and if sche miht</L>
<L N="280">Sche wol feine haue seine sum of &thorn;at siht</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="281">&para; Sche &thorn;out .I. wil wi&thorn; o&thorn;er maidens stonde</L>
<L>&THORN;at bien my felaues in owre dore and see</L>
<L>The Markes and &thorn;arfore wil .I. fonde</L>
<L N="284">To done att home as sone as it mai be</L>
<L>The laboure &thorn;at longe&thorn; vnto me</L>
<L>And &thorn;an .I. maie att leiser hire be-holde</L>
<L N="287">If sche &thorn;is waie in-to &thorn;e castel holde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="288">&para; And as sche wolde ouer &thorn;e &thorn;resshewolde gone</L>
<L>The Markes came and ganne hire for to call</L>
<L>And sche sett doune hire water pott a-none</L>
<L N="291">Be-side &thorn;e &thorn;resshewold of &thorn;is ox. stall</L>
<L>And doune vpon hir knesse sche gan to fall</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; sadde Countenance knele&thorn; still</L>
<L N="294">Til sche hadd herde what was &thorn;e lordes will</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="295">&para; This &thorn;ouhtful Marquys spake vnto &thorn;is maide</L>
<L>Ful soburly and seide in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>Where es &yogh;owre fader Crizild he seide</L>
<L N="298">And sche wi&thorn; reuerence and humble chiere</L>
<L>Ansewerd lorde he is all redie here</L>
<L>And in sche go&thorn;e wi&thorn;-oute langer lette</L>
<L N="301">And to &thorn;e Markys hir fader sche fette</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="302">&para; He be &thorn;e honde &thorn;an toke &thorn;is olde man</L>
<L>And seide &thorn;us whan he had him a side</L>
<L>Ianicula .I. ney&thorn;ere maie ne kan</L>
<L N="305">lenger &thorn;e plesance of myne herte hide
<PB REF="00000319.tif" N="292"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="413"></L>
<L>If &thorn;at &thorn;ou vouche-saf what so be-tide</L>
<L>&THORN;i douhter .I. wil take ar &thorn;at .I. wende<MILESTONE N="118a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="308">As for my wif vnto hire liues ende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="309">&para; Thowe louest me .I. wote it wele certeine</L>
<L>And arte my fei&thorn;eful liege Maifaie y-bore</L>
<L>And al &thorn;at like&thorn; me .I. dar wel seine</L>
<L N="312">It like&thorn; &thorn;e and specialische &thorn;ere-fore</L>
<L>Tel me &thorn;at point as .I. haue seide be-fore</L>
<L>If &thorn;at &thorn;ou wilte vnto &thorn;at purpose drawe</L>
<L N="315">To take me as for &thorn;i son in lawe</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="316">&para; The sodeyne caas &thorn;e man a-stoned so</L>
<L>&thorn;at rede he wex a-bassched and al qwakynge</L>
<L>He stoode vnne&thorn; he seide worde no moo</L>
<L N="319">Bot only &thorn;us lorde quod he my willynge</L>
<L>Is as &yogh;e will nouht a-&yogh;eines &yogh;oure lykeynge</L>
<L>.I. wil no&thorn;inge &yogh;e be my lorde so dere</L>
<L N="322">Bot as &yogh;ow luste gouerne&thorn; &thorn;is matier</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="323">&para; &YOGH;it wil .I. quod &thorn;is Markes softlye</L>
<L>&THORN;at in &thorn;i chamber .I. and &thorn;owe and sche</L>
<L>Haue a collacione and wost &thorn;u whie</L>
<L N="326">For .I. wil ax if &thorn;at hire wil bee</L>
<L>To be my wif and reule hire aftere me</L>
<L>And al &thorn;is schal be done in &thorn;i presence</L>
<L N="329">.I. wil nouht speke owte of &thorn;ine Audience</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="330">&para; And in hire Chambre while &thorn;ei were aboute</L>
<L>Here treteis whiche &thorn;at &yogh;e schal after here</L>
<L>The peple cam in to &thorn;e hous wi&thorn;-oute</L>
<L N="333">And wondred hem in here honest manere</L>
<L>And tentifly sche kepped hir fadere dere</L>
<L>Bot vtterly Crizilda wonder myht</L>
<L N="336">For neuer eft sauhe sche suche a siht
<PB REF="00000320.tif" N="293"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="414"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="337">&para; No wonder is &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at sche were a-stoned</L>
<L>To se so grete a geste in &thorn;at place</L>
<L>Sche neuer was to suche gestez woned</L>
<L N="340">For which sche lokede wi&thorn; ful pale face</L>
<L>Bot schortly for&thorn;e &thorn;is matie[r] for to chace</L>
<L>Thes aren &thorn;e wordes &thorn;at Markes seide</L>
<L N="343">To his benigne fei&thorn;-ful maide</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="344">&para; Crizild he seide &yogh;e schal wele vnderstonde</L>
<L>It like&thorn; to &yogh;oure fader and to me</L>
<L>&THORN;at .I. &yogh;owe wedde and eke it maie so stonde</L>
<L N="347">As .I. suppose &yogh;e wil &thorn;at it so be</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;is demandes ax .I. first quod he.</L>
<L>That se&thorn;en it schal be done in hastie wise<MILESTONE N="118b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="350">Wil &yogh;e assent or elles &yogh;owe avise</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="351">&para; I seie &thorn;is be redye wi&thorn; goode herte</L>
<L>To al my lust and &thorn;at I. frely maie</L>
<L>As me best &thorn;enke&thorn; do &yogh;owe knowe ore smerte</L>
<L N="354">And neuer &thorn;e to grucche it nyht ne daie</L>
<L>And eke whan .I. seie &yogh;e ne saie nouht naie</L>
<L>Ney&thorn;er be worde ne be frounynge contenance</L>
<L N="357">Swere &thorn;is and here .I. swere oure alliance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="358">&para; Weddinge vpon &thorn;is worde whakeinge for drede</L>
<L>Sche seide lorde vndigne or vnwor&thorn;i</L>
<L>Am .I. to &thorn;at ilke honor &thorn;at &yogh;e me bede</L>
<L N="361">Bot as &yogh;e wil &yogh;oure self riht so wil .I.</L>
<L>And here .I. swere &thorn;at neuer wilingely</L>
<L>In werke ne &thorn;ouhte .I. nyl &yogh;owe disobeie</L>
<L N="364">For to be dede &thorn;ouhe me were lo&thorn;e to deie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="365">&para; This is ynouhe Crizilda myne quod he</L>
<L>And for&thorn;e he go&thorn;e wi&thorn;e a ful sobre chiere</L>
<L>Oute atte &thorn;e dore and after &thorn;at cam sche</L>
<L N="368">And to &thorn;e peple he seide in &thorn;is maniere
<PB REF="00000321.tif" N="294"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="415"></L>
<L>This is my wife quod he &thorn;at stonde&thorn; hiere</L>
<L>Honoure&thorn; hir and loue&thorn; hire eke .I. preie</L>
<L N="371">Who so me loue&thorn;e &thorn;are is no more to seie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="372">&para; And for &thorn;at no&thorn;inge of hire olde gere</L>
<L>Sche scholde bringe in to his house he badde</L>
<L>&THORN;at wemmen scholde dispoylen [hire] riht &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="375">Of whiche &thorn;e ladies weren no&thorn;inge gladde</L>
<L>To handel hire clo&thorn;es where in sche was cladde</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles &thorn;is maiden briht of hewe</L>
<L N="378">Fro &thorn;e fote to &thorn;e hede &thorn;ei clo&thorn;ed hane al newe</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="379">&para; Her here ha &thorn;ei kembed &thorn;at laie vntressed</L>
<L N="381">Thei tirede hir hede &thorn;at longe rudely laie dressed</L>
<L N="380">Ful roodely. and wi&thorn; hire fingers smale</L>
<L N="382">Of hire araye what scholde .I. maake a tale</L>
<L>Sche is nowe faire of hewe &thorn;at arst was pale</L>
<L>Vnne&thorn; &thorn;e peple hire knewe for hire fairenesse</L>
<L N="385">Whan sche transemute was in suche rechesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="386">&para; This Markes ha&thorn; her wed wi&thorn; a ringe</L>
<L>Brouht for &thorn;e same cause and hire sette</L>
<L>Vpon an hors snowe white and wele Amblynge</L>
<L N="389">And to &thorn;e paleis ar he langer lette</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; Ioyful peple &thorn;at hire ladde and mette</L>
<L>Conueyde hire and &thorn;us &thorn;e daie &thorn;ei spende<MILESTONE N="119a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="392">In reuele til &thorn;e sonne gan descende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="393">&para; And schortly for&thorn;e &thorn;is tale for to chace</L>
<L>.I. seie &thorn;at to &thorn;is new Marquysesse</L>
<L>God ha&thorn;e suche fauore sent hire of his grace</L>
<L N="396">&THORN;at it ne semed nouht be liknesse</L>
<L>&THORN;at sche was borne and fedde in rudesse</L>
<L>As in a Cote or in an ox stall</L>
<L N="399">Bot norissched in an Emperours hall
<PB REF="00000322.tif" N="295"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="416"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="400">&para; To euery whight sche waxen is so dere</L>
<L>And worschipful &thorn;at folke &thorn;ere sche was bore</L>
<L>And frome hire bir&thorn;e knewe hire &yogh;ere be &yogh;ere</L>
<L N="403">Vnne&thorn; trowed &thorn;ei bot dorst han swore</L>
<L>That to Ianicul of whiche .I. spak before</L>
<L>Sche douhter nas for as be couertore</L>
<L N="406">Hem &thorn;ouht sche was a no&thorn;er creature</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="407">&para; For &thorn;ouhe euere vertuous was sche</L>
<L>Sche was encresed in suche excellence</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ewes goode sette in hihe bounte</L>
<L N="410">And so discrete and faire of eloquence</L>
<L>So benigne and digne of reuerence</L>
<L>And cou&thorn;e so &thorn;e peple hertes so enbrace</L>
<L N="413">That iche hire loue&thorn;e &thorn;at loke&thorn; in hire face</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="414">&para; Nou&yogh;t only of Saluces in &thorn;e toune</L>
<L>Purplyste was &thorn;e bounte of hire name</L>
<L>Bote eke be-side in mony a Regioune</L>
<L N="417">If one seide wele a no&thorn;er seide &thorn;e same</L>
<L>So sprede&thorn;e of hire hihe bounte and fame</L>
<L>That men and wemmen also wele &yogh;onge as olde</L>
<L N="420">Gone to Saluce vpon hire to be-holde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="421">&para; Thus Walter lowly. nou&yogh;t. but royalye</L>
<L>Wedded wi&thorn; fortunate honeste</L>
<L>In goddes pes leue&thorn; ful esilye</L>
<L N="424">Att home and outewarde grace. ynowhe had he</L>
<L>And for he sauhe &thorn;at vnder lowe degre</L>
<L>Was oft vertue hidde &thorn;e peple him helde</L>
<L N="427">A prudent man and &thorn;at is seene ful selde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="428">&para; Nouht only &thorn;is Crisilde &thorn;ourhe hire witte</L>
<L>Cou&thorn;e al &thorn;e fei&thorn;e of wifly homlynesse</L>
<L>Bot eke whan &thorn;at &thorn;e caas required it</L>
<L N="431">The comune profit cou&thorn;e sche redresse
<PB REF="00000323.tif" N="296"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="417"></L>
<L>Ther nas discorde rancor ne heuinesse</L>
<L>In al &thorn;at londe &thorn;at sche cou&thorn;e apese<MILESTONE N="119b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="434">An wisely bringe hem al in hertes ese</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="435">&para; Thouhe &thorn;at hir husbonde absent were anone</L>
<L>If gentil men or o&thorn;ere of here contre</L>
<L>Weere wro&thorn;e sche wolde bringe hem att one</L>
<L N="438">So wise and ripe wordes had sche</L>
<L>And Iuggement of so grete equite</L>
<L>That from heuen ysente was as men wende</L>
<L N="441">The peple to plese and euery wronge to amende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="442">&para; Nouht longe time after &thorn;at &thorn;is Crisilde</L>
<L>Was wedded sche a douhter ha&thorn; .I.-bore</L>
<L>Al had hire leuer haue borne a knaue childe</L>
<L N="445">Gladd was &thorn;is markes and his folk &thorn;er fore</L>
<L>For &thorn;ouhe a mayden childe cam al before</L>
<L>Sche maie vnto a knaue childe atteigne</L>
<L N="448">Belikned se&thorn; sche is nouht bareine</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>[Explicit] Secunda pars ffabule.</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="3" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART III.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="449">There fel att befalle&thorn; times mo [<I>or</I> ino]</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at &thorn;is childe hadde sowked bot a &thorn;rowe</L>
<L>This Markes in his hert lange&thorn; so</L>
<L N="452">To tempt his wif hire saddenesse for to knowe</L>
<L>That he ne myht oute of his hert &thorn;rowe</L>
<L>This meruelous desire his wif to assaie</L>
<L N="455">Nedeles god wote he &thorn;ouht hire to affraie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="456">&para; He hadde assaide hire ynouhe before</L>
<L>And fonde hire euere goode what nedede&thorn;e</L>
<L>Hire for to tempte and alweie more and more</L>
<L N="459">Bot as for me .I. seie &thorn;at yuel it sitte</L>
<L>&THORN;ouhe sume men it preise for a subtile witte</L>
<L>To assaie a wif whan &thorn;at it is no nede</L>
<L N="462">And to putten hire in angwysse and in drede
<PB REF="00000324.tif" N="297"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="418"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="463">&para; ffor whiche &thorn;is markys wrouht in &thorn;is manere</L>
<L>He cam a nyht alone &thorn;ere as sche leye</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; steren face and wi&thorn; trouble chiere</L>
<L N="466">And seide &thorn;us Cr[i]&yogh;ilde quod he &thorn;at deye</L>
<L>&THORN;at .I. &yogh;oue toke oute of &yogh;oure poure aray</L>
<L>And putt &yogh;owe in astate of hihe noblesse</L>
<L N="469">&YOGH;e haue nouht for-geten as .I. gesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="470">&para; .I. seie Criselde &thorn;is present dignite</L>
<L>In whiche .I. haue put &yogh;owe as. I trowe</L>
<L>Make&thorn; &yogh;owe nouht for-&yogh;eteful for to be</L>
<L N="473">&THORN;at .I &yogh;owe toke in poure astate ful lowe</L>
<L>For any wele &yogh;e moste &yogh;oure selue knowe<MILESTONE N="120a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Take hede of euery worde &thorn;at .I. &yogh;owe seie</L>
<L N="476">&THORN;ere is no whight &thorn;at here&thorn; it bot we tweye</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="477">&para; &YOGH;e wote &yogh;oure self wele howe &thorn;at &yogh;e com here</L>
<L>In to &thorn;is house &thorn;at is nouht longe a go</L>
<L>And &thorn;ouhe to me &yogh;e be riht leue and dere</L>
<L N="480">Vn-to my gentils &yogh;e be no&thorn;inge so</L>
<L>Thei seie to hem it is grete schame and woo</L>
<L>For to be soubgetes and be in seruage</L>
<L N="483">To &thorn;e &thorn;at art borne of a smale vilage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="484">&para; And namely se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;i douhter was bore</L>
<L>&THORN;is wordes haue &thorn;ei spoken doutelese</L>
<L>Bot .I. desire as .I. haue done be-fore</L>
<L N="487">To lede my lyue wi&thorn; hem in rest and pese</L>
<L>.I. maie nouht in &thorn;is caas be recheles</L>
<L>.I. mote do wi&thorn; &thorn;i douhter for &thorn;e best</L>
<L N="490">Nat as .I. wolde bot as my genteles leste.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="491">&para; And &yogh;ite god wote &thorn;is is ful lo&thorn;e to me</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles wi&thorn; owten &yogh;oure witeinge</L>
<L>.I. wil nouht do bot &thorn;is will .I. quod he</L>
<L N="494">&THORN;at &yogh;e to me assent as in &thorn;is &thorn;inge
<PB REF="00000325.tif" N="298"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="419"></L>
<L>Schewe nowe &yogh;oure pacience as in werkynge</L>
<L>&THORN;at me &yogh;e hiht and swore in &yogh;oure vilage</L>
<L N="497">&THORN;at daie &thorn;at maked was oure Mariage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="498">&para; Whan sche hadde herde al &thorn;is sche nat ameued</L>
<L>Nei&thorn;ere in worde ne chiere ne countenance</L>
<L>For as it semede sche was nouht agreued</L>
<L N="501">Sche saide lorde al li&thorn;e in &yogh;oure plesance</L>
<L>My childe and .I. wi&thorn; hertly obeissance</L>
<L>Bene &yogh;oures all. and &yogh;e mowe saue and spille</L>
<L N="504">&YOGH;oure owen &thorn;inge worke&thorn; after &yogh;oure wille</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="505">&para; There maie no &thorn;inge so god my soule saue</L>
<L>Likeinge to &yogh;owe &thorn;at maie displesen me</L>
<L>Ne .I. desire no &thorn;inge for to haue</L>
<L N="508">Ne drede for to leese saue onlye &thorn;e</L>
<L>&THORN;is wil is in myne hert and aie schal be</L>
<L>Ne lenge&thorn; of time or de&thorn;e maie &thorn;is deface</L>
<L N="511">Ne chaunge myne corage to ano&thorn;er place</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="512">&para; Glad was &thorn;is Marquys for hir ansewaringe</L>
<L>Bot &yogh;it he feyned. as it wer nouht soo</L>
<L>Al drery was his chier as his lokeinge</L>
<L N="515">Whan &thorn;at he scholde oute of &thorn;e chambre goo.</L>
<L>Sone after &thorn;is a furlonge waie or tuo<MILESTONE N="120b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>He priuely ha&thorn; tolde al his entent</L>
<L N="518">Vnto a man of his assent</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="519">&para; A maner seriant was &thorn;is priue man</L>
<L>&THORN;e whiche he fei&thorn;eful often fonden hadd</L>
<L>In &thorn;inge grete. and eke suche folke wele can.</L>
<L N="522">Done execucione of &thorn;inges badde</L>
<L>The lorde knewe wele &thorn;at he him loued and dradde</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;is Sereiant knewe his lordes wille</L>
<L N="525">In-to &thorn;e chambure he stalked him ful stille
<PB REF="00000326.tif" N="299"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="420"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="526">&para; Madame He seide &yogh;e mot for-&yogh;iue it me</L>
<L>&THORN;ouhe .I. do &thorn;inge whiche .I. am constreeyned</L>
<L>&YOGH;e bue so wise &thorn;at ful wele knowen &yogh;e</L>
<L N="529">&THORN;at lordes hestes mow nou&yogh;t be feyned</L>
<L>&THORN;ay may wele be weiled or compleyned</L>
<L>Bot most nede to here luste obeie.</L>
<L N="532">And so wil .I. &thorn;er is no more to seie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="533">&para; This childe am .I. commaunded for to take</L>
<L>And spak no more bot owte &thorn;e childe he hent</L>
<L>Dispytously and gan a chere make</L>
<L N="536">As &thorn;ouhe he wolde haue sleyne it ar he went</L>
<L>Crisilde most al suffur and consent</L>
<L>And as a lombe sche sitte&thorn; meke and still</L>
<L N="539">And lete &thorn;is seriant haue al his will</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="540">&para; Suspecious was &thorn;e fame of &thorn;is manne</L>
<L>Suspecte his face suspecte his worde also</L>
<L>Suspecte &thorn;e time in whiche he &thorn;is be-ganne</L>
<L N="543">Alas his douhter &thorn;at sche loued so</L>
<L>Sche wende he wolde haue sleyne it riht &thorn;o</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles sche ney&thorn;er wepped ne siked</L>
<L N="546">Confemeinge hir to &thorn;at &thorn;at markes lyked</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="547">&para; Bot att &thorn;e last speke sche began</L>
<L>And mekely to &thorn;e seriant praiede</L>
<L>So as he was a wor&thorn;i gentil man</L>
<L N="550">&THORN;at sche mot kisse hir childe ar &thorn;at it deide</L>
<L>And in hire barme &thorn;is litel childe sche leide</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; ful sadde face and gan &thorn;is childe to blisse</L>
<L N="553">And lulled it and affter gan it kisse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="554">&para; And &thorn;us sche seide in hire benigne voice</L>
<L>Fare wele my childe .I. schal &thorn;e neuer se</L>
<L>Bot se&thorn;e .I. haue &thorn;e merked wi&thorn; &thorn;e croyse</L>
<L N="557">Of &thorn;ilke fader blissed mot &thorn;ou be.
<PB REF="00000327.tif" N="300"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="421"></L>
<L>&THORN;at for vs deide vpon a cros of tre<MILESTONE N="121a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Thi soule litel childe .I. him be-take</L>
<L N="560">For &thorn;is nyht schalt &thorn;ou deie for my saake</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="561">&para; I trowe to a norice in &thorn;is caas</L>
<L>It hadde bien harde &thorn;is reu&thorn;e for to see</L>
<L>Wele myht a moder &thorn;an haue cride alas</L>
<L N="564">Bott na&thorn;eles so sadde stedfast was sche</L>
<L>&THORN;at sche endure&thorn; al aduersite</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e Seriaunte mekely sche seide</L>
<L N="567">Haue here a&yogh;eine &yogh;oure litel &yogh;onge maide</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="568">&para; Go&thorn;e nowe quod sche and do&thorn;e my lordes heste</L>
<L>Bott o &thorn;inge wolde .I. praie &yogh;oue of &yogh;oure grace</L>
<L>&THORN;at but my lorde for-badde &yogh;owe att &thorn;e leste</L>
<L N="571">Beri&thorn;e &thorn;is litel body in sum place</L>
<L>&THORN;at bestes ne birdes it to-race</L>
<L>Bot he ne wolde no worde to &thorn;e pupos seie</L>
<L N="574">Bot toke &thorn;e childe and wente vpon his weie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="575">&para; This seriaunt came vnto &thorn;is lorde a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>And of Crisilde wordes and hir chiere</L>
<L>He tolde him worde for worde in schorte and pleine</L>
<L N="578">And him presente&thorn; wi&thorn; his douhter dere</L>
<L>Somwhat &thorn;is lorde had reu&thorn;e in his manere</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles his purpos helde he still</L>
<L N="581">As lordes done whan &thorn;ei wil haue here will</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="582">&para; And badde &thorn;is sergeant &thorn;at he priuely</L>
<L>Scholde &thorn;is childe ful oft wynde and wrappe</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; al circumstance tenderly</L>
<L N="585">And Carie it in a cofer or in a lappe</L>
<L>Bott vppon peine his hede of for to swappe</L>
<L>&THORN;at no man scholde knowe of his entente</L>
<L N="588">Ne whene ne whedere &thorn;at he wente
<PB REF="00000328.tif" N="301"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="422"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="589">&para; Bot att &thorn;e Boloigne it to his suster dere</L>
<L>&thorn;at ilke time of Pauyke was Countesse</L>
<L>He scholde it take and schewe hir &thorn;is matiere</L>
<L N="592">Be-secheinge hire to tone hir besinesse</L>
<L>This childe to fostre in al gentillesse</L>
<L>And whos childe &thorn;at it was he bad hire hide</L>
<L N="595">Frome euery whiht for ouhte &thorn;at maie be-tide</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="596">&para; &THORN;is sergeant go&thorn;e and ha&thorn;e fulfilled &thorn;is &thorn;inge</L>
<L>Bot nowe to &thorn;is ma[r]kes retorne wee</L>
<L>For nowe go&thorn;e he ful oft ymagyneinge</L>
<L N="599">&yogh;if be his wyues chiere he myht see</L>
<L>Or be hir worde perceyue &thorn;at sche<MILESTONE N="121b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Were chaunged bot he neuer cou&thorn;e hir finde</L>
<L N="602">Bot euere in one ylike sadde and kynde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="603">&para; As gladde as besy as humble in seruise</L>
<L>And eke in loue as sche was wont to be</L>
<L>Was sche to him in euery manere wise</L>
<L N="606">Ne of hir douhter nouht a worde spak sche</L>
<L>Accident for none aduersite</L>
<L>Was seine in hire ne neuer hir douhter name</L>
<L N="609">Ne nemend sche in ernest ne in game</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>[Explicit] Tercia pars fabule.</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="4" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART IV.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="610">IN &thorn;is . astate &thorn;ere ben passed foure &yogh;ere</L>
<L>Er sche wi&thorn; childe was Bot as god wolde</L>
<L>A knaue childe sche bare be &thorn;is waltere</L>
<L N="613">Ful gracious and faire to be-holde</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;at folke it to his fader tolde</L>
<L>Nouht onlyche he but al &thorn;e contre mury</L>
<L N="616">Was for &thorn;is and god &thorn;ei &thorn;onke and hery</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="617">&para; Whan it was tuo &yogh;ere olde and fro &thorn;e breste</L>
<L>Departid of his norice on a daye</L>
<L>&thorn;is Markes cauht &yogh;it ano&thorn;ere leste
<PB REF="00000329.tif" N="302"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="423"></L>
<L N="620">To tempte his wif &yogh;it ofter if he maie</L>
<L>O nedeles was sche tempted in assaie</L>
<L>Bot wedded men knowen no mesure</L>
<L N="623">Whan &thorn;at &thorn;ei finde a pacient creature</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="624">&para; Wif quod &thorn;is Markes &yogh;e haue herde of &thorn;is</L>
<L>My peple sekely bere&thorn; heuye of oure mariage</L>
<L>And namely se&thorn; my son borne is</L>
<L N="627">Nowe is wers &thorn;an euer in al oure age</L>
<L>The mormure sle&thorn;e myn herte and myne corage</L>
<L>For to myne eres comme&thorn; voice so smarte</L>
<L N="630">That it wel nyhe destruyde hathe myne herte</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="631">&para; Nowe seye &thorn;ei &thorn;us whan Waltier is a-gone</L>
<L>Than schal &thorn;e blode of Ianicle succede</L>
<L>And bien oure lorde for o&thorn;ere haue we none</L>
<L N="634">Suche wordes sei&thorn;e my peple it is no drede</L>
<L>Wele ouhte .I. of suche murmure taken hede</L>
<L>For certeinly .I. drede suche sentence</L>
<L N="637">&THORN;ouhe &thorn;ei nouht pleine speke in myne audience</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="638">&para; I wolde leue in pes if &thorn;at .I. myhte</L>
<L>Where-fore .I. am disposed vtterlye</L>
<L>As .I. his suster serued be nyhte</L>
<L N="641">Riht so &thorn;enke .I. to serue him priuely<MILESTONE N="122a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Thus warne .I. &yogh;owe for &yogh;e nouht sodanly</L>
<L>Oute of &yogh;oure selue for no woo scholde outraie</L>
<L N="644">Be&thorn;e pacient and &thorn;erfore .I. &yogh;ow preie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="645">&para; .I. haue quod sche saide and euer schal</L>
<L>.I. will no &thorn;inge certeigne</L>
<L>Bot as &yogh;oue luste nouht greue&thorn;e me al</L>
<L N="648">&THORN;ouhe &thorn;at my douhter and my son bue sleine</L>
<L>Att &yogh;oure commandement &thorn;is is to seine</L>
<L>.I. haue nouht had no parte of childern tweyne</L>
<L N="651">Bot first sekenesse and after woo and peine
<PB REF="00000330.tif" N="303"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="424"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="652">&para; &YOGH;e bene oure lorde do wi&thorn; &yogh;oure owen &thorn;inge</L>
<L>Riht as &yogh;owe liste axe&thorn;e no rede att me</L>
<L>For as .I. left att home al my clo&thorn;inge</L>
<L N="655">Whan .I. first came to &yogh;owe riht so quod sche</L>
<L>Lest .I. my wil and al my liberte</L>
<L>And toke &yogh;oure clo&thorn;inge where-fore .I. &yogh;owe preie</L>
<L N="658">Do&thorn;e &yogh;oure plesance .I. wil &yogh;oure lust obeie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="659">&para; And certes if .I. had prescience</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure will to knowe ar &yogh;e &yogh;oure lust me tolde</L>
<L>.I. wolde it do wi&thorn;-outen necligence</L>
<L N="662">Bot nowe .I. wote &yogh;oure luste and what &yogh;e wolde</L>
<L>Al &yogh;oure plesance ferme and plesance .I. holde</L>
<L>For wist .I. &thorn;at my de&thorn;e wolde do &yogh;owe ese</L>
<L N="665">Riht gladly wolde .I. deie &yogh;owe to plese</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="666">&para; De&thorn; maie nouht make no comparisone</L>
<L>Vnto owre loue and whan &thorn;is Markis seye</L>
<L>&THORN;e Countenance. of his wif he cast a-doune</L>
<L N="669">His ey&yogh;en tuo and wonder&thorn; &thorn;at sche maye</L>
<L>In paciens suffur al &thorn;is araye</L>
<L>And for&thorn;e he go&thorn; wi&thorn; drery countenance</L>
<L N="672">Bot to his hert it was riht grete plesance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="673">&para; &THORN;is Ogel seriant in &thorn;e same wise</L>
<L>&THORN;at he hir douhte cauht riht so he</L>
<L>Or wers. if men wers can deuise</L>
<L N="676">Ha&thorn;e hente hire son &thorn;at ful was of beute</L>
<L>And euer in oone so paciente was sche</L>
<L>That sche no chiere made of heuinesse</L>
<L N="679">Bott kissed hir son and after gan it blesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="680">&para; Saue &thorn;is sche praide him if &thorn;at he myht</L>
<L>Hir litel son he wolde in er&thorn;e graue</L>
<L>His tendre limes delicate to siht</L>
<L N="683">Fro foules and fro bestes forto saue<MILESTONE N="122b" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000331.tif" N="304"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="425"></L>
<L>Bot sche none ansewere of him myht haue</L>
<L>He went his waie as he no &thorn;inge rouht</L>
<L N="686">Bot to Boleigne he tendurly it brouht</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="687">&para; This Markes wondre&thorn; euer lenger &thorn;e more</L>
<L>Vpon hire paciens and if &thorn;at he</L>
<L>Ne hadde so&thorn;ely knowe &thorn;ere before</L>
<L N="690">&THORN;at perfitly hir cheldern loued sche</L>
<L>He wolde haue wende &thorn;at of summe subtilite</L>
<L>And of Males or for cruel curage</L>
<L N="693">&THORN;at sche hadde sufferd &thorn;is wi&thorn; sadde visage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="694">&para; Bot wele he knewe next him selue certeigne</L>
<L>Sche loued hir childern best in euery wise</L>
<L>Bot nowe of wemmen wolde .I. axe feine</L>
<L N="697">If &thorn;es assaies myht nouht suffise</L>
<L>What cou&thorn;e a stordy husbonde more deuyse</L>
<L>to preue his wif and hir stedfastnesse</L>
<L N="700">And he continuinge euer in stordenesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="701">&para; Bot &thorn;ere buen folke of suche condicione</L>
<L>&thorn;at whan &thorn;e haue a certeine purpos take</L>
<L>&thorn;ei can nouht stinte of hire entencion</L>
<L N="704">Bot riht as &thorn;ei were bounden to a stake</L>
<L>&thorn;ai wil nouht of &thorn;at first purpos slake</L>
<L>Riht so &thorn;is ma[r]kes fully ha&thorn;e purposyd</L>
<L N="707">To tempt his wif as he was firste disposyd</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="708">&para; He waite&thorn; if be worde or countenance</L>
<L>That sche to him was chaunged of Corage</L>
<L>Bot neuer cou&thorn;e he finde variance</L>
<L N="711">Sche was aie oon in hert and in visage</L>
<L>And aie &thorn;e for&thorn;er sche was in age</L>
<L>The more trewe if &thorn;at it were possible</L>
<L N="714">Sche was to him loue and more pesible
<PB REF="00000332.tif" N="305"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="426"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="715">&para; For whiche it semed &thorn;us &thorn;at of hem tuo</L>
<L>&THORN;er nas bot o will for as Waltier luste</L>
<L>&THORN;at same lust was hir plesance also</L>
<L N="718">And god he &thorn;onked as fel for &thorn;e beste</L>
<L>Sch schewed wele for no werldly vnreste</L>
<L>A wif as of hire self no &thorn;inge ne scholde</L>
<L N="721">Wille in effecte bot as hir husbonde wolde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="722">&para; The sclander of Walter oft and wide spradde</L>
<L>That of a cruel hert he wikkedly</L>
<L>For he a pouer womman wedded hadde</L>
<L N="725">Had murdred bo&thorn; his childern priuely<MILESTONE N="123a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Suche murmur was ymonge hem comunly</L>
<L>No wonder is for to &thorn;e peples ere</L>
<L N="728">&THORN;ere come no worde bot &thorn;at &thorn;ei murdred were</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="729">&para; ffor whiche &thorn;er as his peple &thorn;ere before</L>
<L>Had loued him wel &thorn;e sclaunder of his defame</L>
<L>Maade hem &thorn;at &thorn;ei hated him &thorn;er-fore</L>
<L N="732">To biene a Mordrer is an hateful name</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles for ernest ne for game</L>
<L>He of his crewel purpos nold stint</L>
<L N="735">To tempte his wif was sette al his entent</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="736">&para; Whan &thorn;at his douhter . xij. &yogh;ere was of age</L>
<L>He to &thorn;e Courte of Rome in soubtile wise</L>
<L>Enformed of his will and sente his message</L>
<L N="739">Commandeinge hem suche bulles to douise</L>
<L>In &thorn;is manere and in &thorn;is same gise</L>
<L>Howe &thorn;at &thorn;e pope for his peple rest</L>
<L N="742">Bat him to wedde ano&thorn;er wif &yogh;if &thorn;at him lest</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="743">&para; I saie he badde &thorn;ei scholde countrefete</L>
<L>The popes bulles makeinge mencione</L>
<L>&thorn;at ha&thorn;e leue his first wif to lete</L>
<L N="746">As by &thorn;e popes despensacione
<PB REF="00000333.tif" N="306"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="427"></L>
<L>To stinte Rancor and discencione</L>
<L>Be-twix his peple and him &thorn;us spake &thorn;e bulle</L>
<L N="749">The whiche &thorn;ei han publisced att &thorn;e fulle</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="750">&para; The rode peple as it no wonder is</L>
<L>Wenden ful wel &thorn;at it hadd be riht so</L>
<L>Bot whan &thorn;is ti&thorn;inges came to Crisildis</L>
<L N="753">.I. deme &thorn;at hire hert was ful woo</L>
<L>Bot sche ylike sadde for euer moo</L>
<L>Disposed was &thorn;is humble creature</L>
<L N="756">To aduersite of fortune al to endure</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="757">&para; Abideinge euer his lust and his plesaunce</L>
<L>To wham sche was &yogh;euen hert and al</L>
<L>As to hir werldly verray suffisance</L>
<L N="760">Bot schortly &yogh;if &thorn;is storie tell .I. schal</L>
<L>This Marqwys writen ha&thorn;e in special</L>
<L>A lettre in whiche he schewe&thorn; his entent</L>
<L N="763">And secretely he to Boleigne it sent</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="764">&para; To &thorn;e erle of pauyke whiche &thorn;at hadde &thorn;o</L>
<L>Wedded his suster prayede he specialy</L>
<L>To bringe home a&yogh;eine his childerne two</L>
<L N="767">Bot he o &thorn;inge praide vtterly<MILESTONE N="123b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Wi&thorn; all his hert ful affectuously</L>
<L>&THORN;at he to no wight &thorn;ouh man wolde enquere</L>
<L N="770">Schol nouht tellen whos childen &thorn;at &thorn;ei were</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="771">&para; Bot seie &thorn;e maiden schold y-wedde be</L>
<L>Vn-to &thorn;e Markes of Salucez riht anone</L>
<L>And as &thorn;is Erle was preide riht so dide</L>
<L N="774">For att &thorn;e daie sette . he on his waie is gone</L>
<L>To-wardes Salutz and lordes many one</L>
<L>In riche Araie &thorn;is Mayden for to Gyde</L>
<L N="777">Hir &yogh;onge bro&thorn;er rideynge be hire side
<PB REF="00000334.tif" N="307"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="428"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="778">&para; Araide was to-warde hir mariage</L>
<L>This frische maide ful of gemmes clere</L>
<L>Hire bro&thorn;er whiche &thorn;at seuen &yogh;ere was of age</L>
<L N="781">Araide eke ful frische in his manere</L>
<L>And &thorn;us in grete noblesse and wi&thorn; gladde chiere</L>
<L>To-ward Saluces schapinge hire Iornaie</L>
<L N="784">Fro daie to daie &thorn;ei rideinge in hire weie.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>[Explicit] Quarta pars fabule</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="5" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART V.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="785">Amonge al &thorn;is after his wikked vsage</L>
<L>&THORN;is Markes &yogh;it his wif gan tempte more</L>
<L>To &thorn;e vttrest preue of hir Corage</L>
<L N="788">Fulli to haue experiment and lore.</L>
<L>If &thorn;at sche was as stedfast as before</L>
<L>He on a daie in open audience</L>
<L N="791">Ful bustusly ha&thorn; seide hir &thorn;is sentence</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="792">&para; Certes Crisilde .I. had .I.-nowhe plesance</L>
<L>To haue &yogh;owe to my wif for &yogh;oure goodnesse</L>
<L>As for &yogh;oure trou&thorn;e and &yogh;oure obeissance</L>
<L N="795">Not for &yogh;oure lignage ne for &yogh;oure rechesse</L>
<L>Bot nowe quod he in verreie so &thorn;efastnesse</L>
<L>That in grete lordeschippe &yogh;if .I. wil a-vise</L>
<L N="798">There is grete seruitute in sundre wise</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="799">&para; .I. maie not do as euery plouhe man may</L>
<L>My peple me constreyne&thorn; forto take</L>
<L>Ano&thorn;er wif and crien daie be daie</L>
<L N="802">And eke &thorn;e pope rankoure for to slake</L>
<L>Consente&thorn; it &thorn;at dare .I. vnder-tak</L>
<L>And trewlye &thorn;us muche .I. wil &yogh;owe seie</L>
<L N="805">My newe wif is cominge be &thorn;e weie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="806">&para; Be stronge of herte and voide anone hir place</L>
<L>And &thorn;ilke dowaire &thorn;at &yogh;e brouhten me</L>
<L>Tak it a&yogh;eine .I. graunte it of my grace<MILESTONE N="124a" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000335.tif" N="308"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="429"></L>
<L N="809">Retorne&thorn; to &yogh;oure faders house quod he</L>
<L>No man maye alweie haue prosp[er]ite</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; euen hert .I. rede &yogh;oue to endure</L>
<L N="812">The stroke of fortune or of aventure</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="813">&para; And sche a&yogh;eine ansewarde in pacience</L>
<L>My lorde seide sche .I. wote and wist al weie</L>
<L>How &thorn;at be-twex &yogh;oure magnificence</L>
<L N="816">And my pouerte no whight can ne maie</L>
<L>Maken comparison &thorn;at is no naye</L>
<L>.I. held me neuer digne in no manere</L>
<L N="819">To be &yogh;oure wif ne &yogh;it &yogh;oure chamberere</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="820">&para; And in &thorn;is &thorn;ere &yogh;e me lady maade</L>
<L>The hihe god take .I. for my wittenesse</L>
<L>And also wisely he my soule gladde</L>
<L N="823">.I. neuer helde me lady ne maistresse</L>
<L>Bot humble seruant to &yogh;oure wor&thorn;inesse</L>
<L>And euer schal while &thorn;at my lif maie dure</L>
<L N="826">Abouen euery worldly creature</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="827">&para; That &yogh;e so longe of &yogh;oure benignite</L>
<L>Haue holde me in honour and nobleie</L>
<L>Where as .I. was nouht wor&thorn;e to be</L>
<L N="830">&thorn;at &thorn;onke .I. god and &yogh;owe whome .I. preie</L>
<L>For-&yogh;elde it &yogh;ow &thorn;ere is no more to seye</L>
<L>Vnto my fader gladly wil .I. wende</L>
<L N="833">And wi&thorn; him duel vnto my lyues ende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="834">&para; Ther .I. was fostred a childe ful small</L>
<L>Til .I. be dede my lif &thorn;er wil .I. lede</L>
<L>A wedowe clen in body hert and all</L>
<L N="837">For se&thorn;&thorn;e .I. &yogh;aue to &yogh;owe my maidenhede</L>
<L>And am &yogh;oure trewe wif it is no drede</L>
<L>God schelde suche a lordes wif to take</L>
<L N="840">Ano&thorn;er man to husbonde or to make
<PB REF="00000336.tif" N="309"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="430"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="841">&para; And of &yogh;owre newe wif god of his grace</L>
<L>So graunt &yogh;owe wele and hihe profperite</L>
<L>For .I. wil gladly &yogh;elden hire my place</L>
<L N="844">In whiche .I. was blisful wonte to be</L>
<L>For se&thorn;e it like&thorn; &yogh;owe my lorde quod sche</L>
<L>That whilom were al myn hertes rest</L>
<L N="847">That .I. schal go .I. wil go whan &yogh;oue lest</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="848">&para; Bot &thorn;ere as &yogh;e me profer suche dowaire</L>
<L>As .I. fist brouht it is wele in my mynde</L>
<L>It were my wreched clo&thorn;es no&thorn;inge faire<MILESTONE N="124b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="851">The whiche to me were nowe ful hard to finde</L>
<L>O goode god howe gentil and howe kinde</L>
<L>&YOGH;e Semed be &yogh;oure speche and be &yogh;oure visage</L>
<L N="854">The daie &thorn;at maked was oure mariage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="855">&para; Bott so&thorn;e is seide al gate .I. finde it trewe</L>
<L>For in effecte it proued is on me</L>
<L>Loue is nouht olde as whan &thorn;at it is newe</L>
<L N="858">Bot certes lorde for none aduersite</L>
<L>To deien in &thorn;e caas it schal nouht be</L>
<L>&THORN;at euer in worde or werke .I. schal repent</L>
<L N="861">&THORN;at .I. &yogh;owe &yogh;afe myne herte in hole entent</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="862">&para; Lorde &yogh;e wote &thorn;at in my faders place</L>
<L>&YOGH;e dide me stripe out of my poure wede</L>
<L>And richely me cladden of &yogh;oure grace</L>
<L N="865">To &yogh;owe brouht .I. not elles out of drede</L>
<L>Bot fei&thorn;e and nakednes and maidenhede</L>
<L>And here a&yogh;eine &yogh;oure clo&thorn;inge .I. restore</L>
<L N="868">And eke &yogh;owre weddinge ringe for euer more</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="869">&para; &THORN;e remenant of &yogh;oure Iewels redi be</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;&thorn;e in &yogh;oure chambre dar .I. sauely seine</L>
<L>Naked oute of my faders house quod sche</L>
<L N="872">.I. cam and naked .y. mote a&yogh;eine
<PB REF="00000337.tif" N="310"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="431"></L>
<L>Al &yogh;oure plesance wold .I. folow feine</L>
<L>Bot &yogh;it .I. hope it be nouht &yogh;oure entent</L>
<L N="875">&thorn;at smokles oute of &yogh;oure paleys .I. went</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="876">&para; &YOGH;e cou&thorn;e nouht do so dishonest a &thorn;inge</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ilke wombe in whiche &yogh;oure childern leye</L>
<L>Scholde be-for &thorn;e peple in my walkinge</L>
<L N="879">Be seene al bare whe[r] for .I. &yogh;owe praye</L>
<L>Late me nouht like a werme go be &thorn;e waie</L>
<L>Remembre &yogh;owe myn owen lorde so dere</L>
<L N="882">.I. was &yogh;owre wif &thorn;ouhe .I. vnwor&thorn;e were</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="883">&para; Wherefore in guerdon of myn maidenhede</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at .I. brouht and not awaie .I. bere</L>
<L>As vowche&thorn; saue to &yogh;eue to my mede</L>
<L N="886">Bot suche a smok as .I. was wonte to were.</L>
<L>&thorn;at .I. &thorn;er-wi&thorn; maie wrie &thorn;e wombe of here</L>
<L>&thorn;at was &yogh;oure wif. and here take .I. my leue</L>
<L N="889">Of &yogh;owe myne owen lorde leste .I. &yogh;owe greue</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="890">&para; The smokke quod he &thorn;at &thorn;ou haste vpon &thorn;i bakke</L>
<L>Lat it still and bere it for&thorn;e wi&thorn; &thorn;e</L>
<L>Bot vnne&thorn; &thorn;ilke worde he spake<MILESTONE N="125a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="893">Bott wente his weie for rew&thorn;e and pite</L>
<L>Be-forne &thorn;e folke hir seluen strepe&thorn; sche</L>
<L>And in hire smoke wi&thorn; foote and hede al bare</L>
<L N="896">To-ward hir fader house sche is fare</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="897">&para; The folke hire folowen wepein in hir weie</L>
<L>And fortune aie &thorn;ei cursen as &thorn;ei gone</L>
<L>Bot sche fro wepeinge kepped her ey&yogh;en drie</L>
<L N="900">Ne in &thorn;is time worde ne spak sche none</L>
<L>Hire fader &thorn;at &thorn;is ti&thorn;inge herd a-none</L>
<L>Cursi&thorn; &thorn;e daie and time &thorn;at nature</L>
<L N="903">Schope him to be a lyues creature
<PB REF="00000338.tif" N="311"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="432"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="904">&para; ffor oute of doute &thorn;is olde poure man</L>
<L>&THORN;at whan &thorn;e lorde had fulfilde his corage</L>
<L>For euer it demed si&thorn;&thorn;e it first began</L>
<L N="907">Him wold &thorn;inge it were disparage</L>
<L>To wedde one of so pouere a lignage</L>
<L>To his astate so lowe to a lyht</L>
<L N="910">And voide hir as sone as euer he myht</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="911">&para; A&yogh;eine his douhter hastely go&thorn;e he</L>
<L>For he be noyse of folke knewe hire comeinge</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; hire olde cote as it miht be</L>
<L N="914">He couerde hir ful sorwfully wepinge</L>
<L>Bot on hir bodi myht he it nouht bringe</L>
<L>For rude was &thorn;e clo&thorn;e and more of age</L>
<L N="917">Be fele daies &thorn;an was hire Mariage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="918">&para; Thus wi&thorn; hire fader for a certeine space</L>
<L>Dwelle&thorn; &thorn;is floure of wifly pacience</L>
<L>That ney&thorn;e[r] be hir wordes ne be hir face</L>
<L N="921">Be-forne &thorn;e folke ne eke in hir absence.</L>
<L>Ne schewede sche &thorn;at hir was done offence</L>
<L>Ne of hire hihe astate in remembrance</L>
<L N="924">Ne hadde sche as be hir countenance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="925">&para; No wondere is for in hire grete astate</L>
<L>Hire goste was euer in pleine humilite</L>
<L>No tendre mou&thorn;e none herte delicate</L>
<L N="928">Ne pompe ne semblant of roialte</L>
<L>Bot ful of pacience and benignite</L>
<L>Discrete and prideles ay honurable</L>
<L N="931">And to hir husbond euere meke and stable</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="932">&para; Men speken of Iob and most of his humblesse</L>
<L>As clerkes whan hem liste can endite</L>
<L>Namely of men bot as in sothefastnesse<MILESTONE N="125b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="935">Thow clerkes preisen wemmen bo[t] a lite
<PB REF="00000339.tif" N="312"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="433"></L>
<L>Ther can no man in humblesse him acquite</L>
<L>As wemmen can ne can be halfe so trewe</L>
<L N="938">As wemmen buen bot it be fal of newe</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="6" TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[PART VI.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="939">&para; Fro Boleyne is &thorn;is erle of pauyhe comme</L>
<L>Of whiche &thorn;e fame vp spronge to more and lesse</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e peple eres al and somme</L>
<L N="942">Was Cou&thorn;e eke &thorn;at a new Marquysesse</L>
<L>He wi&thorn; him brouht in suche pompe and recchesse</L>
<L>&THORN;at neuer was &thorn;er seen wi&thorn; mannes eye</L>
<L N="945">So noble araie in al west lumbardeye</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="946">&para; Ther Markes whiche &thorn;at knewe and schope al &thorn;is</L>
<L>Or &thorn;at &thorn;is Erle was comme sent his message</L>
<L>For &thorn;ilke cely poure Crisild</L>
<L N="949">And sche wi&thorn; humble herte and glad visage</L>
<L>Nouhte wi&thorn;&thorn;e no swollen hert in hire Corage</L>
<L>Cam att hire heste and on hir knes hir sette</L>
<L N="952">And reuerently and wisly sche him grette</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="953">&para; Crisilda quod he my wil is vtterlye</L>
<L>This maiden &thorn;at schal be wedded to me</L>
<L>Receyved be morwe as Roiallye</L>
<L N="956">As possible is in my house to be</L>
<L>And eke &thorn;at euery wyght in his degre</L>
<L>Haue his astate in sittinge and seruice</L>
<L N="959">And hihe plesance as .I. can best deuise</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="960">&para; .I. haue no womman suffisant certeine</L>
<L>The chambres for to arraie in ordinance</L>
<L>After my lust; and &thorn;ere-fore wolde .I. feine</L>
<L N="963">&THORN;ine were al suche maner gouernance</L>
<L>&THORN;ou knowest eke of olde al my plesance</L>
<L>&THORN;ouhe &thorn;ine araie be bad and yuel be-seye</L>
<L N="966">Do &thorn;ou &thorn;i deuere att &thorn;e leste waie
<PB REF="00000340.tif" N="313"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="434"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="967">&para; Not only lorde &thorn;at .I. am gladde quod sche</L>
<L>To do &yogh;oure lust bot .I. desire also</L>
<L>&YOGH;owe for to serue and plese in my degre</L>
<L N="970">Wi&thorn;-outen feynteinge and schal euer moo</L>
<L>Ne neuer for no wele ne for woo</L>
<L>Ne schal &thorn;e goste wi&thorn;-inne myne hert stinte</L>
<L N="973">To loue &yogh;ow best wi&thorn; al my trewe entente</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="974">&para; And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde sche gan &thorn;e house to diht</L>
<L>And tables for to sette <I>aud</I> beddes make</L>
<L>And peyned hire to done al &thorn;at sche myht<MILESTONE N="126a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="977">Preieinge &thorn;e chambreres for goddes sake</L>
<L>To hasten hem and fast swepe and shake</L>
<L>And sche &thorn;e most seruisiable of all</L>
<L N="980">Ha&thorn;e euery chambre arraide and his hall</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="981">&para; Aboute vndern gan &thorn;is erle alyht</L>
<L>And wy&thorn; him brouht his noble childern tweye</L>
<L>For-wi&thorn; &thorn;e peple ran to see &thorn;at siht</L>
<L N="984">Of hir arraye so Richely beseye</L>
<L>and &thorn;an at arst amonges hem &thorn;ei sey</L>
<L>&thorn;at Walter was no fule &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at him leste</L>
<L N="987">To chaunge his wif for it was for &thorn;e beste</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="988">&para; For sche is fairere as &thorn;ei demen alle</L>
<L>&THORN;an is Crisilde and more tendir of age</L>
<L>And feirer fruyte betwene hem schold fall</L>
<L N="991">And more plesance for hir hihe lignage</L>
<L>Hir bro&thorn;er eke so faire was of visage</L>
<L>That hem to se &thorn;e peple ha&thorn; kauht plesance</L>
<L N="994">Commendynge nowe &thorn;e Markes gouernance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="995">&para; O stormy peple vnsad and euer vntrewe</L>
<L>Ay indiscrete and chaungeinge as a fane</L>
<L>Deliteinge aye in Romble &thorn;at is newe</L>
<L N="998">Fare like &thorn;e mone ay wexen &yogh;e and wane
<PB REF="00000341.tif" N="314"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="435"></L>
<L>Ay ful of Clappinge dere ynowhe a Iane</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure dome as fals &yogh;oure inconstance wele preue&thorn;</L>
<L N="1001">A for grete fole is he &thorn;at on &yogh;owe leue&thorn;</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1002">&para; Thus seiden sadde folke in &thorn;at Cite</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at &thorn;e peple gased vp and doune</L>
<L>For &thorn;ei were glad riht for &thorn;e nouelte</L>
<L N="1005">To haue a newe lady of here toune</L>
<L>No more of &thorn;is now make .I. mencione</L>
<L>Bot to Crisilde anone .I. wil me dresse</L>
<L N="1008">And tel hir Constance and hir besinesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1009">&para; Ful besy was crisilde in euery &thorn;inge</L>
<L>&THORN;at to &thorn;e feste was apertenent</L>
<L>Riht nouht was sche abassched of hire clo&thorn;inge</L>
<L N="1012">&thorn;ouhe it were rode and eke somdele to-rente</L>
<L>Bot wi&thorn; glad chiere to &thorn;e &yogh;ate is wente</L>
<L>Wy&thorn; o&thorn;ere folke to grete &thorn;e marquysesse</L>
<L N="1015">And after &thorn;at do&thorn; for&thorn;e hire besinesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1016">&para; Wi&thorn; so gladde chiere his gestes sche resceyue&thorn;</L>
<L>And conyngly eueryche in his degre</L>
<L>&THORN;at defaute no man apperceyue&thorn;</L>
<L N="1019">Bot aie &thorn;ei wondren what sche myht be<MILESTONE N="126b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>That in so pouer araye was for to se</L>
<L>And cou&thorn;e suche honoure and reuerence</L>
<L N="1022">And wor&thorn;ely &thorn;e preised hire prudence</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1023">&para; In al &thorn;is men while sche ne stinte</L>
<L>This maiden and eke hir bro&thorn;er to commende</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; al hir hert wi&thorn; ful benynge entente</L>
<L N="1026">So wele &thorn;at no man cou&thorn;e hir prise amende</L>
<L>Bot att &thorn;e laste whan &thorn;es lordes wende</L>
<L>To sitten doune att mete he gan to call</L>
<L N="1029">Crisilde as sche was busy in his hall
<PB REF="00000342.tif" N="315"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="436"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1030">&para; Crisild quod he as it were in his pleie</L>
<L>Howe like&thorn; &thorn;e my wif and hire beaute</L>
<L>Riht wele quod sche my lorde for in goode feie</L>
<L N="1033">A feirer sawhe .I. neuer none &thorn;an sche</L>
<L>.I. prei to god &yogh;if. &yogh;oue prosperite</L>
<L>And so hope .I. &thorn;at he wil to &yogh;oue sende</L>
<L N="1036">Plesance ynowhe vnto &yogh;oure liues ende</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1037">&para; .O. &thorn;inge beseche .I. &yogh;owe and warne also</L>
<L>&THORN;at &yogh;e prikke wi&thorn; no turnementynge</L>
<L>&THORN;is tender maiden as &yogh;e haue done mo</L>
<L N="1040">For sche is fosterd in hir norischeinge</L>
<L>More tendrely and to my supposinge</L>
<L>Sche cou&thorn;e nouht aduersite endure</L>
<L N="1043">As cou&thorn;e a pore fostred creature</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1044">&para; And whan &thorn;is Waltier sauhe hire pacience</L>
<L>Hir glad chiere and no malece att al</L>
<L>And he so oft had done hire offence</L>
<L N="1047">And sche aye sadde and constante as a wal</L>
<L>Continuinge euer hire Innocens ouer al</L>
<L>This stordy Markes gan his hert dresse</L>
<L N="1050">To rewen on hire wifly stedfastnesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1051">&para; This is ynouhe Crisilde myne quod he</L>
<L>Be nowe no more agaste ne yuel a-paide</L>
<L>.I. haue &thorn;i fei&thorn;e and &thorn;i benignite</L>
<L N="1054">As wele as euer womman was assaide</L>
<L>In grete astate and pouerly araide</L>
<L>Now knowe .I. dere wife &thorn;i stedfastnesse</L>
<L N="1057">And hire in armes toke and gan hir kesse</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1058">&para; And sche for wonder toke of it no kepe</L>
<L>Sche &thorn;ouht nouht what &thorn;inge he to hir seide</L>
<L>Sche ferde as sche had stert oute of hir slepe<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Line repeated at top of leaf</I> 127</NOTE></L>
<L N="1061">Til sche oute of hir masedenesse abraide<MILESTONE N="127a" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000343.tif" N="316"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="437"></L>
<L>Crisida quod he be god &thorn;at for vs deide</L>
<L>Thou ert my wif ne none o&thorn;er .I. haue</L>
<L N="1064">Ne neuer had so god my soule saue</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1065">&para; This is &thorn;i douhter whiche &thorn;ou hast supposed</L>
<L>To be my wif &thorn;at to&thorn;er fai&thorn;e fully</L>
<L>Schal be myne heire as .I. haue aye purposed</L>
<L N="1068">Thou bare hem in &thorn;i bodi trewly.</L>
<L>Att Boleyne haue .I. kepped hem priuely</L>
<L>Take&thorn; hem a&yogh;eine for nowe maist &thorn;ou nou&yogh;t sey</L>
<L N="1071">&THORN;at &thorn;ou hast lorne none of &thorn;i children tweie</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1072">&para; And folke &thorn;at o&thorn;ere wise haue seide of me</L>
<L>.I. warne hem wele &thorn;at .I. haue done &thorn;is dede</L>
<L>For no malece ne for no cruelte</L>
<L N="1075">Bot for to assaie in &thorn;e &thorn;i wommanhede</L>
<L>And nouht for to sle my childern god for-bede</L>
<L>Bot for to kepe hem priuely and still</L>
<L N="1078">Til .I. &thorn;i purpos knewe and al &thorn;i will</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1079">&para; Whan sche &thorn;is herde a swoune doune sche falle&thorn;</L>
<L>For pitous Ioye and after hire swoneinge</L>
<L>Sche bo&thorn;e hir &yogh;onge childerne to hire calle&thorn;</L>
<L N="1082">And in hir armes pytously wepeinge</L>
<L>Embrase&thorn; hem and tendurly kissinge</L>
<L>Ful lyk a mode wi&thorn;&thorn;e hir salte teres</L>
<L N="1085">Sche ba&thorn;es bo&thorn; hire vesage and hire eres</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1086">&para; O whiche a pitous syht it was to see</L>
<L>Hir swoneynge and hire humble voice to here</L>
<L>Graunt mercye lord god .I. &thorn;onked &yogh;owe quod sche</L>
<L N="1089">&thorn;at &yogh;e haue sauede me my childern dere</L>
<L>Nowe reche .I. neuere to be dede riht here</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;e .I. stonde in &yogh;oure loue and in &yogh;oure grace</L>
<L N="1092">No force of de&thorn;e ne whan my sprite passe
<PB REF="00000344.tif" N="317"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="438"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1093">&para; O tender o dere o &yogh;onge childern myne</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure woful modere wende stedfastly</L>
<L>&THORN;at cruel houndes or sum foule vermyne</L>
<L N="1096">Had eten &yogh;owe bot god of his mercye</L>
<L>And &yogh;oure benigne fader tendurly</L>
<L>Ha&thorn;e done &yogh;owe kepe in &thorn;e same stounde</L>
<L N="1099">Al sodanly sche swapped a-downe to grounde</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1100">And in hir swoune so sadly halde&thorn; sche</L>
<L>Here childern tuo whan sche gan hem enbrace</L>
<L>That wi&thorn; grete slyht and grete difficulte<MILESTONE N="127b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1103">The childerne from hir harme &thorn;ei gun race</L>
<L>O many a tere on mony a pitous face</L>
<L>Doune ranne on hem &thorn;at stoden hir be side</L>
<L N="1106">Vnne&thorn; aboute hir myhten &thorn;ei a-bide</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1107">&para; Walter hire glade&thorn; and hire sorwe slake&thorn;</L>
<L>Sche rise&thorn; vp a-basched from hir traunce</L>
<L>And euery wyht hire ioye&thorn; and fest make&thorn;</L>
<L N="1110">Til sche ha&thorn;e cauht a&yogh;eine her countenance</L>
<L>Waltier hir do&thorn;e fei&thorn;efully plesance</L>
<L>&THORN;at it is deynte&thorn; for to see &thorn;e chiere</L>
<L N="1113">Be-twexe hem tuo nowe &thorn;ei bue mette in fere</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1114">&para; This ladyse whan &thorn;at &thorn;ei her time seie</L>
<L>Han taken hire and in to chambre gone</L>
<L>And strippen hir oute of hir rode araie</L>
<L N="1117">And in a clo&thorn;e of golde &thorn;at briht schone</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; a corenal and mony a riche stone</L>
<L>Vpon hir hede &thorn;ei in-to hal hir brouhte</L>
<L N="1120">And &thorn;an sche was honoured as sche ouhte</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1121">&para; Thus ha&thorn;e &thorn;is pytous daie a blisful ende</L>
<L>For euery man and womman do&thorn;e her myht</L>
<L>This daie in mer&thorn;e and reuel to despende</L>
<L N="1124">Til on &thorn;e welkine schone &thorn;e sterres briht
<PB REF="00000345.tif" N="318"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="439"></L>
<L>For more solempne in euery mannes siht</L>
<L>This feste was and gretter of costage</L>
<L N="1127">Than was &thorn;e reuel of hir Mariage</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1128">&para; Ful mony a &yogh;ere in hihe prosperite</L>
<L>Leuen &thorn;is tuo in concorde and rest</L>
<L>And richely his douhter maried he</L>
<L N="1131">Vn-to a lorde one of &thorn;e wor&thorn;iest</L>
<L>Of all ytaile &thorn;an. and pees and rest</L>
<L>His wives fader in his courte he kepe&thorn;</L>
<L N="1134">Til &thorn;at his soule oute of his body crepe&thorn;</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1135">&para; His sonne succede&thorn; in his heritage</L>
<L>In reste and pes after his fader daie</L>
<L>And fortunate eke was in mariage</L>
<L N="1138">Al pute he nouht his wif in grete assaie</L>
<L>&thorn;is werlde is not so stronge it is no naye</L>
<L>As it ha&thorn;e bue in olde time &yogh;ore</L>
<L N="1141">And erkene&thorn; what &thorn;is auctor sei&thorn; &thorn;ere-fore</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1142">&para; This storie is seide not for &thorn;at wyues scholde</L>
<L>Folowen Crisilde as in humilite</L>
<L>For it were importable &thorn;ouhe &thorn;ei wolde<MILESTONE N="128a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="1145">Bot for &thorn;at euery whight in his degre</L>
<L>Scholde be constant in aduersite</L>
<L>As was Crisilda &thorn;er-for Petrake wryte&thorn;</L>
<L N="1148">This story whiche he wi&thorn; hihe stile endite&thorn;</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1149">&para; For se&thorn;&thorn;e a womman was so paciente</L>
<L>Vnto a mortel man wele more vs ouht</L>
<L>Receyuen al in gre &thorn;at god vs sente</L>
<L N="1152">For grete skylles he proue&thorn; &thorn;at he wrouht</L>
<L>Bot he tempte&thorn; no man &thorn;at he bouht</L>
<L>As sei&thorn;e seinte Iame if &yogh;e his pistel rede</L>
<L N="1155">He proue&thorn; folke aldaie it is no drede
<PB REF="00000346.tif" N="319"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="440"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1156">&para; And suffre&thorn; vs as for oure exercise</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; scharpe scourges of aduersite</L>
<L>Ful often to be beten in sundry wise</L>
<L N="1159">Nou&yogh;t for to knowe oure wil for certes he</L>
<L>Or we ware borne knewe al oure frelete</L>
<L>And for oure best is al his gouernance</L>
<L N="1162">Lete vs &thorn;an leue in vertuous suffrance</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1163">&para; Bot lordinges o worde herkene&thorn; ar .I. go</L>
<L>It ware ful harde to finde nowe a dayes</L>
<L>In al a toune Crisildes one or tuo</L>
<L N="1166">For if &thorn;at &thorn;ei were put to suche assaies</L>
<L>The golde of hem ha&thorn;e nowe so bad laies</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; bras &thorn;at &thorn;ouhe &thorn;e coyne be faire at eye</L>
<L N="1169">It wolde ra&thorn;er briste y tuo &thorn;an plye</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1170">&para; For whiche: for &thorn;e wyues loue of ba&thorn;e</L>
<L>Whas lyf and al here hel&thorn;e god maynteigne</L>
<L>In hire maystre and elles ware it ska&thorn;e</L>
<L N="1173">.I. wolde wi&thorn; lusty herte frische and grene</L>
<L>Sey &yogh;owe a songe to glad &yogh;owe .I. wene</L>
<L>And latte us stint of enestful matiere</L>
<L N="1176">Herkene&thorn; my songe &thorn;at sei&thorn;e in &thorn;is manere</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>Lenvoye de Chaucer</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Criselde is dede and hir pacience</L>
<L>And bo&thorn;e at ones beried in ytaile</L>
<L N="1179">Wher-fore .I. crie in open audience</L>
<L>No wedded man be hardie to assaile</L>
<L>His wives pacience in hope to finde</L>
<L N="1182">Crisildez for certes he schal faile
<PB REF="00000347.tif" N="320"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="441"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>O noble wyues ful of ire prudence</L>
<L>Lat none humylite &yogh;oure tonge naile</L>
<L N="1185">Ne late no clerke haue cause or diligence<MILESTONE N="128b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To write of &yogh;owe a storie of suche merveile</L>
<L>As Crisilde pacient and kinde</L>
<L N="1188">Lest chicheuache &yogh;owe swelowe in hire entreile</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Folowe&thorn; here to and holde&thorn; no silence</L>
<L>Bot euer answer att &thorn;e countretaile</L>
<L N="1191">Be&thorn; nouht bedaffed for &yogh;oure innocence</L>
<L>Bot scharpely take on &yogh;owe &thorn;e gouernaile</L>
<L>Enprinte&thorn; wele &thorn;is lesson in &yogh;oure mynde</L>
<L N="1194">For commune profite se&thorn;&thorn;e it maie availe</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&thorn;e Archewyues stande&thorn; att &thorn;e fense</L>
<L>Se&thorn; &yogh;e be stronge as is a grete Camaile</L>
<L N="1197">Ne suffre&thorn; nou&yogh;t &thorn;at men do &yogh;owe offence</L>
<L>And sclender wives and febel as in a bataile</L>
<L>Be&thorn; egre as is a tigre &yogh;onde in. Inde</L>
<L N="1200">Ay clappe&thorn; as a melle .I. &yogh;owe counseile</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne drede hem nouht . ne do hem no reuerence</L>
<L>For &thorn;ouhe &thorn;i husbonde armed be in maile</L>
<L N="1203">&THORN;e arwes of &thorn;i crabbed eloquence</L>
<L>Schal pers his breste and eke his aduentaile</L>
<L>In gelowsye .I. rede eke &thorn;ou him binde</L>
<L N="1206">And &thorn;ou make him couche as do&thorn;e a qwaile</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>If &thorn;ow bue faire &thorn;ere folke bue in presence</L>
<L>schew &thorn;ou &thorn;i visage and &thorn;ine aparaile</L>
<L N="1209">If &thorn;o be foule be fre of &thorn;i dispence</L>
<L>To gete &thorn;e frendes do aye &thorn;i trauayle</L>
<L>Be ay of chier as liht as lef on lynde</L>
<L N="1212">And late him care and wepe and wringe and wayle.</L>
</LG>
</DIV3>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit</B> commendacio</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000348.tif" N="321">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="443">
<HEAD>Incipit ffabula.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 128, <I>back</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>WHilome &thorn;er was dwellinge in lumbardie</L>
<L>A wor&thorn;i knyht &thorn;at borne was in Paue</L>
<L>In whiche he leued in grete prosperite</L>
<L N="1248">And .xl. &yogh;ere a wifles man was he</L>
<L>And folowde aye his bodely delite</L>
<L>On wemmen was his hole appetite</L>
<L>As done &thorn;es foles &thorn;at bu seculere</L>
<L N="1252">And whan &thorn;at he was passed .lx. &yogh;ere</L>
<L>Were it for holynes or for dotage</L>
<L>.I. can nouht seie but suche a grete corage</L>
<L>Had &thorn;is knyht to be a wedded man</L>
<L><SUP>1</SUP>&THORN;at daie and nyht he do&thorn; al &thorn;at he can</L>
<L>To aspie where he myht wedded be<SUP>1</SUP><NOTE PLACE="marg"><SUP>1_1</SUP> <I>repeated on leaf</I> 129</NOTE></L>
<L>Preinge oure lorde to grant him &thorn;at he<MILESTONE N="129a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>myht ones knowe &thorn;at blisful life</L>
<L N="1260">&thorn;at is betwex an husbond and his wif</L>
<L>And for to leue vnder &thorn;at holy honde</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; wiche god first man and womman bonde</L>
<L>None o&thorn;er life seide he is wor&thorn;e a bene</L>
<L N="1264">For wedlok is so esy and so clene</L>
<L>That in &thorn;is werlde it is a paradise</L>
<L>Thus seide &thorn;is olde knyht &thorn;at was so wise</L>
<L>An certeinly as so&thorn;e as godde is kenge</L>
<L N="1268">To take a wif it is a gloriouse &thorn;inge</L>
<L>And namely whan a man is olde and hore</L>
<L>&thorn;an is a wif fruyt of his tresore</L>
<L>&thorn;an scholde he take a &yogh;onge wif and a faire</L>
<L N="1272">On whiche he myht engender him an heire
<PB REF="00000349.tif" N="322"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="444"></L>
<L>And leden his lif in Ioy and solace</L>
<L>Where as &thorn;e bachellier singen alace</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at &thorn;ei finden any aduersite</L>
<L N="1276">In loue whiche &thorn;at is bot childes vanite</L>
<L>And trewli it sitte wele to be so</L>
<L>&thorn;at bachilliers haue ofte peine and woo</L>
<L>On brutel grounde &thorn;ei boiled brutilnesse</L>
<L N="1280">&thorn;ei finde frelte whan &thorn;ei wene Sikernesse</L>
<L>&thorn;ei leue bot as a burde or as a beste</L>
<L>In liberte and vnder none areste</L>
<L>&thorn;ere as a wedded man in his astate</L>
<L N="1284">Leue&thorn; . his lyf blisful and ordinate</L>
<L>Vnder &thorn;e &yogh;okke of mariage .ybounde</L>
<L>Wele may his herte In Ioy and blisse abounde</L>
<L>For who can be so buxum as a wife</L>
<L N="1288">Who is so trewe and eke so tentife</L>
<L>To kepe him seeke and hole as is his make</L>
<L>For wele or woo sche nyll nouht him for-sake</L>
<L>Sche is nouht werye him to loue and serue</L>
<L N="1292">&thorn;eih &thorn;at he lye beddred til he sterue</L>
<L>And &yogh;it somme clerkes seine it is nouht so</L>
<L>Of whiche Theofrast is one of &thorn;o</L>
<L>What fors &thorn;ouhe Theofrast list lye</L>
<L N="1296">Ne take no wif quod he for husbandrie</L>
<L>As for to spare in householde &thorn;i despence</L>
<L>A trew seruant do&thorn;e more diligence<MILESTONE N="129b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Thine goode to kepe &thorn;an &thorn;ine owen wif</L>
<L N="1300">For sche wil claime half parte in al hire lif</L>
<L>And &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ou be seke so god me saue</L>
<L>Thyne verrey frendes or a trew knaue</L>
<L>Wil kepe &thorn;e bett &thorn;an sche &thorn;at waite&thorn; aie</L>
<L N="1304">After &thorn;i goode and haue&thorn; do mony daie</L>
<L>[And if thou take a wife that to the is vn-trewe.</L>
<L>ffull ofte tyme it schall the rewe.<MILESTONE UNIT="Harl. 1758 folio" N="77a"><NOTE PLACE="marg"> <I>Not in Addit.</I> 5140, <I>leaf</I> 149</NOTE>]</L>
<L>To &thorn;is entente and an .C. si&thorn;es wers</L>
<L N="1308">Write&thorn; &thorn;is man &thorn;ere god his soule cors
<PB REF="00000350.tif" N="323"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="445"></L>
<L>Bot take no kepe of al such vanite</L>
<L>Defye Theofrast and herkene&thorn; me</L>
<L>&para; A wif is goddes &yogh;ift verraily</L>
<L N="1312">Al o&thorn;er maner &yogh;iftes hardely</L>
<L>As landes rentes pasture or comune</L>
<L>O&thorn;er ey&thorn;er &yogh;iftes &thorn;at bien mebles of fortune</L>
<L>&thorn;at passen as a schadowe on a wal</L>
<L N="1316">Bot drede nouht if pleinly speke I. schal</L>
<L>A wif wil last and in &thorn;ine house endure</L>
<L>Wel langer &thorn;an &thorn;e list endure</L>
<L>Mariage is a ful grete sacrament</L>
<L N="1320">He whiche ha&thorn; no wif .I. holde him schent</L>
<L>He leue&thorn; helples and is al desolate</L>
<L>.I. speke of folke in seculere astate</L>
<L>And herken whi .I. seie nouht &thorn;is for nouht</L>
<L N="1324">&thorn;e womman is for mannes helpe I-wrouht</L>
<L>&thorn;e hihe god whan he had Adam maked</L>
<L>And sauhe him a-lone b[e]ly nakeded</L>
<L>God of his grete goodnesse seide he &thorn;an</L>
<L N="1328">Latt vs nowe make an helpe to &thorn;is man</L>
<L>.I.-like to him selfe and &thorn;at he maade Eue</L>
<L>Here maie &yogh;e see and here be preue</L>
<L>&THORN;at wif is mannes help and comforte</L>
<L N="1332">His paradise terestre and his disporte</L>
<L>So buxum and so vertuus is sche</L>
<L>&thorn;ei moste nedes leue in vnite</L>
<L>O flesche and o blode as .I. gesse</L>
<L N="1336">Ne ha&thorn;e bot on herte in wele and in destresse</L>
<L>A wif a seinte mare benedicite</L>
<L>Howe myhte a man haue any aduersite</L>
<L>&thorn;at ha&thorn; a wif certes .I. can nouht seye</L>
<L N="1340">The blisse &thorn;at is be-tuex hem tueye</L>
<L>&THORN;ere maie no tunge tel or hert &thorn;inke.</L>
<L>If he be pouere Sche helpe&thorn; him to swynke<MILESTONE N="130a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Sche kepe&thorn; his gode and waste&thorn; neuer a dele</L>
<L N="1344">And al &thorn;at hire husbond lust hire lyke&thorn; wele
<PB REF="00000351.tif" N="324"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="446"></L>
<L>Sche sei&thorn; nouht ones naie whan he sei&thorn;e &yogh;e</L>
