<L>&thorn;at in &thorn;e gardine on &thorn;at fer&thorn;ire side</L>
<L>Pluto &thorn;at is &thorn;e kinge of faire</L>
<L N="2228">And mony a ladi in his companye</L>
<L>Folowinge his wif &thorn;e queene Proserpina</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at he rauesched oute of proserpina.</L>
<L>Whiles &thorn;at sche gaderd floures in a mede<MILESTONE N="140b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="2232">In claudian &yogh;e maie &thorn;e storis rede</L>
<L>How in his grisly carte he hire fette</L>
<L>This kinge of ffaire a-doune him sette</L>
<L>Vppon a benche of torues frische and grene</L>
<L N="2236">And riht anone seide he &thorn;us vnto his qwene</L>
<L>My wif quod he &thorn;at maie not seie naie</L>
<L>The experiens proueth it euery daie</L>
<L>The treson whiche &thorn;at womman do&thorn; to man</L>
<L N="2240">Ten hundre&thorn; &thorn;ousand tell .I. can</L>
<L>Notable of &yogh;oure vntreu&thorn;e and brutelnes</L>
<L>Of Salomon rychest of al riches</L>
<L>Ful filled of Sapiens and of werly glorie</L>
<L N="2244">Ful wor&thorn;i bien &thorn;i wordes to memorie
<PB REF="00000376.tif" N="349"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="471"></L>
<L>To euery wiht &thorn;at witte and reson can</L>
<L>&thorn;us preise&thorn; he &yogh;itte &thorn;e bounte of man</L>
<L>Amonge a .M. men &yogh;it fonde .I. one</L>
<L N="2248">Bot of al wemmen fonde .I. neuer none</L>
<L>&thorn;us sei&thorn;e &thorn;e kinge &thorn;at knowe&thorn; &yogh;oure wikkednesse</L>
<L>And ihesus filius Syrak as .I. gesse</L>
<L>Ne speke&thorn; of &yogh;owe but seldyn reuerence</L>
<L N="2252">A wilde fire a corrupt pestilence</L>
<L>So fal vpon &yogh;oure bodies &yogh;it to nyht</L>
<L>Ne see nouht &thorn;is honurable knyht</L>
<L>Because alas &thorn;at he is blinde and olde</L>
<L N="2256">His owen man schal make him cokewolde</L>
<L>Loo where he sitte &thorn;e lichoure in &thorn;e tree</L>
<L>Nowe wil .I. graunte of my Maiestee</L>
<L>Vnto &thorn;is olde blinde wor&thorn;i knyht</L>
<L N="2260">&thorn;at he schal haue a&yogh;eine his ey&yogh;en siht</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at his wif wold done him velanye</L>
<L>Than schal he knowe al her harlotrye</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e in repreue of hire and o&thorn;ere mo</L>
<L N="2264">&YOGH;e schal quod Procerpine and wil &yogh;e soo</L>
<L>Nowe be my Moders sire soule .I. swere</L>
<L>&thorn;at .I. schal &yogh;eue hire sufficeant ansewere</L>
<L>And alle wemmen after for &yogh;oure saake</L>
<L N="2268">&thorn;at &thorn;ouhe &thorn;ei buen in any gilte ytake</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; face bolde &thorn;ei schollen hem self excuse</L>
<L>And bere hem doune &thorn;at wolde hem accuse</L>
<L>For lakke of ansewere non of hem schollen deyen</L>
<L N="2272">Al had &yogh;e seihe a &thorn;inge wi&thorn; bo&thorn; &yogh;oure ey&yogh;en.</L>
<L>&YOGH;it schollon we so visage it hit hardelye<MILESTONE N="141a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And wepe and swere and chide subtellye</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e schol buen as lewde as arne gese</L>
<L N="2276">What rekke&thorn; me of &yogh;oure auctoritees</L>
<L>.I. wote wele &thorn;is Iewe &thorn;is Salomone</L>
<L>Fande of vs wemmen fules many one</L>
<L>Bot &thorn;ouhe &thorn;at he fonde no goode womman</L>
<L N="2280">There ha&thorn;e he founde mony ano&thorn;ere man
<PB REF="00000377.tif" N="350"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="472"></L>
<L>[Wommen ful trew ful good ful vertuous</L>
<L>Witnes on hem &thorn;at dwellen in cristes hous</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; martirdom &thorn;ey prouyd hir<NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS h]</NOTE> constance</L>
<L>The romaygne Iestis maken remembr&amacr;nce</L>
<L>Of many a verry trewe wyff also</L>
<L>But sire ne be nou&yogh;t wroth as be it soo</L>
<L>&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at he seide he fond no good womman</L>
<L N="2228">I praye &yogh;ow take &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e man<MILESTONE UNIT="Reg. 18 C ii folio" N="103b"><NOTE PLACE="marg">[ <I>Not in Harl.</I> 1758, <I>leaf</I> 87; <I>or Harl.</I> 7335, <I>leaf</I> 127; <I>or Sloane</I> 1686, <I>leaf</I> 192, <I>back; but in Addit.</I> 5140, <I>leaf</I> 166, <I>bk;</I> 17 <I>D xv</I>, <I>leaf</I> 121, <I>bk; Sloane</I> 1685, <I>leaf</I> 101; <I>the sheet out of Harl.</I> 7333 (<I>lf</I>72-73).]</NOTE>]</L>
<L>He ment &thorn;us &thorn;at in souereigne bounte</L>
<L>Nys none bot god ney&thorn;ere he ne sche</L>
<L>Ey for verrey god &thorn;at nys bot one</L>
<L N="2292">What make &yogh;e so muche of Salomone</L>
<L>What &thorn;ouhe he maad a temple goddes hous</L>
<L>What &thorn;ouhe he were riche and glorious</L>
<L>So maade he a temple of fals goddes</L>
<L N="2296">Who myht do a &thorn;inge &thorn;at more for-bode is</L>
<L>Parde als faire as &yogh;e his name implastre</L>
<L>He was a lichoure and a ydolastre</L>
<L>And in his elde he verrei god for-soke</L>
<L N="2300">And &yogh;if &thorn;at god na hadde as sei&thorn;e &thorn;e boke</L>
<L>yspared him for his fader saake he scholde</L>
<L>Haue lost his reigne sauner &thorn;at he wolde</L>
<L>.I. sett nouht of al &thorn;e velany</L>
<L N="2304">&thorn;at &yogh;e of wemmen write a botterflie</L>
<L>.I. am a womman nedes most .I. speke</L>
<L>Or elles swel til myn hert breke</L>
<L>For &thorn;e&thorn;ins he seide &thorn;at we be Iangelers</L>
<L N="2308">As euer mote .I. brouke bo&thorn;e my tresses</L>
<L>I schal spare for no curtesie</L>
<L>to spek him harme &thorn;at wolde vs velanye</L>
<L>Dame quod &thorn;is pluto be no longer wro&thorn;e</L>
<L N="2312">.I. &yogh;eue it vp bot se&thorn;en .I. swore myn o&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;at [I] wolde graunt him his siht a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>My worde schal stande &thorn;at warne .I. &thorn;e certeine</L>
<L>.I. am a kinge it sitte me nouht to lye</L>
<L N="2316">And .I. quod sche a queene of fayre
<PB REF="00000378.tif" N="350*"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="473"></L>
<L>Hire ansewar sche schal haue .I. vnder-take</L>
<L N="2318">Lat us no mo wordes nowe make.<NOTE PLACE="end">[<I>For the rest of the Tale (from Harl. MS</I> 1758) <I>see the Appendix.</I>]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit fabula</B> Mercatoris.<LB> (<I>As in Sloane</I> 1686, <I>and Corpus</I>.)</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="F" TYPE="group">


<DIV2 TYPE="tale"><PB REF="00000379.tif" N="351">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="500">
<HEAD>[THE PROEM.]</HEAD>
<HEAD>Incipit prologus de le ffrankeleyne.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 141</NOTE></HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>THis olde gentil bretons in hire daies</L>
<L>Of diuers auentures maden laies</L>
<L>Rimyden in hir first breton tonge</L>
<L N="712">Whiche laies wi&thorn; here instrumentes &thorn;ei songe.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er elles redden hem for her plesance<MILESTONE N="141b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And one of hem haue .I. in rembrance</L>
<L>Whiche .I. schal seie wi&thorn; as goode wil as .I. can</L>
<L N="716">Bot sires be cause &thorn;at .I. am a burel man</L>
<L>Att my ginnynge first .I. &yogh;oue beseche</L>
<L>Heue&thorn; me excused of my roode speche</L>
<L>.I. lernd neuer retorik certeine</L>
<L N="720">&thorn;inge &thorn;at .I. speke it most . be bare and pleine</L>
<L>.I. slept neuer on &thorn;e mount of parnaso</L>
<L>Ne .y. neuere lerid Marcus . Tullius . ne Cithero</L>
<L>Colours of retorike ne knewe .I. none wi&thorn;-outen drede</L>
<L N="724">Bot suche colours as growen in &thorn;e mede</L>
<L>Or elles suche as men dye or peinte</L>
<L>Colours of rethorik bene me to queynte</L>
<L>My sprite fele&thorn; nou&yogh;t of suche Matier</L>
<L N="728">Bot if &thorn;ou luste Mi tale schal .&yogh;e.<NOTE PLACE="marg">[nouht <I>crosst out</I>]</NOTE> here.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit</B> prologus</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD> <B>Incipit fabula.</B></HEAD>
<HEAD>[THE TALE.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="730">Ther was a knyht &thorn;at loued and dide his peyne</L>
<L N="729">In Armorik &thorn;at cleped is bretaigne</L>
<L N="731">To seruen a lady in his best wise</L>
<L>And many a labour and mony a grete emprise
<PB REF="00000380.tif" N="352"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="501"></L>
<L>He for his lady wrouht er sche were wonne</L>
<L>For sche was on of &thorn;e fairest vnder sonne</L>
<L>And eke &thorn;ere-to com of so hihe kinrede</L>
<L N="736">&thorn;at wele vnne&thorn;is dorst &thorn;is knyht for drede</L>
<L>Tel hir his woo his peine and his distresse</L>
<L>Bot att &thorn;e last sche for his wor&thorn;inesse</L>
<L>And namely for his meke obeissance</L>
<L N="740">Ha&thorn; suche a pite cauht of his penance</L>
<L>&thorn;at priue sche fel of his accorde</L>
<L>To take him for hir husbonde and hir lorde</L>
<L>Of suche lor[d]schip as men haue ouer hire wyues</L>
<L N="744">And for to lede &thorn;e more in blisse her lyues</L>
<L>Of his fre wil he swore hire as a knyht</L>
<L>&thorn;at neuer in his wil be daie ne be nyht</L>
<L>Ne scholde he vpon him take no maistre</L>
<L N="748">A&yogh;eines hir wille ne kuythe hure Ielousye</L>
<L>Bot hire obeie and folowe hire wille in al</L>
<L>As any louer to his ladi schal</L>
<L>Saue &thorn;at &thorn;e name of Souereignete</L>
<L N="752">That wolde he haue for schame of his degre</L>
<L>Sche &thorn;onke&thorn; him and wi&thorn; ful grete humblesse</L>
<L>Sche seide sir se&thorn;&thorn;e &yogh;e of &yogh;oure gentilesse<MILESTONE N="142a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&yogh;e profer me to haue als large a reyne</L>
<L N="756">Ne wold neuere god be-twix vs tueyne</L>
<L>As in my gulte ware ey&thorn;er werre or striffe</L>
<L>Sir .I. wil be &yogh;oure owen humble trewe wif</L>
<L>Haue here my trou&thorn;e til &thorn;at myn hert burst</L>
<L N="760">Thus buen &thorn;ei bo&thorn;e in quiete and in ruste</L>
<L>For o &thorn;inge sires saufly dar .I. seie</L>
<L>&thorn;at frendes eueryche o&thorn;ere motte obeie</L>
<L>If &thorn;ei wil longe hold compaigne</L>
<L N="764">Loue wil nouht buen constreyned be maistre</L>
<L>Whan Maistre comme&thorn; god of loue anone</L>
<L>Bete&thorn; on his wenge and fare wele he is gone</L>
<L>Loue is a &thorn;inge as any spirit fre</L>
<L N="768">Wemmene of kinde desiren liberte
<PB REF="00000381.tif" N="353"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="502"></L>
<L>And nouht to be constreined as a &thorn;rall</L>
<L>And so do&thorn; men. if .I. &thorn;e so&thorn;e saie schall</L>
<L>Loke who &thorn;at is most pacient in loue</L>
<L N="772">He is att auantage aboue</L>
<L>Paciens is an hihe vertue certeigne</L>
<L>[ffor it venquyscheth as these clerkis seyne.<MILESTONE UNIT="Harl. 1758 folio" N="128a">]</L>
<L>Thinges &thorn;at Rigor schol neuere atteigne</L>
<L N="776">For euery worde men maie nouht chide ne pleine</L>
<L>Lerene&thorn; to suffur or elles so must .I. gone</L>
<L>&YOGH;e scholne it leren whe&thorn;er so &yogh;e wol or none</L>
<L>For in &thorn;is werlde certeine no wight ne is</L>
<L N="780">&thorn;at he ne do&thorn; or sei&thorn;e sum time of mys</L>
<L>Or ei&thorn;er sekenes or constillacione</L>
<L>Wyn wo or channgeinge of complexione</L>
<L>Cause&thorn; ful often to don amys or speken</L>
<L N="784">On euery wronge men maye nouht bue awreken</L>
<L>After &thorn;e time most be temperance</L>
<L>To euery whiht &thorn;at can no gouernance</L>
<L>And &thorn;erfore ha&thorn;e &thorn;is wor&thorn;e wise knyht</L>
<L N="788">To leue in ese suffrance hir be-hiht</L>
<L>And sche to him ful wiseli gan to swere</L>
<L>&thorn;at neuere scholde be defaute in hire</L>
<L>Here maie men seen an humble wise accorde</L>
<L N="792">Thus ha&thorn; sche take hire seruant and hir lorde</L>
<L>Seruant in loue and lorde in Mariage</L>
<L>&thorn;an was he bo&thorn;e in lordeschipe and seruage</L>
<L>Seruage naye bot in lordeschip a-boue</L>
<L N="796">Se&thorn;en &thorn;at he ha&thorn; bo&thorn;e his ladi and his loue</L>
<L>His lady certes and his wif also<MILESTONE N="142b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>The whiche &thorn;at lowe of loue accorde&thorn; &thorn;arto</L>
<L>And whan he was in &thorn;is prosperite</L>
<L N="800">Home wi&thorn; his wif he go&thorn; to his contre</L>
<L>Nouht ffer fro penmarke &thorn;ar as his dwellinge was</L>
<L>Where as he leues in blisse and in solas</L>
<L>Who cou&thorn;e tell bot he had wedded bue</L>
<L N="804">The . Ioye &thorn;e ese. and &thorn;e prosperite
<PB REF="00000382.tif" N="354"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="503"></L>
<L>That is betwyx an husbonde and his wif</L>
<L>A &yogh;ere and more lasted &thorn;is blisfull liff</L>
<L>Til &thorn;at &thorn;is kniht &thorn;e whiche .I. spak of &thorn;us</L>
<L N="808">&thorn;at of kynred was cleped Arneragus</L>
<L>Schope him to gone and dwelle a &yogh;ere or tweyne</L>
<L>In yngelond &thorn;at cleped eke was Bretayne</L>
<L>To seche in armes worschipe and honoure</L>
<L N="812">For al his luste he sette in suche laboure</L>
<L>And dwelle&thorn;e &thorn;ere &thorn;e boke sei&thorn;e &thorn;us</L>
<L>Nowe wil .I. stint of &thorn;is arnaragus</L>
<L>And speken .I. of Dorigen. his wif</L>
<L N="816">&thorn;at loue&thorn; hire husbond as hire hertes lif</L>
<L>And for his absence wepe&thorn; sche and syke&thorn;</L>
<L>As done &thorn;is noble wives whan hem like&thorn;</L>
<L>Sche morne&thorn; wake waile&thorn; faste&thorn; and pleyne&thorn;</L>
<L N="820">Desire of his presence hir so distreine&thorn;</L>
<L>That al &thorn;is wide werld sche sett att nouht</L>
<L>Hire frendes whiche &thorn;at knewe hir heue &thorn;ouht</L>
<L>Comforted hire in al &thorn;at euer &thorn;ei myht or maie</L>
<L N="824">Thei prechen hire &thorn;ei telen hire nyht and daie</L>
<L>&thorn;at causeles sche sle&thorn;e hir self alas</L>
<L>And euer-.I. comford possible in &thorn;is cas</L>
<L>&thorn;ei done to hire with al here bisinesse</L>
<L N="828">And al for to make hire lete hire heuynesse</L>
<L>Be proces as &yogh;e knowe wele euerychone</L>
<L>Men Maie so longe graue in &thorn;e stone</L>
<L>Til figure &thorn;er-inne printed be</L>
<L N="832">So longe haue &thorn;ei comfort hire &thorn;at sche</L>
<L>Receyuede ha&thorn;e be hope and be resone</L>
<L>&thorn;e emprinteinge of hire constillacione</L>
<L>Thoruhe whiche hire grete sorwe gan eswage</L>
<L N="836">Sche maie not alweie endure suche a rage</L>
<L>And eke Arnargus in al &thorn;is care</L>
<L>Ha&thorn;e sent hir lettres home in al &thorn;is fare.</L>
<L>And &thorn;at he wolde come hastely a&yogh;eine<MILESTONE N="143a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="840">Or elles hadde &thorn;is sorwe hire hert sleyne
<PB REF="00000383.tif" N="355"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="504"></L>
<L>Hire frendes sauhe hire hert gan to slake</L>
<L>And preide hire on knes for goddes sake</L>
<L>To come and to Rome in companye</L>
<L N="844">Awaie to driue hire derke fantasie</L>
<L>And finally sche graunted &thorn;at request</L>
<L>For wele sche sauhe it was for &thorn;e best</L>
<L>Now stode hir castel fast by &thorn;e see</L>
<L N="848">And often wi&thorn; hire frendes walked sche</L>
<L>Hir to disport on &thorn;e se banke on hihe</L>
<L>Where as sche many schippes and barges seihe</L>
<L>Seileinge her course where hem luste to goo</L>
<L N="852">Bot &yogh;ite was &thorn;ere a percel of hir woo</L>
<L>For to hir selue ful often seide sche</L>
<L>Is &thorn;ere no schippe of so mony as .I. see</L>
<L>Wil bringe home my lorde &thorn;an wolde myne herte</L>
<L N="856">Al warisshe of &thorn;is bitter peine smarte</L>
<L>Ano&thorn;ere time &thorn;ere wil sche sitte and &thorn;enke</L>
<L>And kast hir eye donward fro &thorn;e brenke</L>
<L>Bot whan sche sawhe &thorn;e grisely Rokkes blake</L>
<L N="860">For verrei fere so wolde hire heret qwake</L>
<L>&thorn;at one hir feete sche myhte nouht hire susteigne</L>
<L>&thorn;an wolde sche sit adoune vpon &thorn;e grene</L>
<L>And pitously into &thorn;e see sche walde be-holde</L>
<L N="864">And seine riht &thorn;us wi&thorn; sorweful hertes colde</L>
<L>Eterne god &thorn;at &thorn;oruhe &thorn;i purueance</L>
<L>Ledest &thorn;e werlde be certein gouernance</L>
<L>In ydelnes as men seine &yogh;e no&thorn;inge make</L>
<L N="868">Bot lorde &thorn;is griseli fendely Rockes blake</L>
<L>&thorn;at semen ra&thorn;er a foule confusione</L>
<L>Of werke &thorn;at any faire creacione</L>
<L>Of whiche a parfit god and a stable</L>
<L N="872">Whi haue &yogh;e wrouht &thorn;is werk vnresonable</L>
<L>For be &thorn;is werke sou&thorn;e. nor&thorn;e. este and west</L>
<L>&thorn;are nes ifostred man ne birde ne beste</L>
<L>It do&thorn;e no good to my witte bot anoye&thorn;</L>
<L N="876">Sche &yogh;e nouht lor how mankinde it destrue&thorn;.
<PB REF="00000384.tif" N="356"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="505"></L>
<L>An hundre&thorn; &thorn;ousand bodyes of mankinde</L>
<L>Haue rokkes sleine and al be &thorn;ei nouht in mynde</L>
<L>Whiche mankinde is so faire parte of &thorn;i werke</L>
<L N="880">&thorn;at &thorn;ou it madest ylike to &thorn;ine handwerke.</L>
<L>Than semed it &yogh;e hadde a grete chierte<MILESTONE N="143b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To-ward mankynde bot howe &thorn;an maie it be</L>
<L>That &yogh;e suche menys make it to destroyen</L>
<L N="884">Wyche menys do&thorn; no good but euere annoyen</L>
<L>.I. woote wele clerkes woln sayn as hem lest</L>
<L>By argumentz &thorn;at al &thorn;inges is for &thorn;e best</L>
<L>They .I. ne can &thorn;e causes for so&thorn;e knowe</L>
<L N="888">Bot &thorn;ilke god &thorn;at maade winde to blowe</L>
<L>As kepe my lorde &thorn;is conclusion</L>
<L>To clerkis lat .I. al disputasion</L>
<L>Bot wolde god. &thorn;at al &thorn;e Rokkes blake</L>
<L N="892">Ware sonken in-to hel for his sake</L>
<L>&thorn;es rokkes sleen myne hert for fere</L>
