<L N="5">And o&thorn;ere many Iewels dar .I. vnder-take</L>
<L>And &thorn;at &thorn;i lorde cou&thorn;e vs tel: if we myht him ouere-take</L>
<L>Bot lat him go a deuel waye &thorn;e compaigny is neuer &thorn;e wers<MILESTONE N="169b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And al suche fals harlotes .I. sette not be hem a kers</L>
<L N="9">Bot latt pas ouere nowe al &thorn;es subtilitees</L>
<L>And sume wor&thorn;i man tel vs summe veritees</L>
<L>As &yogh;e worschipful Maister of Phisike</L>
<L N="12">Telle&thorn; vs somme tale &thorn;at is a cronyke</L>
<L>&THORN;at we may of &yogh;owe leren sum witte</L>
<L>Quod &thorn;e Maister of Phisik a tale &thorn;at .I. finde writte</L>
<L>In cronyke passed of olde tyme</L>
<L N="16">Herkene&thorn; for .I. wil tel it &yogh;ow in rime</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit prologus.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="C" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000454.tif" N="426">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="303">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>C.</B> FRAGMENT IV.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; <B>1.</B> THE DOCTOR'S TALE.</HEAD>
<HEAD>LANSDOWNE MS.</HEAD>
<HEAD>&para; Incipit fabu[l]a.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 169, <I>back</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ther was as telle&thorn; vs titus liueus</L>
<L>A knyht &thorn;at cleped was virgineus</L>
<L>Fulfilled of honoure &amp; wor&thorn;inesse</L>
<L N="4">And stronge of frendes and of riches</L>
<L>A douhtere he hadd be his wyf</L>
<L>And neuer hadde he mo in al his lif</L>
<L>Faire was &thorn;is maide in excellent beautee</L>
<L N="8">Abouen euery whight &thorn;at maie see</L>
<L>For Nature ha&thorn;e wi&thorn; souereigne diligence</L>
<L>Formed hir in so grete excellence</L>
<L>As &thorn;ouhe sche wolde seie loo .I. Nature</L>
<L N="12">Thus can .I. forme and painte a creature</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at me leste who can me counterfete</L>
<L>Pigmalyon nouht &thorn;ouhe he alweie forge or bete</L>
<L>Or graue or peinte for .I. dar wel seine</L>
<L N="16">Apollus &yogh;epherus schold werche in veine</L>
<L>To graue or peinte or forge or bete</L>
<L>If &thorn;ei presumed me for to counterfete</L>
<L>For he &thorn;at is &thorn;e formour principal</L>
<L N="20">Ha&thorn;e maade me his viser general</L>
<L>To forme and peinte eche er&thorn;ely creature</L>
<L>Riht as me lest for al &thorn;inge is in my cure</L>
<L>Vnder &thorn;e mone &thorn;at maie wane and wax</L>
<L N="24">And for my werke no &thorn;inge wil .I. ax
<PB REF="00000455.tif" N="427"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="304"></L>
<L>My lorde and .I. bene fullye att acorde</L>
<L>.I. maade hire to &thorn;e worschip of my lorde</L>
<L>So do .I. al myn o&thorn;ere creatures</L>
<L N="28">Of [what] colour &thorn;ei bue or what figures</L>
<L>Thus seme&thorn; me &thorn;at Nature wold seie</L>
<L>This maide was of age twelue &yogh;ere and tweye</L>
<L>In whiche &thorn;at Nature ha&thorn;e suche delite</L>
<L N="32">For riht as sche kan peinte as lyle white<MILESTONE N="170a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>An[d] Rode as rose riht wi&thorn; suche peinture</L>
<L>Sche peinted ha&thorn;e &thorn;is noble creature</L>
<L>Ar sche was borne vppon hire limmes fre</L>
<L N="36">Were als briht as suche coloures scholde be</L>
<L>And phebus hadd dyed hire tresses grete</L>
<L>Lyke to &thorn;e stremes of his burned hete</L>
<L>And if &thorn;at excellent was hire beute</L>
<L N="40">A &thorn;ousand folde mor vertuous was sche</L>
<L>In hire ne lakke&thorn; no condicione</L>
<L>&thorn;at is to preise as be discrecione</L>
<L>As wele in body . as goste chast was schee</L>
<L N="44">For whiche sche floured in virginite</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; al humilite and abstinence</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; al attemperance and pacience</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; mesure eke and bereinge of araie</L>
<L N="48">Discrete sche was in ansewaringe alweie</L>
<L>&thorn;ouhe sche were wise as pallas dar .I. seine</L>
<L>Hire faukonde eke ful wommanly and pleyne</L>
<L>None conterfeted termes hadde sche</L>
<L N="52">To seme wise bot after hire degre</L>
<L>Sche spakk and al hir wordes more and lesse</L>
<L>Souneinge in vertue and in gentillesse</L>
<L>Schamefast sche was in maidens schamfastnesse</L>
<L N="56">Constant in hert and euer in his besinesse</L>
<L>To dryue hire oute of hire slogardie</L>
<L>Bachus hadde of hire mou&thorn;e no maistre</L>
<L>For wil and &thorn;ouht to done venus encrese</L>
<L N="60">As men in fire wil kasten oyle or grese
<PB REF="00000456.tif" N="428"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="305"></L>
<L>And of hir owen vertue vnconstreyned</L>
<L>Sche ha&thorn;e ful oft time hire seke feyned</L>
<L>For &thorn;at sche wolde flye &thorn;e companye</L>
<L N="64">Where likly was to treten of folye</L>
<L>As es att festes reueles and att daunces</L>
<L>&thorn;at bene occasione of dalyaunces</L>
<L>Suche &thorn;inges maken childern for to bee</L>
<L N="68">To sone Ripe and bolde as men maie see</L>
<L>Whiche is ful perilous and ha&thorn;e be &yogh;ore</L>
<L>For al to sone maie sche leren lore</L>
<L>Of boldenesse whan sche is a wyfe</L>
<L N="72">And &yogh;e maistresses in &yogh;oure olde life</L>
<L>&thorn;at lordes douhters haue in gouernance</L>
<L>Ne take&thorn; of mi worde no displesance<MILESTONE N="170b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Thinges &thorn;at bien set in gouernynges</L>
<L N="76">Of lordes douhtres only for tuo &thorn;inges</L>
<L>Ey&thorn;er for &yogh;e han kepped &yogh;oure honeste</L>
<L>Or elles &yogh;e haue fall in frelte</L>
<L>And knowe wele ynowhe &thorn;e olde daunce</L>
<L N="80">And konne forsaake fully meschaunce</L>
<L>For euere mo &thorn;er-fore for crist saak</L>
<L>Kepe&thorn; wel &thorn;o &thorn;at &yogh;e vndertak</L>
<L>A &thorn;ef of venison &thorn;at ha&thorn; for-laft</L>
<L N="84">His lycorusnesse and al his &thorn;efes craft</L>
<L>Kan kepe a forest best [of] ony man</L>
<L>Nowe kepe&thorn;e hem wele for &yogh;e wele can</L>
<L>Loke&thorn; wele to no vice &thorn;at &yogh;e assent</L>
<L N="88">Lest [&yogh;e] be dampned for &yogh;oure yuel entent</L>
<L>For who so do&thorn;e a traitour is certeine</L>
<L>And take&thorn; of &thorn;at &thorn;at .I. schal seine</L>
<L>Of al treson suffreine pestelence</L>
<L N="92">Is whan a whight be-traye&thorn; Innocence</L>
<L>&YOGH;e faders and &yogh;e moders eke also</L>
<L>&THORN;ouhe &yogh;e haue childern be it on or mo</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure is &thorn;e charge of al her suffrance</L>
<L N="96">Whiles &thorn;ei bien vnder gouernance
<PB REF="00000457.tif" N="429"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="306"></L>
<L>Be&thorn;e ware &thorn;at be ensample of &yogh;oure leueinge</L>
<L>Ey&thorn;er be necligence in chastisinge</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ei ne perische for .I. dare wele seie</L>
<L N="100">&YOGH;if &thorn;at &thorn;ei done &yogh;e schol ful sore abye</L>
<L>Vnder a scheperd soft and necligent</L>
<L>&thorn;e wolf ha&thorn; mony a schepe and lamme to-rent</L>
<L>Sufficit one ensample nowe as here</L>
<L N="104">For .I. most torne a&yogh;eine to matiere</L>
<L>This maide of whiche .y tel my tale expresse</L>
<L>Sche kepped hir self sche neded no maistresse</L>
<L>For in hire leueynge maydens myht rede</L>
<L N="108">As in a boke euery good worde and dede</L>
<L>&thorn;at longe&thorn; to a mayden vertuous</L>
<L>Sche was so prudent and so bounteuous</L>
<L>For whiche oute spronge on euery side</L>
<L N="112">Bo&thorn;e of hir beute and hire bounte wide</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;oruhe &thorn;e londe &thorn;ei presede hire ychon</L>
<L>&thorn;at loued verteus saue envye alone</L>
<L>&thorn;at sory is of o&thorn;er mennes wele</L>
<L N="116">And gladde is of his sorwe and vnhele<MILESTONE N="171a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>The doctour make&thorn; &thorn;is descripcioune</L>
<L>This maide went on a daie in-to &thorn;e toune</L>
<L>To-warde &thorn;e temple wi&thorn; hir moder dere</L>
<L N="120">As is of &yogh;onge Maidens &thorn;e manere</L>
<L>Nowe was &thorn;er a Iustice in &thorn;e toune</L>
<L>&thorn;at gouernour was of &thorn;at regioune</L>
<L>And so befel &thorn;is Iuge his ey&yogh;en kast</L>
<L N="124">Vppon &thorn;is maide aviseinge hire ful fast</L>
<L>As sche cam for&thorn; by &thorn;ere &thorn;e Iuge stode</L>
<L>Anone his hert chaunge&thorn; and his moode</L>
<L>So was he cauht wi&thorn; &thorn;e beaute of &thorn;is maide</L>
<L N="128">And to him self ful priuely he seide</L>
<L>This maiden schal be myne for any man</L>
<L>Anone &thorn;e fende in to his hert ran</L>
<L>And tauht him sodanly be what sleyht</L>
<L N="132">The maiden to his purpos wynne he myht
<PB REF="00000458.tif" N="430"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="307"></L>
<L>For certes be no force ne be no meede</L>
<L>Him &thorn;ouht he was not able for to spede</L>
<L>For he was stronge of frendes and eke sche</L>
<L N="136">Confermed was in suche souereigne beute</L>
<L>That wele he wist he myht hire neuer wynne</L>
<L>As for to maake hire wi&thorn; hire bodi synne</L>
<L>For whiche wi&thorn; grete deliberacioune</L>
<L N="140">He sent after a clerk in to &thorn;e toune</L>
<L>The whiche he knewe ful sotel and ful bolde</L>
<L>This Iuge ha&thorn;e vn-to &thorn;is clerke his tale ytolde</L>
<L>In secre wise and maade him to assure</L>
<L N="144">He schold tel it to no creature</L>
<L>And if he dide he scholde lese his hede</L>
<L>And whan assented was &thorn;is cursed rede</L>
<L>Gladde was &thorn;e Iuge and maade goode chiere</L>
<L N="148">And &yogh;af him &yogh;eftes precious and dere</L>
<L>Whan schapen was al &thorn;is conspiracie</L>
<L>From pointe to pointe howe &thorn;at his licherye</L>
<L>Performed schold be ful sotellye</L>
<L N="152">As &yogh;e schal heren afterward openlye</L>
<L>Home go&thorn;e &thorn;is clerk &thorn;at hiht Claudius</L>
<L>This fals Iuge &thorn;at hiht Apius</L>
<L>So was his name it is no fable</L>
<L N="156">Bot knowen for an historall &thorn;inge notable</L>
<L>The sentence of it so&thorn; is oute of doute</L>
<L>This fals Iuge go&thorn; nowe faste aboute<MILESTONE N="171b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To hasten his delite al &thorn;at he maie</L>
<L N="160">And so be-fel sone after on a daie</L>
<L>&THORN;is fals Iuge as telle&thorn; vs &thorn;e storie</L>
<L>As he was wonte satt in his Consistorie</L>
<L>And &yogh;aue his domes vpon sundre caas</L>
<L N="164">This fals clerke cam for&thorn;e a wel good paas</L>
<L>And seide lorde if &thorn;at it be &yogh;oure will</L>
<L>As do&thorn;e me riht vpon &thorn;is pitous bill</L>
<L>In whiche .I. pleine vpon virgineus</L>
<L N="168">And if &thorn;at he wil seine it is nou&yogh;[t] &thorn;us
<PB REF="00000459.tif" N="431"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="308"></L>
<L>.I. wille preue it and finde good wittenesse</L>
<L>&thorn;at so&thorn;e is &thorn;at my bill will expresse</L>
<L>The Iuge Ansewerde of &thorn;is in his absence</L>
<L N="172">.I. maie not &yogh;if diffinitif sentence</L>
<L>Latt done him call . &amp; .I. wil gladly here</L>
<L>Thou schalt haue riht and no wronge here</L>
<L>Virgineus came to wite &thorn;e Iuges will</L>
<L N="176">And riht a-none was redde &thorn;is cursed bill</L>
<L>&thorn;e sentence of hit was as &yogh;e schal here</L>
<L>To &yogh;owe my lorde sir Apius so dere</L>
<L>Schewe&thorn; &yogh;oure pouer seruant Claudius</L>
<L N="180">Howe &thorn;at a knyht called virgineus</L>
<L>A&yogh;eines &thorn;e lawe a&yogh;eines al equite</L>
<L>Holde&thorn; expresse a&yogh;eines &thorn;e wil of me</L>
<L>Mi seruant whiche &thorn;at is &thorn;rall be riht</L>
<L N="184">Wyche from myne hous was stolne one a nyht</L>
<L>Whiles sche was ful &yogh;onge .I. will . it preue</L>
<L>Be wittenesse lorde so &thorn;at &yogh;e &yogh;owe nouht greue</L>
<L>Sche his nouht his douhter what so he seie</L>
<L N="188">Where-for my lorde &thorn;e Iugge to &yogh;owe .I. preie</L>
<L>&YOGH;elde me my &thorn;rall if it be &yogh;oure wil</L>
<L>Lo &thorn;is was &thorn;e sentence of &thorn;e bil</L>
<L>Virgineus began vpon &thorn;e clerke be-holde</L>
<L N="192">Bote hastely ar he his tale tolde</L>
<L>He wolde haue defended it as scholde a knyht</L>
<L>And be wittenesse of mony a trewe wyht</L>
<L>That al was fals &thorn;at seide his aduersarie</L>
<L N="196">This Cursed Iuge wolde no longer tarie</L>
<L>Ne here a worde more of Virgineus</L>
<L>Bot &yogh;af his Iugement and seide &thorn;us</L>
<L>.I. deme anone &thorn;is clerk his seruant haue</L>
<L N="200">Thou schalt no longer in &thorn;in house hir saue<MILESTONE N="172a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Go bringe hir for&thorn;e and bringe hir in owre warde</L>
<L>This clerk schal haue his &thorn;ralle &thorn;us .I. awarde</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;is wor&thorn;i knyht Virgineus</L>
<L N="204">Thoruhe &thorn;assent of &thorn;e Iuge Apius
<PB REF="00000460.tif" N="432"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="309"></L>
<L>Most be force his dere douhter &yogh;euen</L>
<L>Vn-to &thorn;e Iuge in lichere to leuen</L>
<L>He go&thorn;e him home and sett him in his hall</L>
<L N="208">And lete anone his dere douhter call</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; a face dede as asshen colde</L>
<L>Vpon hire hum[ble] face he gan be-holde</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; faders pite stikinge &thorn;oruhe his hert</L>
<L N="212">Al wolde he nouht from his purpos conuert</L>
<L>Douhter quod he virginea be &thorn;i name</L>
<L>There bien tuo weys ey&thorn;er o&thorn;er schame</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;ou must soffer alas &thorn;at .I. was bore</L>
<L N="216">For neuer &thorn;ou deseruest where fore</L>
<L>To deyen wi&thorn; a swerde or wi&thorn; a knyf</L>
<L>O der douhter ender of my lif</L>
<L>Whiche .I. haue fosterd vp wi&thorn; suche plesance</L>
<L N="220">&thorn;at &thorn;ou ne weer oute my remembrance</L>
<L>O douhter whiche &thorn;at ert my last woo</L>
<L>And in lif my last ioy also</L>
<L>O gemme of chastite in pacience</L>
<L N="224">Take &thorn;ou &thorn;i de&thorn; for &thorn;is is my sentence</L>
<L>For loue and nouht for hate &thorn;ou must be dede</L>
<L>My pitous honde most smyte of &thorn;in hede</L>
<L>Alas &thorn;at euer Apius &thorn;e seyhe</L>
<L N="228">Thus ha&thorn;e he falsly Iugged &thorn;e to day</L>
<L>And tolde hire al &thorn;e cas as &yogh;e be-fore</L>
<L>Haue herd it nede&thorn; nouht to tel it no more</L>
<L>Merce dere fadere quod &thorn;is maide</L>
<L N="232">And wi&thorn;e &thorn;at worde sche bo&thorn;e hire armes leide</L>
<L>Aboute his nekke as sche was wont to do</L>
<L>The teres barsten oute of hire yen tuo</L>
<L>And seide goode fader schal .I. deye</L>
<L N="236">Is &thorn;ere no grace is &thorn;ere no remedie</L>
<L>No certes dere douhter myne quod he</L>
<L>Than &yogh;eue me leue fader myn quod sche</L>
<L>My de&thorn; to compleyne a litel space</L>
<L N="240">For parde Ieffa &yogh;aue his douhter grace
<PB REF="00000461.tif" N="433"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="310"></L>
<L>For to compleine ar he hir slowhe alas</L>
<L>And god it wote no &thorn;inge was hire trespas<MILESTONE N="172b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Bot &thorn;at sche rann hir fader first to see</L>
<L N="244">To welcom him wi&thorn; grete solempnite</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde sche fel in swoune anone</L>
<L>And after whan hir swounynge was agone</L>
<L>Sche rise&thorn; vpe and to hire fader seide</L>
<L N="248">Blissed be god &thorn;at .I. schal deye a meide</L>
<L>&yogh;if me my de&thorn;e ar &thorn;at .I. haue a schame</L>
<L>Do&thorn;e wi&thorn; &yogh;oure Childe &yogh;oure wil a goddes name</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word sche praie&thorn; ful oft</L>
<L N="252">&thorn;at with his swerde he scholde smite hir softe</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at word in swoune doune sche felle</L>
<L>Hir fader wi&thorn; ful sorweful hert and felle</L>
<L>Hire heued of smote and be toppe it hent</L>
<L N="256">And to &thorn;e Iuge he &yogh;aue it to present</L>
<L>As he satt in his dome in consistorie</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;e Iuge it sauhe as sei&thorn;e &thorn;e storie</L>
<L>He badde take him and honge him also fast</L>
<L N="260">Bot riht anone al &thorn;e peple in &thorn;rast</L>
<L>To saue &thorn;e knyht for reu&thorn;e and for pyte</L>
<L>ffor knowen was &thorn;e foles iniquite</L>
<L>&thorn;e peple anone hadd susspecte in &thorn;is &thorn;inge</L>
<L N="264">Be maner of &thorn;is clerkes chalangeinge</L>
<L>&thorn;at it was be &thorn;e assent of Apius</L>
<L>That wist wele &thorn;at he was lycherous</L>
<L>ffor whiche vn-to &thorn;is Apius &thorn;ei gone</L>
<L N="268">And kesten him in prison riht a-none</L>
<L>Whereas he slowhe him selfe and Claudius</L>
<L>That seruant was vn-to &thorn;is Apius</L>
<L>Was demed for to honge vpon a tre</L>
<L N="272">Bot virgineus of his grete Pite</L>
<L>Praide for him &thorn;at he was exiled</L>
<L>And elles certes he hadde be by-gilede</L>
<L>The remenant were honged more and lesse</L>
<L N="276">That consented were to &thorn;is cursednesse
<PB REF="00000462.tif" N="434"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="311"></L>
<L>Here maye men see how sinne ha&thorn;e his merite</L>
<L>Be war for no man wote howe god wil smyte</L>
<L>In no degre ne in wyche maner wise</L>
<L N="280">&thorn;e werme of conscience wil arise</L>
<L>Of wikked lif &thorn;ouhe it so priue be</L>
<L>&thorn;at no man woot of it bot god and he</L>
<L>Whe&thorn;er he be lewde man or lerede</L>
<L N="284">He note howe sone . he maie bee aferde</L>
<L>Ther-fore rede .I. &yogh;owe &thorn;is counsel take<MILESTONE N="173a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For-sake&thorn; sinne ar sinne &yogh;oue for-sake</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit fabula</B> Magistri Phisicorum</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000463.tif" N="435">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="312">
<HEAD>Incipit prologus questoris<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 173</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Owre Oste gan swere as he ware wode</L>
<L N="288">Harrowe quod he be Nayles and be blode</L>
<L>This was a cussed &thorn;ef a fals Iustice</L>
<L>A schendful de&thorn;e as hert can deuise</L>
<L>So fal vpon his body and his bones<NOTE PLACE="marg">[<SUP>*</SUP>]</NOTE></L>
<L N="292">&THORN;e deuel .I. be-ken him al att ones<NOTE PLACE="marg">[<SUP>*</SUP>]</NOTE></L>
<L>Alas to dere bouht sche hir beute</L>
<L>Wherefor .I. seie &thorn;at al men maie see</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;iftes of fortune or of Nature</L>
<L N="296">Be&thorn;e cause of de&thorn;e of mony a creature</L>
<L>Hire beute was hir de&thorn;e .I. dare wele seine</L>
<L>Alas how pitously as sche was sleine</L>
<L>Bot here-of wil .I. nouht procede as nowe<NOTE PLACE="marg">[spurious]</NOTE></L>
<L N="300">Men haue ful often more harme &thorn;an prowe</L>
<L>Bot trewly myne owen maister dere</L>
<L>This is a pitous tale for to here</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles pas ouer is no force</L>
<L N="304">.I. praie to god to saue &thorn;i gentil corps</L>
<L>And &thorn;ine vrinals and &thorn;i Iordanes</L>
<L>&THORN;ine ypocras and &thorn;ine Galiounes</L>
<L>And euery box ful of &thorn;ine letuarie</L>
<L N="308">God blesse hem and oure lady seint Mary</L>
<L>So mot .I. &thorn;e &thorn;ou ert a propre man</L>
<L>And ylike a prelate &middot; be seinte Runyan</L>
<L>Sayd .I. nouht wele can .I. nou&yogh;ht speke in terme</L>
<L N="312">Bot wele .I. wote &thorn;ou doste myne herte to erme</L>
<L>&thorn;at .I. almost haue cauht a cardiacle</L>
<L>Be corpus bones bot &yogh;iue .I. haue triacle</L>
<L>Or elles a drauht of moiste and corne ale</L>
<L N="316">Or bott .I. here a-none a meri tale
<PB REF="00000464.tif" N="436"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="313"></L>
<L>Myne hert is loste for pete of &thorn;is maide</L>
<L>Thowe belamy Iohen Pardoner he saide</L>
<L>Tel vs sum Merthes or Iapes riht anone</L>
<L N="320">It schal be do quod he be seinte Ninione</L>
<L>Bot first quod he here at &thorn;is ale stake</L>
<L>.I. wil bo&thorn;e drinke and ette of a kake</L>
<L>Bot riht anone &thorn;es gentiles begon to crie</L>
<L N="324">Nay lat him tel vs of no Rebaudie</L>
<L>Tel vs sume Moral &thorn;inge &thorn;at we mowe lere<MILESTONE N="173b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Some wytt and &thorn;an will we gladly here</L>
<L>.I. graun[t] y-wysse quod he . bot .I. most &thorn;enke</L>
<L N="328">Vppon . sum honest &thorn;inge whiles &thorn;at .I. drinke</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit Prologus questoris</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000465.tif" N="437">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="314">
<HEAD>Incipit fabula questoris.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>LOrdynges quod he in cherches whan .I. preche</L>
<L>.I. peyne me to haue an haunteine speche</L>
<L>Hereynge oute as rounde as go&thorn;e a bell</L>
<L N="332">For .I. kan be roote &thorn;at .I. tell</L>
<L>My teme is alweie one and euer was</L>
<L>Radix omnium malorum est/ cupiditas;</L>
<L>fferst .I. pronounce wense &thorn;at .I. come</L>
<L N="336">An[d] &thorn;an my billes schewe .I. al and somme</L>
<L>Oure liege lorde seal is my patent</L>
<L>&thorn;at schewe .I. first my body to warent</L>
<L>&thorn;at no man be so bolde preste ne clerke</L>
<L N="340">Me to destorble of cristes holy werke</L>
<L>And after &thorn;at tel .I. for&thorn;e my tales</L>
<L>Bulles of popes and of Cardinales</L>
<L>Of Patriarkes and of Bischopes .I. schewe</L>
<L N="344">And in latine .I. speke wordes a fewe</L>
<L>To sauern wi&thorn; my predicacione</L>
<L>And for to ster men to deuocione</L>
<L>&thorn;an schewe .I. for&thorn;e my longe cristal stones</L>
<L N="348">Y-crammed ful of cloutes and of bones</L>
<L>Relekes &thorn;ei buen as ween &thorn;ei euerychon</L>
<L>Than haue .I. in laton a scholdere bone</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at was an holy Iewes schepe</L>
<L N="352">Goodmen saie .I. take&thorn;e of my wordes kepe</L>
<L>If &thorn;at &thorn;is bone bue wasche in any welle</L>
<L>Of cowe or calfe schepe or oxe swelle</L>
<L>&thorn;at worme ha&thorn;e y-ete or y-stonge</L>
<L N="356">[Take watir of that welle and wasshe his tonge<MILESTONE UNIT="Harl. 7335 folio" N="159a"><NOTE PLACE="marg">[<I>Not in Addit.</I> 25,718]</NOTE>]
<PB REF="00000466.tif" N="438"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="315"></L>
<L>Touche he &thorn;is bone anone he schal be sounde</L>
<L>And &yogh;it also for&thorn;ermore; of pokkes &amp; scabbes &amp; of euery sore.</L>
<L>Schal euery schepe be hole &thorn;at of &thorn;is well</L>
<L N="360">Drenke&thorn; a drawht of take&thorn; kepe what .I. tell</L>
<L>Wil euery wyhte er &thorn;at &thorn;e koke him crowe&thorn;e</L>
<L>And do&thorn;e &thorn;inge &thorn;at him owe&thorn;e</L>
<L>ffastynge drinke of &thorn;is welle a drauht</L>
<L N="364">And &thorn;ilke holy Iewe oure helders ones tauht</L>
<L>His bestes and his store schal multeplie</L>
<L>And sires also it hele&thorn; Ielousye<MILESTONE N="174a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And &thorn;ouhe a man be fal in Ielowsie rage</L>
<L N="368">Lat make wi&thorn; &thorn;is water his potage</L>
<L>And neuer schal he more his wif mestruste</L>
<L>&thorn;ouhe he &thorn;e so&thorn;e a defaute by hire wiste</L>
<L>Al hadde sche taken prestes tueyne or &thorn;re</L>
<L N="372">Here is a Metaine eke &yogh;e maye see</L>
<L>He &thorn;at his honde wil put in &thorn;at Metane</L>
<L>He schall haue multipliinge of his greine</L>
<L>Whan he ha&thorn;e sowen be it whete or otes</L>
<L N="376">So &thorn;at of pens o&thorn;er of grotes</L>
<L>And men and wemmen o &thorn;inge warn .I. &yogh;owe</L>
<L>If any whight be in &thorn;is cherche nowe</L>
<L>&thorn;at ha&thorn; done sinne orrible &thorn;at he</L>
<L N="380">Dare nouht fo[r] schame schriuen be</L>
<L>Or any womman be sche &yogh;onge or olde</L>
<L>&thorn;at ha&thorn; ymaad hir husbond cokwolde</L>
<L>Suche folke schal haue no powere no grace</L>
<L N="384">To offer to my relikes in &thorn;is place</L>
<L>And who so finde&thorn; him oute of suche blame</L>
<L>&thorn;ei wil come vp and offer in goddes name</L>
<L>And .I. assoile him be &thorn;e auctorite</L>
<L N="388">Suche as be bul was graunted me</L>
<L>Be &thorn;is Gaude haue .I. wonne euery &yogh;ere</L>
<L>An .C. mark se&thorn;en .I. was pardonere</L>
<L>.I. stonde like a clerke in mony a pulpitt</L>
<L N="392">And schewe &thorn;e lewde peple and doune &thorn;ei sitt
<PB REF="00000467.tif" N="439"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="316"></L>
<L>.I. preche so as &yogh;e haue herde be-fore</L>
<L>And tel an hundre&thorn; Iapes more</L>
<L>Than peyne .I. me to strecche for&thorn;e my nekke</L>
<L N="396">And est and west uppon &thorn;e peple .I. bekke</L>
<L>As do&thorn;e a doue sittinge vpon a berne</L>
<L>Myne hondes and my tonge go so &yogh;erne</L>
<L>&thorn;at it is Ioye to see my besinesse</L>
<L N="400">Of avarise and suche o&thorn;er cursednesse</L>
<L>Is as Mi preccheinge to make hem fre</L>
<L>To &yogh;eue here pens namely vnto me</L>
<L>For myne entent is nouht bot for to wynne</L>
<L N="404">And no &thorn;inge for correction of sinne</L>
<L>.I. reke neuer whan &thorn;at &thorn;ei be buried</L>
<L>&thorn;ouhe &thorn;at here soules gone a blakberied</L>
<L>For certes mony a predicaci&omacr;ne</L>
<L N="408">Soune&thorn; oft time of yuel entencione</L>
<L>[Somme for plesance of folk and for flaterie<MILESTONE UNIT="Addit. 25,718 folio" N="54a"></L>
<L>To ben auaunsed for ypocresye</L>
<L>And somme for veynglory and somme for hate<MILESTONE UNIT="Addit. 25,718 folio" N="54b"></L>
<L N="412">ffor when I dar nought oother weys de-bate</L>
<L>Thenne wolly stynge him with my tunge smert</L>
<L>I preching and that he shal nought astert</L>
<L>To ben defamed falsly if that he</L>
<L N="416">Hath trespased to myn britheren other to me</L>
<L>ffor though I telle nought his propre name</L>
<L>Men shal wel knowe that hit is the same</L>
<L>Bothe by seignes and oother circumstaunces</L>
<L N="420">Thus . rule I folk that doth vs displesances</L>
<L>Thus spitte I myn venym vnder hewe</L>
<L>Of holinesse to seme holy and trewe</L>
<L>But shortly myn entent wol I deuyse</L>
<L>I<NOTE PLACE="marg">[? MS sir]</NOTE> preche of no thing but of Coueytise</L>
<L>Ther-fore my teme is &yogh;et and euer was</L>
<L>Radix malorum est cupiditas</L>
<L>Thus kan I preche ayayns that same vice<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Addit. MS <I>extract stops</I>]</NOTE>]</L>
<L N="428">Suche &thorn;at .I. vse and &thorn;at is of auarice<MILESTONE N="174b" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000468.tif" N="440"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="317"></L>
<L>Bot &thorn;eihe .I. me self be gilte in &thorn;at sinne</L>
<L>&YOGH;it kanne .I. maake o&thorn;er folke to wynne</L>
<L>Fromme auarice and sore to repent</L>
<L N="432">Bot &thorn;at nes nouht myn principal entent</L>
<L>.I. preche no &thorn;inge bot for Couetise</L>
<L>Of &thorn;is matiere it ou&yogh;te ynowhe suffise</L>
<L>&thorn;an tel .I. of ensamples many one</L>
<L N="436">Of Olde stories longe time agone</L>
<L>For lewde peple louen tales olde</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;inges can &thorn;ei wele reporte and holde</L>
<L>What trowe &yogh;e whiles &thorn;at .I. maie preche</L>
<L N="440">And wynne gold and siluer for .I. teche</L>
<L>&thorn;at .I. wil leue in pouert wilfully</L>
<L>Nay . nay .I. &thorn;ouht it neuer treulye</L>
<L>ffor .I. preche and begge in sundre landes</L>
<L N="444">.I. wil nouht do no labour wi&thorn; myn handes</L>
<L>An[d] make basketes and leue &thorn;ere-bye</L>
<L>Be-cause .I. wil nouht bigge ydelye</L>
<L>.I. wil none of &thorn;e aposteles counterfete</L>
<L N="448">.I. wil haue mony chese and whete</L>
<L>Al were it &yogh;euen of &thorn;e porest page</L>
<L>Ey&thorn;er of &thorn;e pourest wedowe in a vilage</L>
<L>Al schold hir childerne sterue for famyne</L>
<L N="452">Nay .I. wil drinke &thorn;e lycoure of &thorn;e vine</L>
<L>And haue a Ioly wenche in euerych toune</L>
<L>Bot herkene&thorn; lordynges in conclusione</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure lykeinge is &thorn;at .I. schal tel a tale</L>
<L N="456">Nowe .I. haue dro[n]ke a drauhte of Corne ale</L>
<L>Be god .I. hope .I. schal tel &yogh;owe a &thorn;inge</L>
<L>&thorn;at schal be reson biene at &yogh;oure lykeinge</L>
<L>ffor &thorn;ouhe my self be a ful vicious man</L>
<L N="460">A more.-il tale &yogh;it .I. &yogh;owe telle can</L>
<L>Whiche .I. am wont to preche for to wynne</L>
<L>Now holde &yogh;oure pes my tale .I. wil beginne.<NOTE PLACE="end">[no break in the MS.]</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000469.tif" N="441"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="318"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN flaundres whilom was a compaignie</L>
<L N="464">Of &yogh;onge folke &thorn;at hawten folye</L>
<L>As Riott . Hasard . stewes . and tauerns</L>
<L>[<NOTE PLACE="marg">[<I>Addit.</I> 25,718 <I>reads</I> "And suche oother diuers mischaunces", <I>leaf</I> 55]</NOTE>Where as with harpees lutes and gyternes<MILESTONE UNIT="Harl. 7335 folio" N="161b">]</L>
<L>&thorn;ei daunce and pleie and dise bo&thorn;e daie and nyht</L>
<L N="468">And eten and drenke al-so ouer al here myht</L>
<L>Thorwhe whiche &thorn;ei done &thorn;e deuel sacrifise</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-inne &thorn;e deueles temple in cursed wyse</L>
<L>The superfluys abhomynable<MILESTONE N="175a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="472">Here o&thorn;es bene so grete and dampnable</L>
<L>&thorn;at it is grisely for to here hem swere</L>
<L>Oure blissed lordes body &thorn;ei to-tere</L>
<L>Hem &thorn;ouht . Iewes rent him nouht ynowhe</L>
<L N="476">And yche of hem att o&thorn;er sinnes lowhe</L>
<L>And riht anone &thorn;an came tomblesters</L>
<L>ffetis and smal and &yogh;onge fruytsters</L>
<L>Singers wi&thorn; harpes baudes waferes</L>
<L N="480">Such bien &thorn;e deuel officiers</L>
<L>To kendel and blowe &thorn;e fire of lychery</L>
<L>&thorn;at is annexed to glotonye</L>
<L>&thorn;e holy writte take .I. to wittenesse</L>
<L N="484">&thorn;at lycherie is in wyne and dronkennesse</L>
<L>Lo howe &thorn;at dronken lothe vnkindelye</L>
<L>Lay be his douhtres tuo vnweteynglye</L>
<L>So dronke he was he nest what he wrouht</L>
<L N="487b">And &thorn;erfore sore repent him ouhte<NOTE PLACE="marg">[spurious]</NOTE></L>
<L N="488">Herodes who so wil &thorn;e story seche</L>
<L N="488b">&thorn;ere maie &yogh;e leren and be ensample teche<NOTE PLACE="marg">[spurious]</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000470.tif" N="442"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="319"></L>
<L N="489">Whan he of wine was replete att his feste</L>
<L>Riht att his owen table &yogh;af his heste</L>
<L>To slene &thorn;e Baptiste Iohn ful gilteles</L>
<L N="492">Senec sei&thorn;e eke good wordes douteles</L>
<L>He sei&thorn;e he kan no difference finde</L>
<L>Be-tuex a man &thorn;at is oute of his mynde</L>
<L>And a man &thorn;at is drongelewe</L>
<L N="496">Bot wodenes is falne in a schrewe</L>
<L>Perseuere&thorn; longer &thorn;an do&thorn; dronkennesse</L>
<L>O glotony ful of cursednesse</L>
<L>O cause firste of oure confusione</L>
<L N="500">O originale of owre dampnacione</L>
<L>To criste hadde bouht owte wi&thorn; his blode a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>Lo howe dere and schortly was to seine</L>
<L>A-boute was &thorn;e cursed velanye</L>
<L N="504">Corrupte was al &thorn;is werld &thorn;oruhe glotonye</L>
<L>Adam oure fadere and his wif also</L>
<L>Fro paradise to labour and to woo</L>
<L>Were dreue for &thorn;at vice it is no drede</L>
<L N="508">For whiles &thorn;at adam fasted as .I. rede</L>
<L>He was in paradise &amp; whan &thorn;at hee</L>
<L>Ete of &thorn;e fruyte defended on a tree</L>
<L>Anone he was out cast to woo and pyne<MILESTONE N="175b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="512">O glotonye on &thorn;e wele ouht vs to pleine</L>
<L>O wist a man howe many maladies</L>
<L>Folowe&thorn; of excesse and of glotonies</L>
<L>He schold be &thorn;e more mesurable</L>
<L N="516">Of his Diet sittinge att &thorn;e table</L>
<L>Alas &thorn;e schort &thorn;rote &thorn;e tender mou&thorn;e</L>
<L>Make&thorn; &thorn;at est and west Nor&thorn;e and sou&thorn;e</L>
<L>In er&thorn;e in eyre in water men to swynke</L>
<L N="520">To gette a gloton Mete and drinkge</L>
<L>Of &thorn;is matiere o paule wele cans &thorn;ou entrete</L>
<L>Metee vn-to wome and wombe eke vn-to mete</L>
<L>Schal god discriuen bo&thorn;e as poule sei&thorn;e</L>
<L N="524">Alas a foule &thorn;inge it is be my fei&thorn;e
<PB REF="00000471.tif" N="443"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="320"></L>
<L>To seie &thorn;is worde and fouler is &thorn;e dede</L>
<L>When men so drenken of &thorn;e white and of &thorn;e rede</L>
<L>&THORN;at of his &thorn;rote he maade his priuetee</L>
<L N="528">&THORN;oruhe &thorn;ilke cursed superfluyte</L>
<L>&thorn;e Appostell wepeinge sei&thorn;e ful pitously</L>
<L>&thorn;ere walken mony of whiche &yogh;oue tolde haue .I.</L>
<L>.I. saye it nowe wepeinge wi&thorn; pitous voice</L>
<L N="532">There bien enmyes of cristes croice</L>
<L>Of whiche &thorn;e ende is de&thorn;e &thorn;e wombe is hire god</L>
<L>O wombe o holy o stinkinge cod</L>
<L>Fulfilled of donge and of corrupcione</L>
<L N="536">Att ey&thorn;e[r] ende of &thorn;e foule is &thorn;e soune</L>
<L>Howe grete cost and laboure is to finde</L>
<L>&thorn;es cokes howe &thorn;aie stame and striue and grinde</L>
<L>And turne substance in-to accident</L>
<L N="540">To fulfil al &thorn;i lykorous talent</L>
<L>Oute of &thorn;e harde bones knoke &thorn;eie</L>
<L>&thorn;e mery for &thorn;ei cast nouht aweie</L>
<L>&thorn;at maie go &thorn;oruh &thorn;e golet soft and swote</L>
<L N="544">Of spicere of leues barke and rote</L>
<L>Schal be his sauce be maade be delite</L>
<L>To maak him &yogh;itt a newere appetite</L>
<L>Bot certes he &thorn;at haunte&thorn; suche delices</L>
<L N="548">Is dede whiles &thorn;at he leue&thorn; in &thorn;e vices</L>
<L>A lycherous &thorn;inge is wyne and dronkennesse</L>
<L>Is ful of stryueynge and of wrechednesse</L>
<L>O dronken man disfigured is &thorn;i face.</L>
<L N="552">Foul is &thorn;i bre&thorn; . foule ert &thorn;ou to embrace</L>
<L>And &thorn;oruhe &thorn;i drongen nose seme&thorn;e &thorn;i soune<MILESTONE N="176a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As &thorn;ouhe &thorn;ou ay said Samson samsoune</L>
<L>And &yogh;it goode wotte Samson dranke neuer wyne</L>
<L N="556">&thorn;ou falest as a dronken swyne</L>
<L>&thorn;i tonge is loste and al &thorn;ine honest cures</L>
<L>For dronkenes is verreie sepultures</L>
<L>Of mannes witte and his discrecion</L>
<L N="560">In whome &thorn;at drinke ha&thorn; dominacion
<PB REF="00000472.tif" N="444"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="321"></L>
<L>He can no counsel kepe it is no drede</L>
<L>Now kepe &yogh;owe fro &thorn;e white and fro &thorn;e reede</L>
<L>Namely fro &thorn;e white wyne of lepe</L>
<L N="564">&thorn;at is to sel in fische strete or in chep</L>
<L>&thorn;is wyne of Spayne crepe&thorn; Sotelly</L>
<L>In o&thorn;er wynes groweinge fast by</L>
<L>Of whiche &thorn;ere rise&thorn; suche fumosite</L>
<L N="568">&thorn;at whan a man ha&thorn; dronke drauhtes &thorn;re</L>
<L>And wene&thorn; &thorn;at he be att home in chepe</L>
<L>He is in spayne riht atte &thorn;e toune of lepe</L>
<L>Nouht att &thorn;e Rochel ne att Bordeux toune</L>
<L N="572">And &thorn;an wille &thorn;ei seyn Sampsone Sampsone</L>
<L>Bot herken lordeynges o worde .I. &yogh;ow preie</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;e souereigne attes dar .I. seie</L>
<L>Of victories in &thorn;e olde testament</L>
<L N="576">&thorn;at &thorn;oruhe verrey god &thorn;at is omnipotent</L>
<L>Weere done in abstinence and in preiere</L>
<L>Loke &thorn;e bible and &thorn;ere &yogh;e maie it leere.</L>
