<L>Herden &thorn;e hennes crie &amp; maden wo</L>
<L>And oute att &thorn;e dore stert &thorn;ei a none</L>
<L>And sawe &thorn;e fox to-warde &thorn;e groue gone<MILESTONE N="224b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And bare vpon his bakke &thorn;e koke awaie</L>
<L>And Criden oute harrowe &amp; walaweie</L>
<L>A ha &thorn;e fox &amp; After hem &thorn;ei Ranne</L>
<L N="4572">And ek wi&thorn; staues mony ano&thorn;er manne</L>
<L>Ranne Colle oure dogge talbot &amp; Garland</L>
<L>And Malkin wi&thorn; here distaf in hire hand</L>
<L>Rann &thorn;e cowe &amp; &thorn;e calf &amp; eke &thorn;e verrey hogges</L>
<L N="4576">Sore aferde for berkeinge of &thorn;e dogges</L>
<L>And schowteinge of men &amp; of wemmen eke</L>
<L>&thorn;ei rann so her hert &thorn;ei &thorn;ouht to breke</L>
<L>The Dokes criden as men wold hem qwelle</L>
<L N="4580">&thorn;ei &yogh;elden as fendes done in helle
<PB REF="00000616.tif" N="588"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="299"></L>
<L>Oute of &thorn;e hyves cam &thorn;e swrame of bees</L>
<L>The gees for fere flowe ouer &thorn;e trees</L>
<L>So hydous was &thorn;e noyce a benedicite</L>
<L N="4584">Sertes he Iac strawe &amp; his Meyne&yogh;e</L>
<L>Ne maade neuere schowte halfe so schill</L>
<L>Whan &thorn;at &thorn;ei wolde any flemmynge kill</L>
<L>As &thorn;at ilke daie was maade on &thorn;e fox</L>
<L N="4588">Of brasse &thorn;ei brouht bemes &amp; of box</L>
<L>Of horne &amp; bone in whiche &thorn;ei poped</L>
<L>&thorn;ere-wi&thorn;-&amacr;l &thorn;ei schriked &amp; schowted</L>
<L>It semed howe &thorn;at heuen schold fal</L>
<L N="4592">Nowe good men .I. preie &yogh;owe herkene&thorn; al</L>
<L>Lo how fortune torne&thorn; sodanly</L>
<L>The hope &amp; eke &thorn;e pride of her envye</L>
<L>This kok &thorn;at lei vpon &thorn;is fox bak</L>
<L N="4596">In al his drede vn-to &thorn;e fox spak</L>
<L>And seide sire . If .I. were as &yogh;e</L>
<L>&yogh;it schold .I. saie as wis god help me</L>
<L>Turne&thorn; a&yogh;eine &yogh;e proude clerkes all</L>
<L N="4600">A verrey pestelence vpon &yogh;ow fall</L>
<L>Nowe am .I. comme vnto &thorn;is wode side</L>
<L>Mawgre &yogh;oure hede &thorn;e koke schal her abide</L>
<L>.I. wil him ete in fei&thorn; &amp; &thorn;at anone</L>
<L N="4604">The fox anseward in fei&thorn;e it schal be done</L>
<L>And [as] he spak &thorn;at worde al sodanly</L>
<L>&thorn;is koke brak fro his mou&thorn;e delyuerlye</L>
<L>And hihe vpon a tree he fly&yogh;e anone</L>
<L N="4608">And &thorn;e fox sawe &thorn;at he was goone</L>
<L>Alas quod he o chaunteclere alas</L>
<L>.I. haue quod he done &yogh;owe a trespas<MILESTONE N="225a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>In also muche as .I. maade &yogh;owe aferd</L>
<L N="4612">Whene .I. &yogh;ow hente &amp; brouht oute of &thorn;e &yogh;er[d]e</L>
<L>Bot sire .I. did it nouht in no wikked entente</L>
<L>Come&thorn; doune &amp; .I. schal tel &yogh;owe whatt .I. mente</L>
<L>.I. schal seie so&thorn; god helpe me so</L>
<L N="4616">Naye &thorn;an quod he .I. schrewe vs bo&thorn;e tuo
<PB REF="00000617.tif" N="589"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="300"></L>
<L>And first .I. schrewe my self bo&thorn;e blode &amp; bones</L>
<L>If &thorn;ou be-gile me ofter &thorn;an ones</L>
<L>Thou schalt no more wi&thorn; &thorn;i flatery</L>
<L N="4620">Do me to singe &amp; wynke wi&thorn; myne ey&yogh;e</L>
<L>For he &thorn;at winke&thorn; whan he schold see</L>
<L>As wysly god let him neuer &thorn;e</L>
<L>Nay quod &thorn;e fox god &yogh;eue him meschaunce</L>
<L N="4624">&THORN;at is so vndiscrete of gouernaunce</L>
<L>&thorn;at Iangele&thorn; whan he schold haue pees</L>
<L>Lo suche it is to bue recheles</L>
<L>And necligent and truste&thorn; on flaterye</L>
<L N="4628">Bot &yogh;e &thorn;at halde &thorn;is tale a folye</L>
<L>As of a fox .&amp;. a kok. &amp; of an hen</L>
<L>Take&thorn; &thorn;e moralite goode men</L>
<L>For seinte Poule sei&thorn; all &thorn;at wreten is</L>
<L N="4632">To oure doctrine it is wreten y-wys</L>
<L>Take&thorn; &thorn;e fruyte &amp; lete&thorn; &thorn;e chaf be still</L>
<L>Now good god if &thorn;at it be &thorn;ine will</L>
<L>As sei&thorn;e my lorde so make&thorn; vs al good men</L>
<L N="4636">And bringe vs al to his hihe blisse Amen.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit fabula Capellani.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="H" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000618.tif" N="590">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="576">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>H.</B> FRAGMENT IX.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; <B>1.</B> THE MANCIPLE'S HEAD-LINK.</HEAD>
<HEAD>LANSDOWNE MS.</HEAD>
<HEAD><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>on leaf</I> 225</NOTE> Incipit prologus Mancipij.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>WEte &yogh;e nouht where &thorn;ere stant a litel toune</L>
<L>Whiche &thorn;at cleped is Bobe vp &amp; doune</L>
<L>Vnder &thorn;e blene in Canterbury weye</L>
<L N="4">Ther gan oure Oste for to Iape &amp; pleye</L>
<L>And seid sires ywisse done is in &thorn;e myre</L>
<L>Is &thorn;ere no man for prayer ne for hire</L>
<L>&thorn;at wil awake oure felawe be-hinde</L>
<L N="8">A &thorn;ef myht him lyhtly Robbe &amp; bynde</L>
<L>Se howe he nappe&thorn; for kokes bones</L>
<L>As he wald fal fro his hors att ones</L>
<L>Is &thorn;at a koce of London wi&thorn; meschaunce</L>
<L N="12">Do him com ford he knowe&thorn; his penaunce</L>
<L>For he schall tel a tale be my feye</L>
<L>Al &thorn;ouhe it be not wor&thorn; a botel heye</L>
<L>Awake &thorn;ou koce quod he quod &yogh;if &thorn;e sorowe<MILESTONE N="225b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="16">What eyle&thorn; &thorn;e to slepe so be &thorn;e morwe</L>
<L>Hast &thorn;ou had flene al nyht or ert &thorn;ou dronke</L>
<L>Or hast &thorn;ou wi&thorn; sum qwene al nyht y-swonke</L>
<L>So &thorn;at &thorn;ou maist nouht holde vp &thorn;ine hede</L>
<L N="20">This koe &thorn;at was ful pale &amp; no &thorn;inge rede</L>
<L>Saide oure oste so god my soule blisse</L>
<L>As &thorn;ere is fal on me suche an heuynesse</L>
<L>.I. note whi me were leuer slepe</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;at &thorn;e best galon wyne in chepe
<PB REF="00000619.tif" N="591"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="577"></L>
<L N="25">Wele quod &thorn;e Manciple if it maie done ese</L>
<L>To &thorn;e sire koke; &amp; to no wight displese</L>
<L>Whicho &thorn;at here ride&thorn; in &thorn;is compaignye</L>
<L N="28">And &thorn;at oure Oste wil of his curtesye</L>
<L>.I. wil as nowe excuse &thorn;e of &thorn;in tale</L>
<L>For in good fei&thorn;e &thorn;i vesage is ful pale</L>
<L>&thorn;in ey&yogh;en dasowe&thorn;e so&thorn;ely as me &thorn;enke&thorn;</L>
<L N="32">And wele .I. wote &thorn;i bre&thorn;e foule stinke&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at schewe&thorn; wele &thorn;ou ert nouht wele disposed</L>
<L>Of me certeyne &thorn;ou schalt not bene yglosed</L>
<L>See howe go&thorn;e &thorn;is dronken wight</L>
<L N="36">As &thorn;ouhe he wold vs swelowe anone riht</L>
<L>Halde close &thorn;i mou&thorn;e man be &thorn;i fader kinne</L>
<L>The deuel of hel sett his fote &thorn;ere inne</L>
<L>This cursede bre&thorn;e wil enfect us al</L>
<L N="40">Fy stynkinge swyne fy foule motte &thorn;e fall</L>
<L>Take&thorn; hede sire of &thorn;is lusty manne</L>
<L>Now swete sire wil &yogh;e iust att &thorn;e fanne</L>
<L>Ther-to me &thorn;inke&thorn; &yogh;e be wel yschape</L>
<L N="44">I trowe &thorn;at &yogh;e haue dronken wyne ape</L>
<L>And &thorn;at is whan men pley wi&thorn; a strawe</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;is speke &thorn;e koce wex al wrawe</L>
<L>And on &thorn;e Manciple gan he nodde fast</L>
<L N="48">For lak of speche &amp; doune &thorn;e hors him cast</L>
<L>Where as he laye til men him vp toke</L>
<L>This was &thorn;e faire cheuache of a coke</L>
<L>Alas he ne hadd hold him be his ladel</L>
<L N="52">And er &thorn;at he a&yogh;eine were in his sadel</L>
<L>&thorn;ere was grete schoueinge to &amp; fro</L>
<L>To lift him vp &amp; muche care &amp; woo</L>
<L>So vnwelde was &thorn;i cely palled gost</L>
<L N="56">And to &thorn;e Mancyple &thorn;an spak oure Ost</L>
<L>Be cause &thorn;at drinke ha&thorn;e dominacione<MILESTONE N="226a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Vpon &thorn;is man be my saluacione</L>
<L>.I. trowe fill lewdly he wolde tel his tale</L>
<L N="60">For were it wyne or olde or moyste ale
<PB REF="00000620.tif" N="592"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="578"></L>
<L N="61">That he ha&thorn; dronke he speke&thorn; so in his nose</L>
<L>And fnese&thorn; fast &amp; eke he ha&thorn;e &thorn;e pose</L>
<L>He also to done more &thorn;an .I.-nouhe</L>
<L N="64">To kepen him &amp; his capel oute of &thorn;e slowhe</L>
<L>And if he fal fro his Capel eft sone</L>
<L>&THORN;&amacr;n schal we al haue . ynouhe to done</L>
<L>In liftynge vp his hevy dronken cors</L>
<L N="68">Tel on &thorn;i tale . of him maake .I. no force</L>
<L>Bot &yogh;itte Maunciple in fei&thorn;e &thorn;ou ert to nyce</L>
<L>Thus openly to reproue him of his vice</L>
<L>Ano&thorn;ere daie he wil peraduenture</L>
<L N="72">Recleyme &thorn;e &amp; bringe &thorn;e to luyre</L>
<L>.I. mene he speke will of smale &thorn;inges</L>
<L>And for to speke att &thorn;ine rekenynges</L>
<L>&thorn;at were nouht honest &thorn;ouhe it cam to preue</L>
<L N="76">No quod &thorn;e Manciple &thorn;at were a grete meschef</L>
<L>So myht he bringe me in to &thorn;e snare</L>
<L>&YOGH;it hadde I leuer pay . for &thorn;e Mare</L>
<L>Whiche he ride&thorn; on &thorn;an he schold wi&thorn; me strive</L>
<L N="80">.I. wil nouht wre&thorn;&thorn;e him so mot .I. &thorn;riue</L>
<L>&thorn;at att .I. spak .I. saide it in my bourde</L>
<L>And wyte &yogh;e wele &thorn;at .I. haue here in a gourde</L>
<L>A drauht of wyne . &yogh;e of a rype grape</L>
<L N="84">And riht anone &yogh;e scholne se a good Iape</L>
<L>This koce schal drink &thorn;er-of if .I. maye</L>
<L>Vpon peine of my lif he wil not sey neye</L>
<L>And certanly to tellen as it was</L>
<L N="88">Of &thorn;is vessel &thorn;e koce drank fast alas</L>
<L>Whate nede&thorn; it he dranke . ynowhe aforne</L>
<L>And whan he had poped in his horne</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e manciple he toke &thorn;e gourde a&yogh;eine</L>
<L N="92">And of &thorn;at drink &thorn;e koc was wonder feyne</L>
<L>And &thorn;onked him in suche wise as he cou&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;an gan oure oste waxen wonder lou&thorn;e</L>
<L>And seide .I. see wele it is necessarie</L>
<L N="96">Wher &thorn;at we gone drinke wi&thorn; vs to carye
<PB REF="00000621.tif" N="593"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="579"></L>
<L N="97">For &thorn;at wil torne Rankoure &amp; disese</L>
<L>To accord &amp; loue &amp; mony worde to pese?</L>
<L>O. Bachus blissed be &thorn;in name<MILESTONE N="226b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="100">&thorn;at so can turne ernest in to game</L>
<L>Worschipe &amp; &thorn;onke be to &thorn;i deite</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at Matier gete &yogh;e no more of me</L>
<L>Tel on &thorn;ou Manciple .I. &thorn;e preie</L>
<L N="104">Sires quod he nowe herkene&thorn; what .I. seye</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER><B>Explicit</B> prologus.</TRAILER>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">

<PB REF="00000622.tif" N="594">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="580">
<HEAD>Incipit fabula Mancipij.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="105">WHan phebus dwelled here in &thorn;is er&thorn;e adoune</L>
<L>As olde bokes make&thorn; mencioune</L>
<L>He was &thorn;e most lusti bacheller</L>
<L N="108">Of al &thorn;is werlde &amp; eke &thorn;e best archer</L>
<L>He slowe phiton &thorn;e serpent as he leye</L>
<L>Slepeinge a-&yogh;eine sonne vpon a daie</L>
<L>And mony ano&thorn;ere wor&thorn;e noble dede</L>
<L N="112">He wi&thorn; his bowe brouht as men mowe rede</L>
<L>Pleynge he cou&thorn;e of euery mynstralcye</L>
<L>And singen &thorn;at it was a melodye</L>
<L>To heren of his clere voice &thorn;e soune</L>
<L N="116">Certes &thorn;e kinge of Thebes amphione</L>
<L>&thorn;at wi&thorn; his singeinge walled &thorn;at Cite</L>
<L>Cou&thorn;e neuer singen half so wele as he</L>
<L>Therto he was &thorn;e semelest man</L>
<L N="120">&thorn;at is or was se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;e werlde be-ganne</L>
<L>Whatt nede&thorn; it his fetures for to discryue</L>
<L>For in &thorn;is werld was none so faire on lyue</L>
<L>He was &thorn;er-wi&thorn; fulfilled of gentillesse</L>
<L N="124">Of honour &amp; of parfite wor&thorn;inesse</L>
<L>&thorn;is Phebus &thorn;at was floure ob Bachellarie</L>
<L>As wele in fredam as in Cheualrye</L>
<L>For disport in signe eke of victorie</L>
<L N="128">Of Pheton so as telle&thorn; vs &thorn;e storie</L>
<L>Was wor&thorn;i to beren in his honde a bowe</L>
<L>Now hadde &thorn;is Phebus in his hous a crowe</L>
<L>Whiche in cage he fostred moni a daie</L>
<L N="132">And tauht it speke as men teche&thorn; a iaie
<PB REF="00000623.tif" N="595"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="581"></L>
<L N="133">White was &thorn;is crowe as is a snowe white swanne</L>
<L>And counterfede &thorn;e speche of euery manne</L>
<L>He cou&thorn;e wh&amacr;n he schold tel a tale</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;ere wi&thorn; in al &thorn;is werlde no nyhtinggale</L>
<L>Ne cou&thorn;e be an hundre&thorn; &thorn;ousand dele</L>
<L>Singen so wonderli mery &amp; wele</L>
<L>Nowe hadde &thorn;is Phebus in his hous a wif<MILESTONE N="227a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="140">Whiche &thorn;at he loued more &thorn;an his owen lif</L>
<L>And nyht &amp; daie dide euer his diligence</L>
<L>Hire for to plese &amp; done hire reuerence</L>
<L>Saue onely if &thorn;e so&thorn;e &thorn;at .I. schal seye</L>
<L N="144">Ielowse he was &amp; wolde haue kepped hire feyne</L>
<L>For him were lo&thorn;e Iaped for to be</L>
<L>And so euery whiht in suche degre</L>
<L>Bot al for nouht for it a-vaile&thorn; nouht</L>
<L N="148">A good wif &thorn;at is clene of werke &amp; &thorn;ouht</L>
<L>Schold not be kepped in none awaite certeine</L>
<L>And trewly &thorn;e labour is in veyne</L>
<L>To kepe a schrewe for it wil nouht be</L>
<L N="152">&thorn;is holde .I. for a verraie nycete</L>
<L>To spill a labour for to kepe wives</L>
<L>Thus writen olde clerkes in her lyues</L>
<L>Bot nowe to purpos as .I. first began</L>
<L N="156">&thorn;is wor&thorn;i phebus do&thorn; al &thorn;at he can</L>
<L>To plesen hire weneinge be suche plesance</L>
<L>And for his manhode &amp; his gouernance</L>
<L>&thorn;at noman schold haue put him fro hire grace</L>
<L N="160">Bot god it wote &thorn;er maie noman enbrace</L>
<L>As to discryue a &thorn;inge whiche &thorn;at nature</L>
<L>Ha&thorn;e naturelly sette in a creature</L>
<L>Tak any birde &amp; put it in a kage</L>
<L N="164">And do al &thorn;ine entente &amp; &thorn;i Corage</L>
<L>To foster it tendurli wi&thorn; mete &amp; drinke</L>
<L>Of al Deynte&thorn;es &thorn;ou canst be-&thorn;inke</L>
<L>And kepe it as clenly as &thorn;ou maie</L>
<L N="168">Al-&thorn;ou-he his cage of golde be neuere so gaie
<PB REF="00000624.tif" N="596"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="582"></L>
<L N="169">&YOGH;it ha&thorn; &thorn;is berde be twenti &thorn;ousande folde</L>
<L>Leuer in a forest &thorn;at is wilde &amp; colde</L>
<L>gone ete wermes &amp; suche wrechednesse</L>
<L N="172">For euer &thorn;is birde wil done his besinesse</L>
<L>To ascape oute of his cage whan he maie</L>
<L>His liberte &thorn;e birde desire&thorn; aie</L>
<L>Lat take a katte &amp; foster him wele wi&thorn; melke</L>
<L N="176">And tendre flessche &amp; make his couche of selke</L>
<L>And late him sene a mouse go by &thorn;e wall</L>
<L>And anone he weyue&thorn; melke flesche &amp; all</L>
<L>And euery deynte &thorn;at is in &thorn;at house</L>
<L N="180">Suche appetite ha&thorn; he to ete a mouse</L>
<L>Lo he[re] ha&thorn; lust his dampnacione</L>
<L>And appetite fleme&thorn; discrecione<MILESTONE N="227b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>As &thorn;e wolfe ha&thorn;e also a veleyns kinde</L>
<L N="184">&thorn;e lewdest wolf &thorn;at sche maie finde</L>
<L>Or lewedest of Reputacione &thorn;at will sche take</L>
<L>In time whan hir list to haue a maake</L>
<L>Al &thorn;es ensamples speke .I. be &thorn;is men</L>
<L N="188">&thorn;at bien vntrewe &amp; no &thorn;inge be wemmen</L>
<L>For men haue euere a lykerous appetite</L>
<L>On lower &thorn;ink to performe her delite</L>
<L>&thorn;an on here wives bien &thorn;ei neuer so faire</L>
<L N="192">Ne neuere so trewe ne so debonaire</L>
<L>Flesche is so new fangul wi&thorn; meschance</L>
<L>That we ne kunne in no&thorn;inge haue plesaunce</L>
<L>&thorn;at sownet in to vertew any while</L>
<L N="196">This Phebus whiche &thorn;at &thorn;ouht vpon no gile</L>
<L>Deceyved was for al his Iolyte</L>
<L>For under him a no&thorn;ere hadde sche</L>
<L>A man of litel Reputacione</L>
<L N="200">Not wor&thorn;e to Phebus in comparaci&omacr;ne</L>
<L>&thorn;e more harme is it happe&thorn;e oft soo</L>
<L>Of whiche &thorn;ere comme&thorn; muche harme &amp; wo.</L>
<L>And so be-fel whan Phebus was absent</L>
<L N="204">His wif anone ha&thorn; for hire lemman sent
<PB REF="00000625.tif" N="597"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="583"></L>
<L N="205">Here lemman sertes &thorn;is is a knauysche speche</L>
<L>For&yogh;euen it me &amp; &thorn;at .I. &yogh;ow beseche</L>
<L>The wise plauto sei&thorn; as &yogh;e maie rede</L>
<L N="208">The worde mot nede accorde wi&thorn; &thorn;e dede</L>
<L>If men schal tel properly a &thorn;inge</L>
<L>The worde mot Cosine be to &thorn;e worcheinge</L>
<L>.I. am a bustuse man riht &thorn;us seie .I.</L>
<L N="212">There is no difference treuly</L>
<L>Be-twex a wif &thorn;at is of hihe degre</L>
<L>If of hir body dishonest sche be</L>
<L>And a pouerer wenche o&thorn;ere &thorn;an &thorn;is</L>
<L N="216">If it so be &thorn;ei werken bo&thorn;e amys</L>
<L>Botte &thorn;at &thorn;e gentil is in astate aboue</L>
<L>Sche schal be cleped his ladi as in loue</L>
<L>And for &thorn;at to&thorn;er is a p[o]uere womman</L>
<L N="220">Sche schal be cleped his wenche or his lemman</L>
<L>And god it woote myne owen dere bro&thorn;ere</L>
<L>Men ley&thorn;e &thorn;e tone as lowe as ly&thorn;e &thorn;at o&thorn;ere</L>
<L>Riht so be-twyx a titles tir&amacr;nt</L>
<L>And an owtelawe &amp; a &thorn;efe errant<MILESTONE N="228a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;e sam .I. seie &thorn;ere is no difference</L>
<L>To Alisander was tolde &thorn;is sentence</L>
<L>&thorn;at for &thorn;e terant is of gretter myht</L>
<L N="228">Be fors of meyne to sle doune riht</L>
<L>And birne hous &amp; home and maken al pleyne</L>
<L>Lo &thorn;erefore he is clepe a Capiteigne</L>
<L>And for &thorn;e outelawe ha&thorn;e bot smal men&yogh;e</L>
<L N="232">And may nouht do so grete an harme as he</L>
<L>Ne bringe a contre to so grete meschefe</L>
<L>Men klepen him an outelawe or elles an &thorn;ef</L>
<L>Bot for .I. am a man not texed wele</L>
<L N="236">.I. wil note tel of titus neuer a dele</L>
<L>.I. wil go to my tale as .I. beganne</L>
<L>Whan Phebus wif hadde sent for hir lemman</L>
<L>Anone &thorn;ei wrouht al her lust volage</L>
<L N="240">&thorn;is white crowe &thorn;at honge aye in &thorn;e cage
<PB REF="00000626.tif" N="598"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="584"></L>
<L N="241">Be-helde her werke &amp; seide neuere a worde</L>
<L>And whan &thorn;at home was commen phebus &thorn;e lorde</L>
<L>This Crowe sange kokkow kokkowe cokkowe</L>
<L N="244">What birde quod Phebus what songe singes &thorn;ou</L>
<L>Ne were &thorn;ow wonte so merilye to singe</L>
<L>&thorn;at to myne herte it was a reioysinge</L>
<L>To here &thorn;i voice alace what songe is &thorn;is</L>
<L N="248">Be god quod he .I. singe nouht amys</L>
<L>Phebus quod he for al &thorn;i wor&thorn;inesse</L>
<L>For al &thorn;i beute and &thorn;i gentillesse</L>
<L>For al &thorn;i songe &amp; al &thorn;i Minstralcye</L>
<L N="252">For al &thorn;i wayteinge blered is &thorn;ine eye</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; one of luytel reputacion</L>
<L>Nouht wor&thorn; to &thorn;e as in comparison</L>
<L>The mountance of a gnate so mot [I] priue</L>
<L N="256">For on &thorn;i bedde &thorn;i wif .I. sawe him swyue</L>
<L>What wile &yogh;e more &thorn;e crowe anone him tolde</L>
<L>Be sadde tokenes &amp; be wordes bolde</L>
<L>Howe &thorn;at his wif hadde done her lycherie</L>
<L N="260">Him to grete schame &amp; to grete velanye</L>
<L>And tolde him oft he sawe it wi&thorn; his ey&yogh;en</L>
<L>This Phebus gan awaiwarde for to wrien</L>
<L>Him &thorn;ouht his sorweful herte a brast in tuo</L>
<L N="264">His bowe he bente &amp; sette &thorn;erinne a floo</L>
<L>And in his .Ire &thorn;an ha&thorn;e he his wif sleyne</L>
<L>This es &thorn;e effecte &thorn;ere is nomore to seine<MILESTONE N="228b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For sorwe of whiche he brak his mynstralcy</L>
<L N="268">Bothe harpe &amp; Lute getern &amp; sautrie</L>
<L>And eke he brak his arwes &amp; his bowe</L>
<L>And after &thorn;at &thorn;us spake he to &thorn;e crowe</L>
<L>Traytour quod he wi&thorn; tonge of scorpione</L>
<L N="272">&thorn;ou hast me brouht to my confusione</L>
<L>Alas &thorn;at .I. was wrouht whi nere .I. dede</L>
<L>O dere wif o Iemme of lustihede</L>
<L>That were to me so sadde &amp; eke so trewe</L>
<L N="276">Nowe liest &thorn;ou dede wi&thorn; face pale of hewe
<PB REF="00000627.tif" N="599"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="585"></L>
<L N="277">Ful giltles &thorn;at dorst [I] swere .I.-wys</L>
<L>O rachel hounde to done so foule amys</L>
<L>O trouble witte o yre recheles</L>
<L N="280">&thorn;at vnavised smytest giltles</L>
<L>O wanne trust ful of fals suspeccion</L>
<L>Where was &thorn;i witte and &thorn;i discrecione</L>
<L>Of euery mair be war of rechelnesse</L>
<L N="284">Ne trowe no &thorn;inge wi&thorn; outen stronge wittenesse</L>
<L>Smyte nouhte to sone ar &thorn;at &thorn;ou wyt why</L>
<L>Ande be auisede wele &amp; soburlye</L>
<L>Or &yogh;e do any execucion</L>
<L N="288">Vpon &yogh;oure ire for suspecci&omacr;n</L>
<L>Alas a &thorn;ousand folke haue Rachel ire</L>
<L>Fully for-done or brouht hem in &thorn;e myre</L>
<L>Alas for sorwe .I. wil my self sle</L>
<L N="292">And to &thorn;e crowe o fals &thorn;ef seide he</L>
<L>.I. wil &thorn;e qwite anone &thorn;i fals tale</L>
<L>&thorn;ow songe whilom like a nyht gale</L>
<L>Nowe schalt &thorn;ou fals &thorn;ef &thorn;i songe for-gone</L>
<L N="296">Eke &thorn;ine white fe&thorn;ers euerychon</L>
<L>Ne neuer in al &thorn;i lif schal &thorn;u speke</L>
<L>&thorn;us schal men on a traitur buen y-wreke</L>
<L>&thorn;ou &amp; &thorn;in hofspringe euere schal be blake</L>
<L N="300">Ne neuere swete noise schal &yogh;e maake</L>
<L>Bot euere Crie a-&yogh;eine tempest &amp; reyne</L>
<L>In tokeneynge &thorn;at &thorn;oruhe &thorn;e my wif is sleyne</L>
<L>And to &thorn;e crowe he sterte &amp; &thorn;at anone</L>
<L N="304">And pullede his white fe&thorn;ers euerychone</L>
<L>And maad him blake &amp; raft him al his songe</L>
<L>And eke his speche &amp; oute at &thorn;e dore him slonge</L>
<L>Vn-to &thorn;e deuel whiche .I. him be-take</L>
<L N="308">And for &thorn;is cas bene al crowes blake<MILESTONE N="229a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Lordeinges be &thorn;is ensample .I. &yogh;owe preye</L>
<L>Be&thorn;e ware &amp; take&thorn; kepe what &thorn;at &yogh;e seye</L>
<L>Ne telle&thorn; neuere no man in &yogh;oure lif</L>
<L N="312">Howe &thorn;at ano&thorn;ere man ha&thorn; swyved his wif
<PB REF="00000628.tif" N="600"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="586"></L>
<L N="313">He wil &yogh;owe hate mortally certeyne</L>
<L>Daun Salomon as wise clerkes seyne</L>
<L>Teche&thorn; a man to kepe his tunge wele</L>
<L N="316">Bot as .I. seide .I. am nouht text wele</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles &thorn;us tauht me my dame</L>
<L>My sonne &thorn;inke on &thorn;e crowe a goddes name</L>
<L>My sonne kepe wele &thorn;i tonge &amp; kepe &thorn;i frende</L>
<L N="320">A wikked tonge is wers &thorn;an a fende</L>
<L>My sonne frome a fende men may hem blisse</L>
<L>My sonne god of his endles goodenesse</L>
<L>Walled a tonge wi&thorn; te&thorn;e &amp; lippes eke</L>
<L N="324">For man schold him a-vise what he speke</L>
<L>Mi sonne ful oft for to mechel speche</L>
<L>Ha&thorn;e mony a man be spilt as clerkes teche</L>
<L>Bot for litel speche avisily</L>
<L N="328">Is no man schent to spek generaly</L>
<L>My sonne &thorn;i tonge scholdest &thorn;ou restreine</L>
<L>Att alle time bot whan &thorn;ou dost &thorn;i peine</L>
<L>To speke of god in honour &amp; preyere</L>
<L N="332">The first vertue sonne if &thorn;ou wilt lere</L>
<L>Is to restreyne &amp; kepe wel &thorn;i tonge</L>
<L>&thorn;us leren childern whan &thorn;e be &yogh;onge</L>
<L>My sonne of Mechel spekeinge yuel avisede</L>
<L N="336">&thorn;ere lasse spekeinge had .I.-nowhe suffised</L>
<L>Come&thorn; mochel harme &thorn;us was me tolde &amp; tauht</L>
<L>In muchel speche&thorn; sinne wante&thorn; nouht</L>
<L>Wostowe where-of a rachel tonge serue&thorn;</L>
<L N="340">Riht as swerde for-kotte&thorn; &amp; for-kerue&thorn;</L>
<L>And arm a tuo . my dere sone riht so</L>
<L>A tunge kutte&thorn; frenschep al a two</L>
<L>A Iangler is to god abhominable</L>
<L N="344">Rede Salomon so wyse &amp; honurable</L>
<L>Rede dauid &amp; his psalmys rede seneke</L>
<L>My sone speke nouht bot wi&thorn; &thorn;ine hede &thorn;u bekke</L>
<L>Dissimule as &thorn;ou were def if &thorn;at &thorn;ou here</L>
<L N="348">A Iangelere speke&thorn; of perilous matere
<PB REF="00000629.tif" N="601"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="587"></L>
<L N="349">The flemynge sei&thorn;e &amp; lerne &yogh;if &thorn;e lest</L>
<L>&THORN;at litel Iangelinge cause&thorn; mechel rest<MILESTONE N="229b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>My sone if &thorn;ou no wykked worde hast seide</L>
<L N="352">&THORN;e &thorn;ar nouht drede for to be bewreide</L>
<L>Bot he &thorn;at ha&thorn; my-saide .I. dare wele seine</L>
<L>He may be no weye clepe his worde a&yogh;eine</L>
<L>&thorn;inge &thorn;at is seide is seide &amp; for&thorn; it go&thorn;e</L>
<L N="356">&thorn;ouhe him repent or be him neuer so lo&thorn;e</L>
<L>He is his &thorn;ral to whome &thorn;at he ha&thorn; seide</L>
<L>A tale of whiche he is nowe yuel apaide</L>
<L>My sone be war &amp; be none auctor newe</L>
<L N="360">Of Ty&thorn;inges whe&thorn;ere &thorn;ei be fals or trewe</L>
<L>Where so &thorn;ou comme amonges hihe or lowe</L>
<L N="362">Kepe wele &thorn;i tonge &amp; &thorn;inke vpon &thorn;e crowe</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>Explicit ffabula Mancipij.</TRAILER>
