<DIV1 N="I" TYPE="group">

<PB REF="00000630.tif" N="602">
<MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="589">
<HEAD>GROUP <B>I.</B> FRAGMENT X.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="tale">
<HEAD>&sect; <B>1.</B> THE BLANK-PARSON LINK. LANSDOWNE MS. <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="229b"> Incipit prologus Rectoris.</HEAD>
<HEADNOTE><P>[This is really a link between some unwritten Tale and the Parson's. It has been made into the Manciple-Parson Link (or Yeoman-Parson by the Christ-Church MS) by Chaucer's copiers, though not meant for it.]</P></HEADNOTE>

<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="1">BE &thorn;at &thorn;e manciple hadde his tale endede</L>
<L>The sonne fro &thorn;e sou&thorn;e side is descendede</L>
<L>So lowe &thorn;at he was nouht to my siht</L>
<L N="4">Degrees nyne &amp; twente as of heiht</L>
<L>Than of &thorn;e clokke it was so as .I. gesse</L>
<L>For a .xj. fote a lite more or lesse</L>
<L>My schadowe was at &thorn;ilke time as &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="8">Of fusche fete as myn lenge&thorn; partide were</L>
<L>In sex foote equale of proporocione</L>
<L>&thorn;ere-wi&thorn;e &thorn;e mones exaltacione</L>
<L>.I. mene libra alweye gan ascende</L>
<L N="12">As we were entrynge att &thorn;e &thorn;ropes ende</L>
<L>For wi&thorn; oure oste as he was wonte to guye</L>
<L>As in &thorn;is caas oure Ioly compaignye</L>
<L>Seide in &thorn;is wise lordeinges euerychone</L>
<L N="16">Now lakke&thorn; vs no tale more &thorn;an one</L>
<L>Fulfilled is my sentence &amp; my degre</L>
<L>Who wil nowe tel a tale latt see</L>
<L>Almost ffulfilled is myne ordenaunce</L>
<L N="20">.I. praie to god . so &yogh;if him riht good chaunce</L>
<L>&thorn;at Telli&thorn; &thorn;is tale to vs lustely.</L>
<L>Sir prist quod he ert &thorn;ou a vicarie</L>
<L>Or ert &thorn;ou a person sei so&thorn;e be &thorn;i feye</L>
<L N="24">Be what &thorn;owe be ne breke &thorn;ou nouht oure pleye
<PB REF="00000631.tif" N="603"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="590"></L>
<L N="25">For euery man saue &thorn;oue ha&thorn;e told his tale</L>
<L>vnbukel and schewe vs what is in &thorn;i male</L>
<L>For treuly me &thorn;inke&thorn; be &thorn;i chere</L>
<L N="28">Thow scholdest knyht vpe wele a grete matier</L>
<L>Tel vs a fable anone for kokkes bones<MILESTONE N="230a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;is persone ansewerd al att ones</L>
<L>&thorn;ou getest fable none ytolde for me</L>
<L N="32">For Poule &thorn;at write&thorn; vn-to Timothe</L>
<L>Repreue&thorn; hem &thorn;at veyfen so&thorn;efastnesse</L>
<L>And tellen fabels &amp; suche wrechednesse</L>
<L>Whi shold .I. schewen draf out of my fest</L>
<L N="36">Whan .I. may schewe whete if &thorn;at me lest</L>
<L>For whiche .I. saie if &thorn;at &thorn;e lust to here</L>
<L>Moralite &amp; vertuous Matiere</L>
<L>And &thorn;an &thorn;at &yogh;e wil &yogh;ef me audience</L>
<L N="40">.I. wil ful feyne att cristes Reuerence</L>
<L>Done &yogh;owe plesance lefful as .I. canne</L>
<L>Bot truste&thorn; wele .I. am a so&thorn;erne manne</L>
<L>.I. can nouht geste. Rom Ram . Ruf be my lettre</L>
<L N="44">Ne god wote Rime holde .I. bot litel better</L>
<L>And &thorn;erefor if &yogh;owe luste .I. wil not glose</L>
<L>.I. wil &yogh;owe tel a mere tale in prose</L>
<L>To knyte vp al &thorn;is fest &amp; maake an ende</L>
<L N="48">An ihesu for his grace witte me sende</L>
<L>To schew &yogh;ow &thorn;e waye in &thorn;is viage</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ilke parfite gloriouse pilgrenage</L>
<L>&THORN;at hiht Ierusalem Celestiall</L>
<L N="52">And if &yogh;e vouche saue a-none &yogh;e schall</L>
<L>Beginne vpon my tale for whiche .I. preye</L>
<L>Tell &yogh;oure avise .I. can no better seye</L>
<L>Bot na&thorn;eles &thorn;is Meditacione</L>
<L N="56">.I. put it alweie in correctione</L>
<L>Of clerkes for .I. am nouht text wele</L>
<L>I take bot &thorn;e sentence truste&thorn; wele</L>
<L>Thare-fore .I. maake a prodestacione</L>
<L N="60">&thorn;at .I. wil stant to correctione
<PB REF="00000632.tif" N="604"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="591"></L>
<L N="61">Vpon &thorn;is worde we haue assented sone</L>
<L>For as it semed it was for to done</L>
<L>To enden in som vertuous sentence</L>
<L N="64">And for to &yogh;eue him space &amp; audience</L>
<L>And badde oure Oste he scholde to him seye</L>
<L>&thorn;at al we to telle his tale we preye</L>
<L>Oure Oste hadde &thorn;e wordes for vs all</L>
<L N="68">Sire preste quod he faire mote &yogh;ow fall</L>
<L>Saye what &yogh;owe lust &amp; we schal gladly here</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; &thorn;at worde he seide in &thorn;is manere.</L>
<L>Telle&thorn; quod he &yogh;oure Meditacione<MILESTONE N="230b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="72">Bot haste&thorn; &yogh;owe &thorn;e sonne wil adoune</L>
<L>Be&thorn; fructuous &amp; &thorn;at in litel space</L>
<L N="74">And to do wele god send &yogh;owe his grace</L>
</LG>
