<PB REF="00000652.tif" N="620"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="606"> &thorn;ei to a-brigge &thorn;e peyne of hell; or elles to geten temporel richesse; [244] or elles &thorn;at god wol &thorn;e ra&thorn;er elumyne &amp; lyhten &thorn;e hert of &thorn;e sinful|man. to have repentance; [245] And eke &thorn;ei aveilen to vsen a man to done goode werkes &thorn;at &thorn;e fende haue &thorn;e lesse powere of his soule [246] &para; And &thorn;us &thorn;e curteise lorde ihesu crist wol &thorn;at no goode werke be lost; ffor in somwhat it schal availe [247] &para; Bot for also muche &thorn;e goode werke &thorn;at men done whiles &thorn;ei bien in goode lif bien al mortified be sinne folowynge; &para; And eke se&thorn;en &thorn;at al &thorn;e goode werkes . . <NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in MS.</NOTE> whiles &thorn;ei bue in dedely sinne bien vtterly dede as for to haue &thorn;e lif perdurable; [248] wele may &thorn;at man &thorn;at no goode werke do&thorn;e singe &thorn;ilke newe fresshe songe; Iay tout perduz mon temps &amp; mon labour [249] &para; For certes sinne bereue&thorn; a man goodnesse of nature; &amp; eke &thorn;e goodnesse of grace; [250] &para; For so&thorn;e &thorn;e grace of &thorn;e holy gost fare&thorn; like fire &thorn;at may not bu ydel; ffor fire faile&thorn; anone as it fo[r]lese&thorn; his worche|inge; . . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> [251] So lese&thorn; &thorn;e sinfulman &thorn;e goodnesse of glorie &thorn;at only is behiht to good men &thorn;at labouren &amp; wirken; [252] wele maie he bu sorie &thorn;an &thorn;at owe&thorn; al his lif to god as longe as he leue&thorn;; ha&thorn;e leued; And eke also longe as he schal leue; &thorn;at no goodenesse ne ha&thorn;e to paye with his dett to god to whome he owe&thorn; al his lif [253] &para; For treste&thorn; wele he schal &yogh;eue acomptes as sei&thorn; sein Bernard. of al &thorn;e goodes &thorn;at haue bu &yogh;ouen him in &thorn;is present lif &amp; howe he ha&thorn;e hem dispended