<PB REF="00000653.tif" N="621"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="607"> of &thorn;e traveyles &thorn;at oure lorde ihesu crist suffred in precheinge; [257] his werenesse in travaileinge; his tempt|acions whan he fasted; his longe wakeinges whan he praide; his teres whan &thorn;at he <MILESTONE N="234b" UNIT="folio">wepte for pyte of goode peple; [258] &thorn;e wor &amp; &thorn;e schame &amp; &thorn;e fil&thorn;e &thorn;at mem seiden to him oft; &thorn;e foule spitteinge; &thorn;at men spitten on his face; of &thorn;e buffetes &thorn;at men &yogh;aue him; of &thorn;e foule mou&thorn;es; &amp; of &thorn;e re|proues &thorn;at men to him seyden; [259] of &thorn;e nayles with &thorn;e whiche he was nailed to &thorn;e crose and of al &thorn;e remenant of his passion &thorn;at he suffred for my sinnes And no&thorn;inge for his gilte; [260] And &yogh;e scholne vnder|stonde &thorn;at in man sinne is euery maner of order of ordinance turned vp so doune; [261] ffor it is so&thorn;e; &thorn;at god. &amp; reson &amp; sensualite &amp; &thorn;e body of man; buen so ordeined; &thorn;at euer yche of &thorn;is foure &thorn;inges schold haue lordschipe ouer &thorn;at o&thorn;er [262] As &thorn;us; As &thorn;us God schold haue lordeschip ouer reson; &amp; resone ouere sensualite; And sensualite ouere &thorn;e body of man; [263] But so&thorn;ely whan man sinne&thorn; al &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> order of ordenance is turned vp so doune; [264] And &thorn;er fore &thorn;an for also muche as &thorn;e reson of man wil nouht be subiette ne obeisant to god &thorn;at is lord be riht; &thorn;ere for lese&thorn; he &thorn;e lordschip &thorn;at he scholde haue in sensualite; and eke ouere &thorn;e body of man; [265] And whie For sensualite rebelle&thorn; a&yogh;ein reson; And &thorn;at waye lese&thorn; reson his lordschip ouer sensualite &amp; ouer &thorn;e body; [266] For riht as reson is rebelle to god; Riht so is bo&thorn;e sensualite rebel to reson. &amp; &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> man also; [267] &para; And c