<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>[The Remedy against Lechery.]</HEAD>
<P>[915] &para; Nowe come&thorn; remedy a&yogh;eines lycherye &amp; &thorn;at is generaly chastite &amp; continence; &thorn;at re|freyne&thorn;. <MILESTONE N="250b" UNIT="folio">al &thorn;e disordeine meueinges &thorn;at comen of flesscly talante&yogh;; [916] And euere &thorn;[e] grete merite shal he haue &thorn;at moste restreyne&thorn; &thorn;e wykkede eschau|feinges of ordur of &thorn;is sinne; &amp; &thorn;is is in tuo maners; &thorn;at is for to seyn; chastite of Mariage &amp; chastite of wydewhede;// [917] Now schalt &thorn;ou knowe &thorn;at matrimony is leful assemblynge of man &amp; womman &thorn;at receyue be vertue of sacrament &thorn;e bande &thorn;oruhe whiche &thorn;ei maie not bu departed al here lif; &thorn;at is to sey whiles &thorn;ei leuen bo&thorn;e; [918] &para; &thorn;is is as sei&thorn;e &thorn;e boke a ful gret sacrament; God maked it as .I. haue seide in paradise; &amp; wolde him self bu borne in mariage; [919] &para; And for to halowen mariage he was at wedynge where as he torned water vnto wyne; whiche was &thorn;e firste miracle &thorn;at he wrouhte here in er&thorn;e befor his deciples; [920] trewe effecte of Mariage clense&thorn; fornicacion; &amp; replenysche&thorn; holy chirche of good lignage; for as &thorn;e ende of Mariage &amp; it chaunge&thorn; dedly sinne in to veniale be-twex hem &thorn;at biene wedded; &amp; make&thorn; &thorn;e hertes alone. . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> [921] &thorn;is is &thorn;e verrey maryage &thorn;at is ystabist be god; ere &thorn;at sinne beganne; whan natural lawe was in his riht pointe in paradise &para; And it ordeynede &thorn;at o m&amacr;n schold haue bot o womman; &amp; o womman bott o m&amacr;n; as sei&thorn; seint Austine be mony resones;</P>
<P>[922] first for &thorn;at Mariage is figured betuex man &amp; 
<PB REF="00000715.tif" N="683"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="669"> holy chirche; And &thorn;at o&thorn;ere is for aman is &thorn;e hede of &thorn;e womman algate be ordinance it scholde be so; [923] &para; For if a womman had mo men &thorn;an one; &thorn;an schold sche haue mo hedes &thorn;an one; &amp; &thorn;at were an orrible &thorn;inge to for god; &para; An eke one womman ne myht nouht pleise to mony folke att ones; And also &thorn;ere ne scholde neuer be pes ne rest amonges hem; ffor eueryche wold axe his owen &thorn;inge; [924] And for&thorn;er more no man schold knowe his owen en|gendrure ne who scholde haue his heritage; And &thorn;e womman scholde &thorn;e lasse be louede ffro &thorn;e time &thorn;at sche were comune to mony men;</P>
<P>[925] &para; Nowe comme&thorn; howe &thorn;at aman scholde bere him wi&thorn; his wif; &amp; namely in tuo &thorn;inges &thorn;at is to seye in suffrance &amp; in reuerence; And &thorn;at schewd first criste whan he maade first womman; [926] ffor he maad hir nouht of &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> hede of Adam for sche scholde nou&yogh;t haue to grete lordschipe; [927] ffor &thorn;ere as &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> womman ha&thorn;e &thorn;e maystre sche make&thorn; to mekel disaraye; &thorn;ere nede none ensamples of &thorn;is &para; Thexperience of &thorn;is day be day ouhte suffice [928] &para; Also certes god ne maad no&yogh;t womman of &thorn;e foote of Adam; ffor sche schold nou&yogh;t be holden to lowe ffor sche cannot paciently suffur;= Bot god maad womman of &thorn;e ribbe of Adam. ffor womman scholde be felawe vnto man; [929] &para; A man schold bere him to his wif in fei&thorn;e in trou&thorn;e &amp; in loue; as sei&thorn;e seint Poule; &thorn;at aman schol loue his wif; As criste loue&thorn; holy chirche &thorn;at loued it so wele &thorn;at he dyed for it; So schal aman for his wif If it were nede</P>
<P>[930] &para; Nowe howe &thorn;at a womman schold be soubiette to her Husbonde &thorn;at telle&thorn; seint Peter; . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> [931] And eke as sei&thorn;e &thorn;e decree. A womman as longe as sche is a wyf sche ha&thorn;e non auctorite to swere ne to bere wittenesse wi&thorn; outen leue of here husbonde &thorn;at is hire lorde it scholde be so by reson; [932] Sche scholde eke serue him in all 
<PB REF="00000716.tif" N="684"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="670"> honeste &amp; ben atempre of here <MILESTONE N="251a" UNIT="folio">araye; I. wote wele &thorn;at &thorn;ei scholden sette hire entente to plese her hus|bondes bot not by here qweyntise of araye; [933] &para; Seint Ierom; sei&thorn;; &thorn;at wyues &thorn;at bien appareled in silke ne mowen nouht clo&thorn;en hem in ihesu criste; . . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> [934] Seint gregori sei&thorn; eke &thorn;at no wight seke&thorn; precious araye bot onely veinglorie to be honoured &thorn;e more to for &thorn;e peple; [935] &para; It is a grete foly a womman to haue a grete araye outewarde and her self bue foule inwarde; [936] A wif scholde eke be mesurable in lokeynge &amp; in bereinge &amp; in lawheinge; &amp; discrete in al here wordes &amp; here dedes; [937] and abouen al werldly &thorn;inges sche scholde loue her housbonde wi&thorn; al her hert; &amp; to him be trewe of hire bodye; [938] So schold an husbond eke be trewe vnto his wif; ffor se&thorn;ine &thorn;at al &thorn;e body is &thorn;e hosbondes; so schold her hertes bien; Or elles &thorn;ere is be tuex hem tuo; as in &thorn;at no parfit mariage [939] &para; &thorn;an schal aman vnder|stonde &thorn;at for &thorn;re &thorn;inges aman &amp; his wif aman &amp; his wif mowen assemblen; &para; &thorn;e first is in entente of engen|drure of children to &thorn;e seruice of god; &para; For certes &thorn;at is &thorn;e cause fynal of Matrymoyne; [940] Ano&thorn;ere is to &yogh;elde eueryche of hem to o&thorn;ere &thorn;e dette of his bodye; ffor ney&thorn;ere of hem ha&thorn; powere of his owen bodye; The &thorn;redde is to eschiew lichery &amp; velanye; &para; &thorn;e fer&thorn;e forso&thorn;e is dedly sinne; [941] &para; As to &thorn;e first it is meritorye; = &thorn;e secunde also; ffor as sei&thorn;e &thorn;e decree. &para; &thorn;at chasi&thorn; merite of chastite &thorn;at &yogh;elde&thorn; to her husbonde &thorn;e dette of hire bodye; &yogh;e &thorn;ouhe it be a&yogh;eine hir lykeinge &amp; &thorn;e lust of here herte; [942] &para; &thorn;e &thorn;red manere is veniale An trewly scarcely maye any of &thorn;es bue with outen venial sinne for &thorn;e corrupcion &amp; for &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> delite; [943] &para; &thorn;e fer&thorn;e manere is for to vnderstonde; and if &thorn;e assemble onelye for amerous loue &amp; for none of &thorn;e forseide causes bot 
<PB REF="00000717.tif" N="685"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="671"> for accomplice &thorn;ilke birneinge delite; &thorn;ei rekken neuer howe often so&thorn;ely it is a dedely synne; &para; And &yogh;itte with sorwe som folke will peynen hem more &thorn;an her appetite suffri&thorn;;</P>
<P>[944] &para; &thorn;e secunde Manere of chastie; is to be aclene wydowe &amp; to eschewe &thorn;enbraseinge of man; &amp; to desiren &thorn;enbrasinges of ihesu crist; [945] &para; Thes bien &thorn;o &thorn;at haue bue wyves; &amp; haue for gone here hus|bondes &para; And eke wemmen &thorn;at haue done lycherye &amp; bien releued by penance; [946] And certez if &thorn;at a wif cou&thorn;e keper al chaste be lycence of hire husbonde so &thorn;at sche nere none occasion &thorn;at he a-gilte it were to hire a grete merite; [947] &para; Thes manere of wemmen &thorn;at obseruen chastite moste bue clene in herte as wele as in body; &amp; in &thorn;ouht; &amp; mesurable in clo&thorn;einge &amp; in countenance; Abstinent in etynge &amp; drinkeinge in spekeinge // &amp; in dede; &amp; &thorn;an is sche &thorn;e vessel of &thorn;e boyste of &thorn;e blissed Magdalene &thorn;at fulfille&thorn; holy chirche ful of good odoure; [948] &para; &thorn;e &thorn;redde maner chastite is virginite; &para; And it be-houe&thorn; &thorn;at sche be holy in herte &amp; clene of body; &thorn;an is sche spouse to ihesu crist; &para; And sche is &thorn;e lif of Angels; [949] sche is &thorn;e preiseinge of &thorn;is werld; And sche is as &thorn;es martires in Regalite; Sche ha&thorn;e in hire &thorn;at tunge may not tell; [950] virginite bare oure lorde ihesu crist &amp; virgine was him self;</P>
<P>[951] &para; Ano&thorn;ere remede a&yogh;eines licherie is to wi&thorn; draw suche &thorn;inges &thorn;at &yogh;euen occacion to &thorn;ilke velany; As ese. &amp; eteynge &amp; drinkeinge; ffor certez whan. <MILESTONE N="251b" UNIT="folio">&thorn;e potte boyle&thorn; strongelye &thorn;e best remedye is to with|drawe &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> fire; [952] Slepeinge lange in grete quiete is eke a grete norische to licherye;</P>
<P>[953] &para; Ano&thorn;ere remedye a&yogh;eines lycherie is &thorn;at a womman or a man eschiewe compaignye of hem be wiche he doute&thorn; to be tempted; ffor albeit so &thorn;at &thorn;e dede be with-stande &yogh;ite is &thorn;ere grete temptacione; 
<PB REF="00000718.tif" N="686"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="672"> [954] So&thorn;ely a white wall al&thorn;ouhe it birne nouht ffully be stykynge of a candel; &yogh;it is &thorn;e wal blakke of &thorn;e leyte [955] ful oft time; &para; .I. rede &thorn;at noman truste in his owen perfeccione; bot he be st[r]onger &thorn;an Sampson. Holiere &thorn;an Dauid. wiser &thorn;an Salomon</P>
<P>[956] &para; Nowe after &thorn;at .I. haue declared &yogh;owe as .I. can of &thorn;e vij. dedely sinnes and sume of here braunches &amp; her remedies; So&thorn;e if; y. cou&thorn;e .I. wolde tel &yogh;owe &thorn;e ten. commandementes; [957] Bot so hihe a dottrine .I. lete to devines; Na&thorn;eles .I. hope to god &thorn;ei bien touched in &thorn;is tretise eueryche of hem all</P>
