<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>De .2<SUP>a</SUP>. part penitencie</HEAD>
<P>[958]</P>
<P>NOw for as muche as &thorn;e secunde parte of penite; stant in confessioun of mou&thorn;e; as .I. began in &thorn;e chapetre; I. seye seint Austine sei&thorn;e; [959] Sinne is euery worde &amp; euery dede &amp; al &thorn;at men coueyten a&yogh;eines &thorn;e lawe of ihesu criste; and &thorn;is for to sinne in herte in mou&thorn;e &amp; in dede. be &thorn;ine .v. wittes &thorn;at bien siht hereinge smelinge tasteinge or saueringe &amp; feleinge. [960] &para; Nowe is it goode to vnderstond &thorn;e circumstance &thorn;at aggregen muchel euery sinne [961] &para; &thorn;ou schalt consider what &thorn;ou ert &thorn;at dost &thorn;e sinne whe&thorn;ere &thorn;ou be male or female. &yogh;onge or olde. gentil or &thorn;rall. free or seruant hole or seke; wedded or sengel. orderde or nou&yogh;t wise or fool. Clerke or seculer; [962] if sche be of &thorn;i kinred bodely or gostely or none; If any of &thorn;i kinred haue sinned wi&thorn; hire or none; &amp; mony moo &thorn;inges;</P>
<P>[963] &para; &thorn;e o&thorn;ere circumstance is &thorn;is; whe&thorn;er it be done in fornicacione or none; Or in aduoutre; or inceste or none; Mayden or none; In manere of homicide or none orrible grete sinne or smal. An howe longe &thorn;ou continued in sinne = [964] &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> &thorn;red circumstance is &thorn;e place where &thorn;ou haste done sinne; Whe&thorn;ere in o&thorn;ere 
<PB REF="00000719.tif" N="687"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="673"> mennes hous or in &thorn;ine owen In felde or in cherche or in chirche hawe In chirche dedicate or none; [965] For if &thorn;e cherche were halowed and man or womman spilled his kinde in wi&thorn; &thorn;at place be waye of sinne or be wykked temptacione &thorn;e chirche were enterdited; til it were reconsiled be &thorn;e Bischop; [966] And &thorn;e priste scholde be enterdited &thorn;at dide suche a velanye to terme of al his lif; he scholde no more singe masse; &amp; if he dide he schold do dedely sinne; att euery time at euery time att he sange masse; [967] &para; &thorn;e fer&thorn;e circumstance is be whiche mediat|ours as be messangeres or for enticement or for enticement or for consentment to bere compaigne wi&thorn; felawschipe; ffor mony a wrecche for to bere compaigny wil go to &thorn;e deuel of hell [968] &para; For &thorn;ei &thorn;at eggen or con|senten to &thorn;e sinne bien partiners of &thorn;e sinne &amp; of &thorn;e dampnacion of &thorn;e sinner</P>
<P>[969] &para; &thorn;e .v. is; howe monye times &thorn;at he ha&thorn; sinned; &amp; it be in his mynde; &amp; howe oft &thorn;at he ha&thorn;e fall; [970] ffor he &thorn;at oft falle&thorn; in sinne dispice&thorn; &thorn;e mercie of god; And encrese&thorn; his sinne &amp; is vnkinde to god; &amp; he wexe&thorn; &thorn;e more feble to wi&thorn;stonde sinne; and sinne&thorn; &thorn;e more lyhtlyer [971] <MILESTONE N="252a" UNIT="folio">and &thorn;e latter arise&thorn;; and is &thorn;e more eschewe to schriven him &amp; namely to him &thorn;at ha&thorn;e bue his Con|fessour;// [972] ffor whiche &thorn;at folke when &thorn;ei fall a&yogh;eine in here olde folyes oft &thorn;ei for-leten here confessours al vtterlye or elles &thorn;ei departen her scrift in diuers place; Bot so&thorn;ely suche departed schrift deseue&thorn; no mercy of god of his sinnes; [973] &para; &thorn;e vj<SUP>e</SUP>. Circum|stance is &thorn;is; whi &thorn;at a man sinne&thorn; as be whiche temptacion; And if him self procure &thorn;ilk temptacione or be ex|citinge of o&thorn;ere folke or if &thorn;ou sinne wi&thorn; a womman be force or be hir owen assent [974] or if &thorn;e womman mawgre hire hede ha&thorn;e bue enforced or none &thorn;is schal &yogh;e tell; ffor couetise or for pouerte; &amp; if it was here procureinge or none &amp; suche manere 
<PB REF="00000720.tif" N="688"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="674"> harneys [975] &para; &thorn;e .vij. circumstance is in what manere he ha&thorn; done his sinne or none or howe &thorn;at he ha&thorn; suffryd howe folke han don to hire; [976] of &thorn;e same schal &thorn;e man tel pleynely al circumstance &amp; where he ha&thorn; sinned; with commune bordel wymmen or none [977] or done his sinne in holy times or none; in fast|inge times or none or be-forne his schrift or aftere his latter schrift [978] &amp; ha&thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> par aduenture broken &thorn;ere-fore his penance enioyned. by whos &amp; whos consel. by sorcery or craft; al must be tolde [979] &thorn;es &thorn;inges after &thorn;at &thorn;ei bien grete &amp; smale Engregen &thorn;e conscience of man; &amp; eke &thorn;e &thorn;reste &thorn;at is &thorn;i Iuge may &thorn;e better bue avised of his Iugement in &yogh;eueinge of &thorn;ine penaunce; And &thorn;at is after &thorn;ine contricione; [980] &para; For vnderstande&thorn; wele &thorn;at after &thorn;e time &thorn;at aman ha&thorn;e defouled his Baptime by sinne if he wil comme to saluacion; &thorn;ere is none o&thorn;ere weye bot be penytence &amp; schrift &amp; satisfactione. [981] And namely by &thorn;o tuo; if &thorn;ere be a confessour to whiche he may schriue him &para; And &thorn;e &thorn;red if he haue lif to performe it;</P>
<P>[982] &thorn;an schal man loke &amp; consider if he wil make a trewe &amp; profitable confessione &thorn;ere moste bue foure condiciones; = [983] Firste it must be in sorwful bitternesse of hert &para; As sei&thorn;e &thorn;e kinge ezechiel; = To god .I. wil remembre me al &yogh;e &yogh;eres of my lif in bitternesse of myne herte; [984] &para; &thorn;is condicioun of bitter|nesse ha&thorn;e .v. signes; &thorn;e first is &thorn;at confession most be schamefaste not for to kouerne ne to hiden his sinne; = bot for he ha&thorn; a-gilte his god &amp; defouled his soule; [985] And here of sei&thorn; seinte Austine; &para; The hert travaile&thorn; for schame of his sinne; &amp; for he ha&thorn;e grete schamfastnes he is digne to haue grete mercye; [986] whiche was &thorn;e confession of &thorn;e puplicane &thorn;at wolde not heue vp his ey&yogh;en to heuen; ffor he hadde offended god of heuen; ffor whiche schamfastnesse he had anone &thorn;e mercy of god [987] &para; And &thorn;erefore sei&thorn; 
<PB REF="00000721.tif" N="689"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="675"> seint Austine. &thorn;at suche schamefast folke bien next for-&yogh;euenesse &amp; remission [988] &para; &thorn;at o&thorn;ere signe is humilite of confessione; of whiche sei&thorn;e seint Petre. Vmble&thorn; &yogh;ow vnder &thorn;e miht of of god; &para; &thorn;e honde of god is myhti in confession; For &thorn;ereby god fo[r]&yogh;eue&thorn; &thorn;e sinnes; for he alon ha&thorn; &thorn;e powere; [989] &amp; &thorn;is humylite schal be in herte &amp; in signe outewarde; For riht as he ha&thorn; humylite to god in his herte. Riht so schold he humblen his body outwarde to &thorn;e preste &thorn;at sitte&thorn; in <MILESTONE N="252b" UNIT="folio">goddes place; [990] for whiche in no maner se&thorn;en &thorn;at crist is souereigne; &amp; &thorn;e preste mene &amp; mediatour be tuex criste &amp; &thorn;e sinner; And &thorn;e sinner is &thorn;e last be weie of resoun; [991] &thorn;an scholde not &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> sinner sitte also hihe as his confessour bot knele be-forne him or att his fete bot if malady distourbe it; for he schal not take kepe who sitte&thorn; &thorn;ere bot in wos place &thorn;at he sitte&thorn;; [992] &para; A man &thorn;at ha&thorn; trespassed to alorde &amp; comme&thorn;e to axe mercye; &amp; maken his accorde &amp; sitte him doune anone by &thorn;e lorde; men wolde holde him outrageous &amp; nouht wor&thorn;i so sone to haue remissione ne mercye; [993] &para; &thorn;e .iij. signe is &thorn;at &thorn;i schrift scholde be ful of teres if man may wepe; And if man maie not wepe wi&thorn; his bodely ey&yogh;en lat him wepe in his herte; [994] Suche was &thorn;e confessione of seinte Peter; ffor after &thorn;at he hadde for saake ihesu criste he went oute &amp; weppet ful bitterly; [995] &para; &thorn;e; iiij. signe is &thorn;at he let not for his schame to schewe his confessione. [996] Suche was &thorn;e confession of &thorn;e Magdaleyn for sche spared for no schame of hem &thorn;at weren att &thorn;e fest for to go to oure lorde ihesu criste; &amp; be-knowe to him hire sinne [997] &para; &thorn;e .v.<SUP>te</SUP> signe &thorn;at aman or womman be obeisant to receyue &thorn;e penance &thorn;at is him enioynede; &para; For certes ihesu criste for &thorn;e giltes of o man was obediente to &thorn;e de&thorn;e</P>
<P>[998] &para; &thorn;e secunde condicion of verreye confessi[on] is &thorn;at it be hastily done; For certes if aman had a dedly wounde euer &thorn;e langer &thorn;at he tarie&thorn; to warische 
<PB REF="00000722.tif" N="690"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="676"> him self; &thorn;e more wolde it corrupte; and haste him to his de&thorn;e &amp; eke &thorn;e wounde wolde be &thorn;e wers for to hele;// [999] And riht so fare&thorn; sinne &thorn;at longe time is in a man vnschewde; [1000] Certes aman ouht hastely to schewe his sinne for mony cause as for drede of de&thorn;e &thorn;at comme&thorn; oft sodanly; &amp; is in no certeine what time it schal be ne in no place; and eke &thorn;e drecchinge of o sinne drawe&thorn; ine ano&thorn;ere [1001] &amp; eke &thorn;e longer &thorn;at he tarie&thorn; &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> fer&thorn;ere is he fro criste; &amp; if he abide vnto his last daye skarsly may he schriue him or amend him for his sinnes or repent him for &thorn;e greuous malady of his de&thorn;e; [1002] &para; And for as muche as he ha&thorn; nouhte in his lif herkened ihesu criste whan he ha&thorn;e spoken vn to him; he schal crien vnto oure lorde ihesu criste att his last daye; And scarsely wil he herken him [1003] &para; Vnder stonde &thorn;at &thorn;is condicione most haue foure &thorn;inges; &thorn;i schrift moste bien purveide be-forne &amp; avised; = for wykked haste do&thorn;e no prophete &amp; &thorn;at aman con schriue him. of his sinnes be it of pride ey&thorn;ere of envie; An so for&thorn;e wi&thorn; &thorn;e spices &amp; &thorn;e circumstaunces; [1004] And &thorn;at he haue comprehended in his mynde &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> nombre &amp; &thorn;e gretnesse of his sinnes; &amp; howe longe &thorn;at he ha&thorn; leyne in sinne [1005] &amp; eke &thorn;at he bue contrite of his sinnes; And in stedfast purpos by &thorn;e grace of god neuere efte to fal a-&yogh;eine in sinne; And eke &thorn;at he drede &amp; contrewaite him self &thorn;at he flie &thorn;e occasione of sinne to whiche he is enclined. [1006] &para; Also &thorn;at &thorn;ou schal schriue &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> of al &thorn;i sinnes to oman; &amp; nouht parcel mele to oman &amp; parcel mele to a no&thorn;ere man; &thorn;at is to vnderstonde in entent to parten &thorn;ine confessione as for schame or drede; for it is bot<MILESTONE N="253a" UNIT="folio"> bot stranglinge of &thorn;ine soule &para; [1007] For certes ihesu criste is al goode; In him is none imperfeccione; &amp; &thorn;erfore euer he for-&yogh;eue&thorn; perfytlye or elles neuer a dele. [1008] &para; I saye note if &thorn;ou be assigned to &thorn;e penitancere of certeyne sinne &thorn;at &thorn;ou ert bounden to schew him al &thorn;e remenant of &thorn;<SUP>i</SUP> sinnes of whiche 
<PB REF="00000723.tif" N="691"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="677"> &thorn;ou hast bue schreuen att &thorn;i Curate; bot if it like &thorn;e of &thorn;ine humylite &para; &thorn;is is no depar[t]inge of schreft; = [1009] ne .I. saye not &thorn;ere as .I. speke of diuision of confes|sione if &thorn;at &thorn;ou haue lycence for to schriue &thorn;e to a discrete &amp; an honeste preste; &amp; where &thorn;e like&thorn;e // &amp; be &thorn;e licence eke of &thorn;ine curate &thorn;at &thorn;ou ne maiste wel schriue &thorn;e of al &thorn;i sinnes [1010] bot late no blot bue by-hinde; lete no sinne vntolde as fer as &thorn;ou haste remem|brance; [1011] &para; And whan &thorn;ou schalte bu schriuen of &thorn;<SUP>i</SUP> Curate. Tel him eke of al &thorn;e sinnes &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast done; se&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;ou were last y-schryuen; as &thorn;is is &thorn;e wikked entent of deuysion of schrift</P>
<P>[1012] &para; Also &thorn;e verrey schrift axe&thorn; certeyne con|diciones.= First &thorn;at &thorn;ou schriue &thorn;e be &thorn;i fre wyl nouht constreyned ne for schame of folke ne for malady or suche &thorn;inges; &para; For it is reson &thorn;at he &thorn;at trespas be his fre will . . . . <NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> confesse his trespace; [1013] None o&thorn;ere man schatel his sinne bot he him self; ne schal no&yogh;t nay it or denye his sinne; ne wre&thorn;&thorn;e hime a&yogh;eines &thorn;e preste for his amonyscheynge to lete sinne [1014] &para; &thorn;e condicion is &thorn;at &thorn;i schrift be lawful; &thorn;at is to sey &thorn;ou &thorn;at schryue&thorn; &thorn;e; &amp; eke &thorn;e preste &thorn;at here&thorn; &thorn;<SUP>i</SUP> confession bien verrei in &thorn;e fay&thorn;e of holy cherche [1015] &para; And &thorn;at aman be nouht despeirede of &thorn;e mercie of ihesu criste; as Kayme or Iudas [1016] &para; And eke aman most accuse him of his owen trespas; &amp; nouht a no&thorn;ere; bot he schal blame &amp; wyten him self of his owen malice of his sinne &amp; none o&thorn;ere [1017] Bot na&thorn;eles if ano&thorn;ere man bue encheson or entyse&thorn; of his sinnes; Or &thorn;at if &thorn;e state of a persone bu suche &thorn;oruhe whiche his sinne is agregede or elles &thorn;at he may not pleynely schriuen him bot he tel &thorn;e persone whiche he ha&thorn;e sinned wi&thorn; &thorn;en maye he tel it [1018] so &thorn;at is entent ne be not to bakbite &thorn;e person; bot onely to declare his con|fession;
<PB REF="00000724.tif" N="692"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="678"></P>
<P>[1019] &thorn;ou schalt not eke make no lesinge in &thorn;i confessione; ffor humilite peraduenture to seie &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast done sinnes of whiche &thorn;ou were neuer gilte [1020] &para; For seinte sei&thorn;e; If &thorn;ou because of humylite makest lesinge of &thorn;i self &thorn;ouhe &thorn;ou ne were nou&yogh;t in sinne a forne &yogh;it ert &thorn;ou &thorn;an in sinne &thorn;oruhe &thorn;i lessinges [1021] &para; &thorn;ou muste eke schewe &thorn;i sinne by &thorn;i propre mou&thorn;e bot &thorn;ou be wax domme; &amp; nouht be no letter; ffor &thorn;ou &thorn;at hast don sinne &thorn;ou schalt haue &thorn;e same confesse [1022] &para; &thorn;ou schalt nou&yogh;t eke peynte &thorn;i confession be faire &amp; subtile wordes to keuer &thorn;e more &thorn;i sinne; ffor &thorn;an begiles &thorn;ou &thorn;i self &amp; not &thorn;e priste; &thorn;ou most tel it platlye be it neuere so foule ne so orrible; [1023] &thorn;ou schalt schriue &thorn;e eke to a priste &thorn;at is discrete to counseil &thorn;e; &amp; eke &thorn;ou schalt nouht schriue &thorn;e for veyne glorye ne for ypocrisye ne for no cause bott onely for &thorn;e deute of ihesu criste; &amp; &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> hele of &thorn;i soule; [1024] &para; &thorn;ou schalt not eke rinne to &thorn;e priste al sodenly to tel him &thorn;ine sinne as who so telle&thorn; a Iape or a tale; bo avysyly &amp; wi&thorn;e grete deuocyon; [1025] &amp; generaly schriue &thorn;e ofte. <MILESTONE N="253b" UNIT="folio">if often fall of arise be confessione; [1026] &amp; if &thorn;ou schriue &thorn;e ofter &thorn;an ones of sinne of whiche &thorn;ou haste bue schryuen it is &thorn;e more merite &amp; as sei&thorn;e seint Austine; &thorn;ou schalte haue &thorn;e more lyhtly relesinge &amp; &thorn;e grace of god bo&thorn;e of sinne &amp; of peyne; [1027] An certes ones a &yogh;ere att &thorn;e lest weye it is lawful for to bue houselde; for so&thorn;ely ones al &thorn;inges renouellen;</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>De Satisfaccione</HEAD>
<P>[1028]</P>
<P>NOw haue .I. tolde of verrey confession &thorn;at is &thorn;e secunde parte of penitence;
<PB REF="00000725.tif" N="693"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="679"></P>
<P>[1029] &para; &thorn;e &thorn;redde parte of penitence is satisfaccione; &amp; &thorn;at stant generaly in almes &amp; in bodely peyne; [1030] Nowe bien &thorn;ere. &thorn;rey manere of almes; contricion of hert &thorn;at a man openne&thorn; him self to god; Ano&thorn;ere; is to haue pete of &thorn;e defaute of his neyhbours; &para; &thorn;e &thorn;red is in &yogh;eueinge good counsel &amp; comfort gostly &amp; bodelye where men haue nede; &amp; namely in sustinance of mannes foode; [1031] &amp; take kepe &thorn;at a man ha&thorn;e nede of &thorn;es &thorn;inges generaly; he ha&thorn;e nede of foode of clo&thorn;inge of herboruhe; he ha&thorn;e nede of charitable conselyng &amp; avisetinge in prison; &amp; maladye; &amp; sepulture of his dede bodye; [1032] &amp; if &thorn;ou maiste not viset &thorn;e nedefoll wi&thorn; &thorn;i persone; viset him wi&thorn; messages &amp; &thorn;i &yogh;eftes;// [1033] &thorn;es bien &thorn;e general almes &amp; werkes of charite of hem &thorn;at ha&thorn; Temperel riches or discrecion in counselinge; &para; Of &thorn;es werkes schalt &thorn;ou here of &thorn;e daie of dome;</P>
<P>[1034] &thorn;es almos schal &thorn;ou done of &thorn;ine owen propre &thorn;inges; And hastely &amp; priuely if &thorn;ou maiste [1035] &para; Bot na&thorn;eles if &thorn;ou maye nouht done hit priuelye &thorn;ou schalt nouht for bere to done almos nere adel &thorn;ouhe men it see; So &thorn;at it be nouht ydo for &thorn;e &thorn;onke of &thorn;e werlde; bot onely to haue &thorn;e &thorn;onke of oure lorde ihesu crist &para; [1036] For as wittenesse seint Mathewe .5. A Cite maie not bue hidde &thorn;at is on a mowntan sette; Ne men lyhten not a lanterne; &amp; put it vnder a buschell; bot men sette&thorn; it on a candel|stik to lyhten &thorn;e men in &thorn;e house; [1037] Riht so schal &yogh;oure liht aforne men &thorn;at &thorn;ei maie seene &yogh;oure good werkes; and glorifien &yogh;oure fader &thorn;at is in heuen</P>
<P>[1038] &para; Nowe as to speke of bodely peine it stant in preyer. in wakeinges in fastinge &amp; in vertuus 
<PB REF="00000726.tif" N="694"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="680"> techeinge of orisons [1039] &para; &YOGH;e schol vnder stonde &thorn;at orisons or preyers is for to seye a pytous wil of hert &thorn;at redresse&thorn; in god &amp; expresse&thorn; be worde outewarde to remowe harmes; &amp; to haue &thorn;inges espirituel &amp; durable; &amp; somtyme temperal &thorn;inges of whiche orisones; certez in &thorn;e orsones of &thorn;e pater noster ha&thorn;e ihesu criste enclosed most &thorn;inges; [1040] Certes it is priueleged of &thorn;rey &thorn;inges in his dignite For whiche it is more digne &thorn;an any o&thorn;ere preyere; ffor &thorn;at ihesu crist him self maked it; [1041] &amp; it is schorte for it scholde be konde more lihtlye &amp; for to wi&thorn;e-holde it more esily in herte; &amp; helpen hem self &thorn;offter wi&thorn; &thorn;orison; [1042] And for aman schold be &thorn;e lasse were to sey it; And for a man may nouht excusen him to leren it for it is so schort &amp; so Esye &amp; for it comprehendi&thorn; in it selfe al goode preyers; [1043] &para; &thorn;e exposicioun of &thorn;is holy preyer &thorn;at is so excellent &amp; digne .I. be-take to &thorn;es Maystres of Theologie saue &thorn;us muche wil .I. seyne; &thorn;at whan &thorn;ou preyest. <MILESTONE N="254a" UNIT="folio">&thorn;at god schold for &yogh;euen &thorn;e &thorn;i giltes as &thorn;ou for&yogh;euest ham<NOTE PLACE="marg">[MS. h<SUP>a</SUP>m]</NOTE> &thorn;at agilten &thorn;e be ful wil; war &thorn;at &thorn;ou be not oute of charite; [1044] &para; &thorn;is holy orison amenuse&thorn; eke venyal sinne; And &thorn;erefor it appertene&thorn; specialy to penytence;</P>
<P>[1045] &para; &thorn;is preyer most bu trewly seide in verray fai&thorn;e &amp; &thorn;at men prey to god ordinately; dis|cretely &amp; deuoutely; &para; Alweye aman schal put his wille to be subiecte to &thorn;e wil of god; [1046] &para; &thorn;is orison most eke be seide with grete humblesse &amp; pure honestly. &amp; nouht to anoyance of any man; or womman. &para; It moste eke be continued with &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> werkes of charite; = [1047] It avayle&thorn; eke a&yogh;eynes &thorn;e vices of &thorn;e soule; &para; For as sei&thorn;e seint Ierom; Be fastinge bien saued &thorn;e vices of flesche; &amp; be preiers &thorn;e vices of soule;</P>
<P>[1048] After &thorn;is &thorn;ou schalt vnderstand &thorn;at bodely peyne stant in wakeynge; &para; For ihesu criste sei&thorn;e; wake&thorn; &amp; praye&thorn; &thorn;at &yogh;e ne enter in wikked 
<PB REF="00000727.tif" N="695"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="681"> temptacione. [1049] &yogh;e scholn vnder stand &thorn;at ffast|inge stant in &thorn;re &thorn;inges; = In for beringe of bodely mete &amp; drinke; &amp; in for beringe of werldly Iolytees; &amp; in for|beringe of dedely sinne; &thorn;is is to seye &thorn;at aman schal kepe him fro dedely sinne; wi&thorn; al his myht;</P>
<P>[1050] &para; And &thorn;ou schalt vnderstand eke &thorn;at god ordeyned fastinges; And to fastinges appartenen .iiij. &thorn;inges; [1051] largenesse to pouer folke; Gladnesse of hert espirituel: nou&yogh;ht to be angred ne to be anoyed; ne to grocche for he faste&thorn;; and also att resonable owre for to ete be mesure; &thorn;at is to saye &thorn;at aman schold nouht eten in vntyme ne sitte &thorn;e langer att his table for he faste&thorn;;</P>
<P>[1052] &para; &thorn;an schalt &thorn;ou vnderstand &thorn;at bodely peyne stant in discipline or techeinge be worde or be writeinge; or by ensample; Also in wereinge of heyres ey&thorn;ere of Stamyne; ey&thorn;[er]e of haberione on here naked flesshe for criste sake &amp; suche manere penaunces; [1053] Bot ware &thorn;e wele &thorn;at suche manere penaunces make nou&yogh;t &thorn;ine herte bitter or angry anoyed of &thorn;ine self &para; For better is to kast awaie &thorn;ine heire &thorn;an for to cast awey &thorn;e swettnes of oure lorde; ihesu criste [1054] &para; And &thorn;erefore sei&thorn;e seinte poule; Clo&thorn;e &yogh;owe as &thorn;ei &thorn;at bien chosen of god in hert of mysericorde debonarte; suffrance. And suche maner of clo&thorn;inge; of whiche ihesu criste is more appaied &thorn;an of heyre or of Aberion;</P>
<P>[1055] &para; &thorn;an is discipline eke in knokynge on &thorn;<SUP>i</SUP> breste; in scouregeinge with &yogh;erdes in knelyinge in tribulacions; [1056] In suffringe paciently wronges &thorn;at bien done to him; &amp; eke in pacient suffrance of Maledies or lesinge of werldly Catel; or wyf or childe or o&thorn;ere frendes;</P>
<P>[1057] &para; &thorn;an schal &thorn;ou vnderstande wiche &thorn;inge distourben penance; &amp; &thorn;is is in &thorn;re maners &thorn;at is drede schame hope; &amp; wanhope; &thorn;at is desperacione; [1058] And for to speken firste of drede; for whiche he 
<PB REF="00000728.tif" N="696"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="682"> wene&thorn; &thorn;at he may suffur no penaunce [1059] &thorn;ere a&yogh;eines is remedye for to &thorn;inke &thorn;at bodely penaunce is bot schort &amp; lytel att &thorn;e regard of &thorn;e peyne of hell &thorn;at is cruel &amp; so longe &thorn;at it laste&thorn; wi&thorn; outen ende;</P>
<P>[1060] &para; Now a&yogh;eines &thorn;e schame &thorn;at aman ha&thorn;e to schryuen him; . . . . .<NOTE PLACE="inline">no gap in the MS.</NOTE> [1061] A&yogh;eines &thorn;e schame schal a man &thorn;inke &thorn;at by &thorn;e waye of resoun &thorn;at he &thorn;at ha&thorn;e nouht bue aschamed to do foule &thorn;inges; Certes him ouhte not <MILESTONE N="254b" UNIT="folio">bue aschamed to do faire &thorn;inges &amp; goode &thorn;inges; &amp; &thorn;at is confessions; [1062] Aman schold &thorn;inke &thorn;at god se&thorn;e &amp; wote al his &thorn;ouhtes &amp; his werkes; to him maie no&thorn;inge bu hudde ne couerde; [1063] Men scholde eke remembre hem of &thorn;e schame &thorn;at is to come att &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> daie of dome to hem &thorn;at biene nou&yogh;t penitence &amp; lif in present lif; [1064] &para; For al &thorn;e creatures in heuen in er&thorn;e &amp; in hell scholne seen apertely al &thorn;at hiden in &thorn;is werlde;</P>
<P>[1065] Nowe for to speke of &thorn;e hope of hem &thorn;at bien so neclygent &amp; slowe to schriuen ham it stant in tuo maners; [1066] &thorn;at on is; &thorn;at he hope&thorn; to leue longe; &amp; for to purchase muchel riches for his delite &amp; &thorn;an he wil schriue hime as he sei&thorn;e; he maie as him seme&thorn; timely ynouhe comme to schrifte; [1067] &para; Ano&thorn;ere is of &thorn;e surquydrye &thorn;at he ha&thorn;e in ha&thorn;e in cristes mercye; [1068] And a&yogh;eines &thorn;e first he schal &thorn;inke &thorn;at oure lif is in no sekernesse; &amp; eke &thorn;at al &thorn;e reches in &thorn;e werlde bien in aduenture &amp; passinge as a schadowe on a wal [1069] &para; And as sei&thorn;e seinte Gregorie; &thorn;at it appartene&thorn; to &thorn;e grete rihtwisnesse of god; &thorn;at neuere schal &thorn;e peine stinte of hem &thorn;at neuere wolde withdrawe hem fro sinne here &thorn;ankes bot euer continue in sinne; &para; For &thorn;ilke perpetuele wil to do sinne scholne &thorn;ei haue perpetuel peyne;</P>
<P>[1070] &para; Whanhope is in tuo maners &para; &thorn;e first whan|hope is in &thorn;e mercye of criste; &thorn;at o&thorn;ere is &thorn;at &thorn;ei 
<PB REF="00000729.tif" N="697"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="683"> &thorn;enke &thorn;at &thorn;ei myht nouht longe perseuerne in good|nesse; [1071] &para; &thorn;e first wanhope comme&thorn; of &thorn;at he deme&thorn; &thorn;at he ha&thorn; sinned so gretely; so ofte &amp; so longe lyggen in sinne &thorn;at he schal nouht be sauede; [1072] &para; Certe&yogh; a&yogh;eines &thorn;at cursed wanhope he schold &thorn;inke &thorn;at &thorn;e passion of ihesu criste is more stronge for to vnbynde; &thorn;an sinne is for to binde; [1073] &para; And a&yogh;eines &thorn;e secunde wanhope; he schal &thorn;inke &thorn;at as oft as he falle&thorn;e he schal arisen be penitence; And &thorn;ouhe he neuer so longe haue lyen in sinne; &thorn;e mercye of criste is alwey redy to receyuen him to mercye; [1074] &para; A&yogh;eynes &thorn;e wanhope &thorn;at he deme&thorn; &thorn;at he schold nouht longe perseuere in goodnes; He schal &thorn;inke &thorn;at &thorn;e febelne of &thorn;e deuel may no&thorn;inge done bot men wil suffren him; [1075] &para; And eke he schal haue streynke&thorn; of god &amp; of al holy chirche &amp; of &thorn;e proteccions of Angels if him luste;</P>
<P>[1076] &para; &thorn;an schol men vndirstande what is &thorn;e fruyte of penaunce as after &thorn;e worde of ihesu criste; It is &thorn;e Endeles blisse of heuen [1077] &thorn;ere Ioye ha&thorn;e none contrariouste of woo ne greuance &thorn;ere all harmes bien passed of &thorn;is present lif; = &thorn;ere as is &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> sekernesse fro &thorn;e peyne of hell; = &thorn;ere as &thorn;e blisful compaignie &thorn;at reioysen hem euermore; Eueryche of o&thorn;eres Ioye; [1078] &thorn;ere as &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> body of man &thorn;at whilom was foule &amp; derke; is more clere &thorn;an is &thorn;e sonne &para; &thorn;ere as whilom &thorn;e body was seeke &amp; frele; &amp; mortale is vnmortale; &amp; so strange &amp; so hole; &thorn;at &thorn;ere maye no &thorn;inge empeyre it; [1079] &thorn;ere as ney&thorn;ere is hunger &thorn;urst ne colde; Bot euery soule replenysche&thorn; with &thorn;e siht of &thorn;e perfit knoweynge of god. [1080] &para; &thorn;is blisfull Regne may man purchace be pouerte espirituell &amp; &thorn;e glorie be lowe|nesse; &thorn;e plentee of Ioye be hunger &amp; &thorn;erste; &amp; &thorn;e reste be trauayle; &amp; &thorn;<SUP>e</SUP> lyf be de&thorn;; &amp; mortificacione of sinne;
<PB REF="00000730.tif" N="698"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="684"></P>
<P>To &thorn;ilke lif he vs bringe &thorn;at bouht vs wi&thorn; his precious blode AmeN /</P>
<TRAILER>Explicit Fabula. Rectoris</TRAILER>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="part">
<HEAD>Composito huius libri hic capit licenciam. suam.</HEAD>
<P>[1081]</P>
<P>NOw preye .I. to hem all &thorn;at herken &thorn;is litel tretis or rede; &thorn;at if &thorn;ere bue any &thorn;inge in it &thorn;at like&thorn; hem; &thorn;at &thorn;ere of &thorn;ei &thorn;onken oure lorde ihesu criste of whome procede&thorn; al wite &amp; al goodenesse. [1082] &para; And if &thorn;ere be any &thorn;inge &thorn;at displesen hem .I. preye hem also &thorn;at &thorn;ei arette it to &thorn;e defaute of myne vnkonynge: &amp; n[ot] to my will. &thorn;at wolde fulfeyne haue seide better. if .I. hadd konynge; [1083] For oure booke sey&thorn;e al &thorn;at is wreten is writen for oure doctrine &amp; &thorn;at is myne entent [1084] &para; Whare for .I. be seke &yogh;owe mekely att &thorn;e mercye of god; &thorn;at &yogh;e praye for me / &thorn;at criste haue mercie on me; &amp; for&yogh;eue me my gultes; [1085] And namely of my translaciones &amp; endite|ynges of werldly vanytees &para; &thorn;e whiche .I. reuoke in my re|tractions [1086] &para; As is / &thorn;e booke of Troyles; &para; The booke also of fame &thorn;e booke of xv ladyes &para; &thorn;e booke of &thorn;e Duchesse; &thorn;e booke of seint valentynes day &amp; of &thorn;e parlement of birdes &para; &thorn;e tales of Cantur|bury &thorn;ilke &thorn;at sounen in to sinne [1087] &para; &thorn;e booke of &thorn;e lyon; And moni ano&thorn;ere booke if &thorn;ei were in myne remembraunce &amp; mony a songe; &amp; mony a lycherous laye; &thorn;at Criste for his grete Mercy for&yogh;eue me &thorn;e sinne [1088] &para; Bot of &thorn;e translacioune of Boyce de Consolacione; &para; And o&thorn;ere bokes of legendis of seintis; And omelyes &amp; moralyte; &amp; deuocions; [1089] &thorn;at &thorn;onke .I. oure lorde iesu criste &amp; his blissed moder &amp; al &thorn;e seintes of heuen; [1090] besecheinge hem &para; &thorn;at &thorn;ei from hennes for&thorn;e vnto my lyues ende sende me grace to beweyle my giltes; &amp; to stody to saluacione of my soule; And graunt me grace of verrei penance con|fessione 
<PB REF="00000731.tif" N="699"><MILESTONE UNIT="6-text p" N="685"> &amp; satisfaccioun to done in &thorn;is present lif. [1091] &thorn;oruhe &thorn;e benigne grace of him &thorn;at is kinge of kynges. &amp; priste of all pristes; &thorn;at bouht vs wi&thorn; &thorn;e precious blode of his herte [1092] so &thorn;at .I. may bie one of hem att &thorn;e daye of dome &thorn;at schal be saued. to receyue &thorn;e blisse &thorn;at euere schal last wi&thorn;outen ende. Amen.</P>
